Summary: nan

Name: Atlas Flame
Summary: Atlas Flame was one of the seven Dragons that appeared in Crocus through the Eclipse Gate. He was a close friend of Igneel, and was the creator of the Sun Village.

Name: Bacchus Groh
Summary: Bacchus Groh is an S-Class Mage of the Quatro Cerberus Guild. Renowned for his incredible alcohol tolerance (to the point that he even drank Cana Alberona under the table), he participates in the Grand Magic Games and faces off against Elfman Strauss despite the King of Fiore's request that Bacchus fight Erza Scarlet. Although Bacchus initially had the upper hand, Elfman's perseverance and quick thinking ultimately won him the battle.

Name: Bisca Connell
Summary: Bisca Connell, formerly Bisca Mulan, was originally an immigrant from the West, who moved to Magnolia and joined the Fairy Tail Guild. During the year X785, she became Alzack Connell's wife and the mother of Asuka Connell.

Name: Caitlyn (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: At least 10-B, 7-B with Weapons | At least 10-B, High 6-C with Weapons | At least 10-B, 4-B with Weapons | At least 10-B, At least 7-B with Weapons, Low 2-C via Hax

Name: Cana Alberona
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792''' | '''In X793'''
Summary: Cana Alberona is a member of the Fairy Tail Guild, and is a potential S-Class Mage. She is a heavy drinker, but hardly ever gets drunk, no matter how much she drinks. She is also the daughter of Gildarts Clive.

Name: Captain Cold (Pre-Crisis)
Summary: Once just a run-of-the-mill thief, Len Snart managed to get his hands on the 'Cold Gun', a piece of strange, futuristic technology capable of freezing seemingly anything it fired at, from people to buildings, from energy constructs to New Gods. With weapon in tole, Snart donned the identity of Captain Cold and quickly became one of Flash's most persistent and deadly foes.

Name: Carla (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Carla is an Exceed, the daughter of Queen Shagotte, and a close companion to Wendy Marvell. She and Wendy belonged to Cait Shelter before joining Fairy Tail. After the disbandment of Fairy Tail, Carla, along with Wendy, joined Lamia Scale. She's a major supporting character. Carla is a small, white Exceed with pink ears and brown eyes, which are smaller than Happy's eyes. She also has two whiskers on each side of her face. Carla wears a pink bow near the end of her tail. Carla's usual top consists of a mustard yellow and pink top with a pink bow tie. She wears a pink skirt with this top. Carla, like other characters, seems to switch outfits on a regular basis. When Carla uses Magic, she sprouts two angel-like wings to fly. Her pink Guild Mark is located on her back.

Name: Celestial Spirit King
Key: '''Celestial Spirit (Summoned by Lucy)''' | '''Celestial Spirit (Full Power)''' | '''Eclipse Celestial Spirit'''
Summary: The Celestial Spirit King is the benevolent ruler of the Celestial Spirits and the most powerful among them. He can only be summoned by breaking one of the twelve Zodiac keys. Due to the severity of his summoning conditions, he will show no mercy towards those who dare to harm his contractor.

Name: Cho'Gath
Summary: Tier: 8-B, Unknown maximum potential | At least High 6-C, Unknown maximum potential | Low 1-C

Name: Chocomon (Wallace)
Summary: Chocomon is an antagonist in Digimon Adventure 02: Digimon Hurricane Landing!! Transcendent Evolution!! The Golden Digimentals. He is one of Wallace's partner Digimon, being the twin brother of Terriermon. He was driven insane by a virus, forcing the Chosen Children to fight him to prevent him from doing irreparable damage.

Name: Cobra (Fairy Tail)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Cobra, real name Erik, is a former member of the now-disbanded Oración Seis, a Dark Guild composed of six powerful Mages. He, along with the other Oración Seis members, sought to find Nirvana, a destructive Magic that was sealed long ago. At some point before seeking Nirvana, Erik implanted a Dragon Slayer Lacrima into his own body, which thereby resulted in him becoming the Poison Dragon Slayer. Cobra was among the few remaining members who formed the Reborn Oración Seis, and later joined Crime Sorcière per Jellal's request to help him take down Zeref. In the year X793, he became the boyfriend of Kinana.

Name: Darkdramon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | 1-C

Name: Dianamon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | 1-C

Name: Ego (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ego was a Celestial, a primordial and extremely powerful entity, and the father of Star-Lord. He originally appeared to be a caring and wise father with a cocky personality, similar to his own son. However, it is later revealed that he is a ruthless entity with a god complex who wishes to conquer the universe. He is a mysterious adventurer from far parts of the galaxy who has heard the legend of the Guardians of the Galaxy following the Battle of Xandar and has come to meet them for the first time. Reunited with his son in 2014, Ego desired to forward his plan to rule the universe by using his son's Celestial genes to terraform the planets he had planted alien seedlings on. Ego's plans were foiled by the Guardians of the Galaxy and he was ultimately destroyed by their hand.

Name: Ethan (Pokémon)
Summary: Ethan is a young boy who turned 10 and went on his Pokémon journey in HeartGold and SoulSilver, 3 years after the original FireRed and LeafGreen. Having a similar story to his predecessor, on his tenth birthday he got to see his local Professor and pick out a First Partner Pokémon to take on his journey.

Name: Gabumon (Yamato Ishida)
Summary: Yamato Ishida (Matt in the dub) and Gabumon are main characters in the Digimon Adventure trilogy. Yamato is the secondary main character of 01 and Tri, next to Taichi Yagami. Yamato is the crest bearer of friendship, this can be seen in his character rather early on in the series, as he's usually looking out for his friends best interest. Yamato is the older brother of Takeru Takaishi.

Name: Gajeel Redfox (X784 to X792)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Gajeel Redfox is an Iron Dragon Slayer, a member of the Fairy Tail Guild and a former S-Class Mage of Phantom Lord. After Fairy Tail's disbandment, Gajeel joins the Magic Council and becomes the captain of the Custody Enforcement Unit, but after Avatar is defeated, he returns to Fairy Tail. Originally a Dragon Slayer from four hundred years past, Gajeel was sent to the future to assist in the destruction of Acnologia.

Name: Gaomon (Thoma H. Norstein)
Summary: Thoma H. Norstein is a coolheaded child genius who has already graduated from university. His intelligence is highly valued, even within DATS. He executes his missions based on data and theories, so his personality frequently clashes with Masaru's, who relies more on emotions.

Name: Gildarts Clive
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792''' | '''In X793'''
Summary: Gildarts Clive was the fifth Fairy Tail Guild Master, its S-Class Mage, and the guild regarded him as their most powerful member. He is also the father of Cana Alberona.

Name: Gray Fullbuster (X784 to X792)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Gray Fullbuster is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild, wherein he is a member of Team Natsu. He is infamous for his ability to subconsciously strip off his clothing due to the instincts ingrained in him by his teacher's training. Nevertheless, he's a powerful Ice Mage and one of Natsu's main rivals. Gray was from a village up in the North, but the entire village was destroyed by the Demon Deliora. Gray's parents were killed in the incident as well. Along with Ur, a powerful ice Mage, Lyon came investigating Deliora's destruction and found Gray alive among the ruins. Ur took Gray in as her second student and taught him and Lyon Ice-Make Magic. In another encounter with Deliora, his teacher used Iced Shell to seal him away in order to save and protect Gray. After this, Gray took Ur's advice to find strong wizards. This led him to Fairy Tail, where he became a member.

Name: Hoteye (Richard Buchanan)
Summary: Hoteye, real name Richard Buchanan, is a former member of the Oración Seis, a Dark Guild composed of highly powerful Mages whose goal is to find Nirvana, a destructive power that was sealed away long ago. After his release from prison, he joined Crime Sorcière per Jellal's request to help him take down Zeref. He is the elder brother of Wally Buchanan.

Name: Illaoi
Summary: Illaoi's powerful physique is dwarfed only by her indomitable faith. As the prophet of the Great Kraken, she uses a huge, golden idol to rip her foes' spirits from their bodies and shatter their perception of reality. All who challenge the 'Truth Bearer of Nagakabouros' soon discover Illaoi never battles alone - the god of the Serpent Isles fights by her side.

Name: Jayce
Summary: Tier: 7-B | High 6-C

Name: Jellal Fernandes
Summary: Jellal Fernandes is a childhood friend of Erza Scarlet. Before he lost his own memory, he was a Dark Mage who desperately sought to revive Zeref via the R-System due to Ultear's tampering. His given name at birth was Siegrain, but after witnessing his mother killed by child snatchers and imprisoned by them, he referred to him as Jellal; due to his life as Siegrain not going according to his original plan. Jellal currently serves as a member and co-founder of Crime Sorcière.

Name: Jiemma Orland
Summary: Jiemma Orland was the former Guild Master of the former strongest Mage Guild in Fiore, Sabertooth. He ended up leaving Sabertooth and became a member of the Dark Guild, Tartaros.

Name: Jura Neekis
Summary: Jura Neekis is a former Mage of the Lamia Scale Guild and one of the Ten Wizard Saints. In X792, he elected to reform the Magic Council alongside the other Ten Wizard Saints after it was destroyed in the Tartarus Arc.

Name: Kamen Rider Saber
Key: '''Beginning of Story (1-22)''' | '''Middle of Story (23-35)''' | '''Late Story (36-40)''' | '''End of Story (41-47)'''
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:KRSaber_Brave_Dragon_Sound.mp3

Name: Kinana
Summary: Kinana is a member of the Fairy Tail Guild and the former pet of Oración Seis member, Cobra. Unlike most other members of Fairy Tail, she initially joined the guild as an employee, rather than as a Mage. After Fairy Tail's disbandment she is finally able to use magic, rejoining the guild as a Mage.

Name: Kog'Maw
Summary: Belched forth from a rotting Void incursion deep in the wastelands of Icathia, Kog’Maw is an inquisitive yet putrid creature with a caustic, gaping mouth. This particular Void-spawn needs to gnaw and drool on anything within reach to truly understand it. Though not inherently evil, Kog’Maw’s beguiling naiveté is dangerous, as it often precedes a feeding frenzy—not for sustenance, but to satisfy its unending curiosity.

Name: La Garita Caldera super-eruption
Summary: Around 28-26 million years ago, a super-volcanic eruption known as La Garita super-eruption invaded the Oligocene as one, if not the most energetic occurrence throughout the entirety of Earth’s history, only behind the Cretaceous-Paleogene extinction event and other cosmic phenomena.

Name: Laxus Dreyar (X784 to X792)
Key: '''In X784 (Battle of Fairy Tail Arc)''' | '''In X784 (Tenrou Island Arc)''' | '''In X791''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Laxus Dreyar is an S-Class Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild. He is the grandson of Fairy Tail's Guild Master, Makarov Dreyar, and the son of Raven Tail's Master, Ivan Dreyar. He was expelled from the guild after the events of the Fairy Tail Fighting Festival. However, after Gildarts Clive became the 5th Master, he allowed Laxus to rejoin. After Fairy Tail's disbandment in X791, he joined the Blue Pegasus Guild along with the members of the Thunder God Tribe. However, after the guild's reformation, he rejoined Fairy Tail again along with the Thunder God Tribe.

Name: Levy McGarden
Summary: Levy McGarden is a member of Team Shadow Gear, along with Jet and Droy. She loves to read books and has a very cheerful personality, being able to get along with many other guild members. Levy and Lucy quickly became friends through their mutual interest in books. Levy's magic is called Solid Script. It allows her to make words solid and then throw the words at her opponent. For instance, if the word fire were to be thrown at her opponent the victim would feel as if he were hit by a fireball.

Name: Loma Shade (DC Comics)
Summary: Part of the Avian an alien race enslaved on the planet Meta, Loma Shade named herself after her favorite poet, Rac Shade, whose work could give her some much-needed escapism from her grim condition. Still inspired by his poems, Loma managed to get her hands on Rac's famous M-Vest, which transmitted her consciousness in the body of a comatose, brain-dead teenager named Megan Boyer. Loma took over her life, struggling to deal with her new abilities, the human lifestyle she was forced into and the consequences Megan's abuse of her classmates.

Name: Lucy Heartfilia (X784 to X792)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Lucy Heartfilia is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild and a member of Team Natsu. The daughter of Layla and Jude Heartfilia, she has a family history tied to magic; her parents were members of the guild "Love & Lucky" until Layla's pregnancy prompted them to strike out on their own. Lucy's name itself is a quirky coincidence: her parents noticed their former guild's name, missing a "K," read "Love & Lucy." Her father founded the influential Heartfilia Konzern, one of Fiore's wealthiest organizations. Following her mother Layla's death, Lucy's relationship with her father deteriorated, leading to years of loneliness and neglect. Seeking a new life, she ran away from home, hoping to join Fairy Tail. During her journey, she encountered Natsu Dragneel and Happy, who rescued her from the corrupt wizard Bora and ultimately brought her into the Fairy Tail Guild, where she's been a valued member ever since.

Name: Macao Conbolt
Summary: Macao Conbolt is a veteran Mage of Fairy Tail, and their Fourth Guild Master, following the disappearance of Makarov Dreyar and those who were with him.

Name: Mandarin (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Mandarin was born the child of Mongolian and British aristocrats, both of whom died shortly after his birth. He was raised by his aunt, who was bitter about not being the inheritor of the family fortune and decided to twist his mind, raising him to be vain and bloodthirsty.

Name: Mard Geer Tartaros
Summary: Mard Geer Tartaros was an Etherious of the Dark Guild Tartaros and is known as the "Underworld King" and the "Absolute Demon", having placed himself in charge of the guild in E.N.D.'s absence. He is tall, lean, and has the appearance of a young man. Often seen wearing a smirk, Mard is a cool, collected, yet arrogant man who plays himself off as being extremely intelligent; he quite regularly refers to himself in the third person. Much like the rest of his kind, Mard belittles humans, and thinks of them as nothing more than insects.

Name: Marin Hollow
Summary: Marin Hollow is a soldier in the Alvarez Empire's Imperial Army, and a former member of Brandish Squad, that serves directly under the Shield of Spriggan, Brandish μ.

Name: Mature (King of Fighters)
Key: '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '96)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Max Alors
Summary: Max Alors is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild who is in charge of most of the guild's social activities, given his love for talking to people. His Magic is a type of Sand Magic: Sandstorm.

Name: Mest Gryder
Summary: Mest Gryder is a member of Fairy Tail, a former member of the Magic Council, and a former Division Head of the Rune Knights. In X784, he used his Memory Control to deceive the members of the Fairy Tail so that he could infiltrate the guild, while in actuality he was always a member of Fairy Tail who erased his own memories to successfully infiltrate the aforementioned Magic Council, using the alias Doranbolt.

Name: MetalGarurumon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | High 7-A | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least High 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | At least 5-B

Name: Midnight (Macbeth)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Midnight, real name Macbeth, was a Dark Mage of the Oración Seis: a Dark Guild composed of highly powerful Mages whose goal was to find a Magic known as Nirvana, a very destructive power that was sealed away long ago. After the rebirth of the Oración Seis, Midnight referred to himself as Brain II. He joined Crime Sorcière as an Independent Mage after his escape from prison, per Jellal's request to help him take down Zeref.

Name: Millianna
Summary: Millianna is one of Erza Scarlet's childhood friends from their days as slaves at the Tower of Heaven, having additionally worked as one of Jellal's minions for a time. She is currently a Mage of the all-female guild—Mermaid Heel. She is an avid cat lover, having decorated her entire room with a cat theme.

Name: MirageGaogamon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B, 1-C with Burst Mode

Name: Motherglare
Summary: Motherglare was one of the seven Dragons who invaded Fiore through the malfunctioning Eclipse Gate.

Name: Natsu Dragneel (X784 to X791)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Beginning of Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X791 (End of Tartaros Arc)'''
Summary: Natsu Dragneel is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild, wherein he is a member of Team Natsu. He is the younger brother of Zeref Dragneel, having originally died 400 years ago, being subsequently revived as his brother's most powerful Etherious, E.N.D. (Etherious Natsu Dragneel). During this time, Zeref brought him to his friend, Igneel to be raised and taught Dragon Slayer Magic. He also had his signature scarf knitted from Igneel's molted scales by Anna. He is among the five Dragon Slayers sent to the future from four hundred years past, having an additional purpose in the assistance of the defeat of Acnologia. He was then found by Makarov and was brought to Fairy Tail, where he would become a member.

Name: Orga Nanagear
Summary: Orga Nanagear is a Lightning God Slayer and one of the five strongest Mages of Sabertooth, the former strongest Guild in Fiore, in terms of power.

Name: Ouryumon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | At least 6-C | At least High 6-C | At least 5-B, possibly 1-C

Name: Panther Lily
Summary: Panther Lily is an Exceed that used to work for the kingdom of Edolas as the Magic Militia's First Division Commander of the Royal Army. He is a member of the Fairy Tail Guild and is Gajeel Redfox's companion. During the time Fairy Tail was disbanded he was a member of the Magic Council however rejoined Fairy Tail after the guild returned.

Name: Paracelsus (Fate)
Summary: Caster is a Caster-class Servant of Manaka Sajyou in the First Holy Grail War of Fate/Prototype: Fragments of Sky Silver. He is also able to be summoned by Ritsuka Fujimaru in the Grand Orders of Fate/Grand Order, debuting in the London Singularity.

Name: Rac Shade (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Where dark falls dark despite the light, I touch. I smell. I breathe. I beat. Running off to the great blue. Our hearts, now lost, just fade away.

Name: Racer (Sawyer)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Racer, real name Sawyer, is a former member of the now-disbanded Dark Guild: the Oración Seis. He also led another Dark Guild, Harpuia, his so-called "personal Guild". In X791, Sawyer was among the remaining Oración Seis members who comprised the Reborn Oración Seis. After his escape from prison, he became an Independent Mage of Crime Sorcière, who joined per Jellal's request to help him take down Zeref.

Name: Raikou (Pokémon)
Summary: Raikou (Japanese: ライコウ Raikou) is an Electric-Type Legendary Pokémon. Along with Entei and Suicune, it is one of the Legendary beasts resurrected by Ho-Oh after the burning of the Brass Tower. Of the three Legendary beasts, Raikou is said to represent the lightning strike which ignited the fire that consumed the Brass Tower.

Name: Rapidmon
Summary: Tier: At least High 6-C | At least High 6-C | 1-C

Name: Ravemon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B, 1-C with Burst Mode

Name: Rogue Cheney (Future)
Summary: Future Rogue Cheney is Rogue Cheney's future counterpart. He was originally thought to have traveled back in time to kill Lucy Heartfilia, who closed the Eclipse Gate and left the world at the mercy of the 10,000 Dragons. However, his true intent lies in his bid to kill Acnologia and become the new Dragon King.

Name: Rufus Lore
Summary: Rufus Lore is a Mage of Sabertooth: the former strongest guild in Fiore. He is also known as "The Minstrel Who Sings to the Red Moon".

Name: Sarah Kerrigan
Key: '''Ghost Operative''' | '''Queen of Blades''' | '''Primal Queen of Blades''' | '''Xel'Naga'''
Summary: Sarah Kerrigan is a Terran Psionic and the Queen of Blades. Originally an agent of the Dominion, she was an incredible sniper. Eventually, she was betrayed by her commanding officer, Emperor Arcturus Mengsk, and left for dead. She was not killed, however, and was instead infected by the Zerg Overmind. Her psionic potential vastly increased, she wielded devastating power and was a terror to all who encountered her, effortlessly tearing through entire armies.

Name: ShineGreymon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B, 1-C with Burst Mode | 1-C

Name: Skarner
Summary: One of the brackern, Skarner is an immense crystalline scorpion from a hidden valley in Shurima. Known for their great wisdom and deep connection to magic, the brackern’s bodies are fused with powerful life crystals which hold the living thoughts and memories of their ancestors. In an age long past, they entered hibernation to avoid destruction—but recent, threatening events have roused Skarner, and he now strives to protect his dormant kin from those who would harm them.

Name: SkullKnightmon
Summary: SkullKnightmon is an elder brother who exchanged cups of brotherhood with Deadly Axemon. As a knight that excels in cunning, its behavior is based on its policy, "Those who are knights must fight. Even more importantly than fighting, they must win," and it places great importance on attaining a victorious outcome at any rate. In order to achieve that, it will unabashedly use all means, no matter how underhanded. It specializes in combat that capitalizes on the size of its body, and the manner in which it dives at the opponent's chest, swinging its "Spear Needle", shows off actions one would not expect from a knight that has forgotten its pride.

Name: Taiki Kudo and Shoutmon (Manga)
Key: '''Shoutmon''' | '''Shoutmon X2''' | '''Shoutmon X3''' | '''Shoutmon X4''' | '''Shoutmon X5''' | '''OmegaShoutmon''' | '''Shoutmon DX''' | '''Shoutmon X6''' | '''Shoutmon X7''' | '''Shoutmon EX6''' | '''Shoutmon X7 Superior Mode'''
Summary: To make the whole world happy!!! That's the King that I am for!!!

Name: The Protagonist (Digimon World: DS)
Summary: The Protagonist of Digimon World: DS is a young boy who stumbled upon the Digital World while investigating rumors he heard about "Digital Monsters". Later found by ClavisAngemon after observing the Digimon instruct a group of aspiring Tamers, the boy was allowed to become a full-fledged Tamer himself, proving to be exceptionally capable. After Unknown D began brainwashing his fellow Tamers to turn them against each other, the protagonist took it upon himself to stop Unknown D and later save the entire Digital World.

Name: TigerVespamon
Summary: Tier: 9-B | High 8-C | 6-C | At least High 6-C, higher with Nitro Stinger | 5-B, higher with Nitro Stinger

Name: Toby Horhorta
Summary: Toby Horhorta is a Mage of the Lamia Scale Guild and subsequently a member of Team Lyon.

Name: Ultear Milkovich
Summary: Ultear Milkovich is a female Mage and the daughter of Ur. She is a former member of the Magic Council. She was also a former member of Grimoire Heart, where she was the leader of the Seven Kin of Purgatory. She has also disguised herself as a masked individual named Zalty. After defecting from the Dark Guild, she became an Independent Mage and co-founder of Crime Sorcière, until she left following the conclusion of the X791 Grand Magic Games.

Name: Urgot
Summary: Tier: 7-B | High 6-C

Name: Vel'Koz
Summary: Tier: 8-B | 7-A | High 6-C

Name: Vice
Key: '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '96)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Viktor (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: 7-B | High 6-C

Name: Volcdramon
Summary: Volcdramon is a volcanic dragon Digimon that inhabits the magma beds of the active volcanoes that dot the Digital World. It is said that volcanic eruptions occur due to the activity of Volcdoramon, so the Digital World's volcanologists study not volcanic activity, but the activity of Volcdoramon and the stirring of volcanoes. Although its appearance is that of a terrifying figure, its personality is gentle, and it is not the type to like conflict. However, if it's offended just once, you will surely suffer its scorching attacks like a "raging fire".

Name: Wakaba Mine
Summary: Wakaba Mine is a veteran Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild. He is a long-time friend of Macao Conbolt, acting as his adviser during Macao's tenure as the guild's Fourth Guild Master.

Name: Warren Rocko
Summary: Warren Rocko is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild. He is a telepath and invented a magical communication device.

Name: Xerath
Summary: Xerath is an Ascended Magus of ancient Shurima, a being of arcane energy writhing in the broken shards of a magical sarcophagus. For millennia, he was trapped beneath the desert sands, but the rise of Shurima freed him from his ancient prison. Driven insane with power, he now seeks to take what he believes is rightfully his and replace the upstart civilizations of the world with one fashioned in his image.

Name: Yuka Suzuki
Summary: Yuka Suzuki, is a Mage of Lamia Scale Guild and one of Lyon Vastia's allies. He serves as the guild's anti-Mage, as his Wave Magic can cancel out others' Magic.

Name: Yukino Agria
Summary: Yukino Agria is a Celestial Spirit Mage and a member of the former strongest Guild in Fiore, Sabertooth. She is also the younger sister of Sorano. She once had a family consisting of her parents and an older sister, Sorano. Her parents were killed by an attack from a group of Zeref's followers and her sister was captured. Since that day, her goal is to stop Zeref in any possible way.

Name: Zacian
Summary: nan

Name: Zamazenta
Summary: Zamazenta is a Legendary Fighting Type Pokémon which gains the Steel Type when changing in the Crowned Shield form, gained from getting the Rusted Shield. It's native of the Galar Region and is also known as the Fighting Master's Shield due to its ability to defect any attacks. Along with Zacian it was able to save the Galar Region from the Darkest Day, an event happened 3'000 years ago which would have brought total chaos and destruction to the Region if it wasn't stopped.

Name: Zygarde
Summary: Zygarde is a Dragon/Ground Type Legendary Pokémon introduced in Generation VI. It's hypothesized that it's monitoring those who destroy the ecosystem from deep in the cave where it lives. When the Kalos region's ecosystem falls into disarray, it appears and reveals its secret power.

Name: Ash Ketchum
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Original Series)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Advance Generation through Best Wishes)''' | '''Pokémon Team (XY)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Sun and Moon)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Journeys)'''
Summary: Ash Ketchum (Japanese: サトシ Satoshi) is the main character of the original Pokémon anime. He is also the main character of various manga based on the anime, including The Electric Tale of Pikachu, Ash & Pikachu, Magical Pokémon Journey, and Pocket Monsters Diamond & Pearl, including some direct adaptations like the Pokémon Journeys manga.

Name: Asmodeus (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: I have heard it said evil is nothing more than good’s absence, as if evil was the darkness to good’s light. A comforting thought, I imagine, for those seeking redemption, but, I tell you, put such thoughts from your mind. You need only peer into a demon’s eyes to know evil is not some vacuum waiting for virtue to come and fill its emptiness. Evil is a force. It is an influence in the cosmos, an agency equal to or perhaps even greater than its antithesis. There are two sides in this eternal struggle, one light and the other dark. You might find evil’s works reprehensible, yet to those whose hearts belong to corruption, good deeds are equally deplorable. Understand, there is no redemption, only treason against the side you were born to serve.

Name: Cervantes de Leon
Key: '''Original Timeline w/Soul Edge''' | '''Original Timeline w/o Soul Edge''' | '''New Timeline Resurrected'''
Summary: Cervantes de León is a character in the Soul series of fighting games. Cervantes made his first appearance as the main antagonist of Soul Edge and has returned in all of the games. He is the father of Ivy Valentine and is an undead pirate who travels the seven seas in order to loot, kill and steal the souls of anyone he kills.

Name: Dendar
Summary: Dendar is a primordial serpent that according to legend, came into existence as soon as the first being slept and had a nightmare. She has, for the eternity of the multiverse, consumed all of the most foul and dreaded nightmares and visions dreamt by mortals and deities alike and if not for her, all nightmares would be remembered in crucial details. It is said that she will also be the harbinger to the end of the world and the gods.

Name: Dragotha
Summary: Dragotha was once a powerful dragon residing in the upper layers of the Nine Hells, and was among the most powerful of the companions of his consort, Tiamat, evil queen of all dragons. Eventually, he was sentenced to death for slaying a fellow dragon- and thus began his rise to immortality through lichdom, assisted to eternal life by an unknown deity of death (though supposedly this was done by Nerull).

Name: Dream Larva
Summary: Dream Larva are among the mightiest denizens of the Dream Realm, a mental plane of existence spanning the entirety of the multiverse. They are the misbegotten children of gods of fancy, dreams, and desire. Such is the might of a Dream Larva that they are often summoned by powerful spellcasters to slay their enemies with reckless abandon.

Name: Ein (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Shadow PKMN Lab)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Realgam Tower)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Deep Colosseum)'''
Summary: Ein (Japanese: ボルグ Borg) is one of the original four Cipher Admins. A cruel and callous young scientist, he is long on ambition and short on emotion. He is obsessed with the idea of creating an insanely powerful Pokémon at any cost which he managed to do with amazing results.

Name: Eldes
Summary: Eldes (Japanese: エルデス Eldes) is the younger brother of Ardos and one of the five Cipher Admins of Pokémon XD: Gale of Darkness.

Name: Ezreal
Summary: Tier: Unknown, 7-B with Magic, potentially Low 6-B with Ne'Zuk's Gauntlet | Unknown, 4-B with Magic | Unknown, 7-B with Magic, 2-A via hax, up to Low 1-C | 4-B

Name: Father Llymic
Summary: Father Llymic is an Elder Evil imprisoned in a glacier, the monster being in truth a fragment of alien thought given flesh. He was allowed into this reality by the Vast Gate, a portal created by the Elves that peered into the eldritch Far Realm.

Name: Fire Giant
Summary: Strong and proud, the Fire Giants are the artisans of the Giant race. They stand at around 18 feet tall, always being clad in armor and carrying a weapon. They build massive forts, using their immunity to fire to have them be located in areas of great heat.

Name: Flesh Golem (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Created by various evil spellcasters across D&D, a Flesh Golem is various bodies sown together and animated through magic in order to create a minion for one's bidding. Flesh Golems can be created from various creatures ranging from humans, Scale Ones, and all the way to demons. No matter what a Flesh Golem is a fierce enemy to face in combat.

Name: Forge Guardian
Summary: The Forge Guardian are powerful golems made by Moradin after the events of the founding to protect the divine furnaces and hearths that made the first dwarves on Exandria, as well to test those that wish to use them to craft powerful items.

Name: Galaxia (Anime)
Summary: Galaxia is Meta Knight's signature blade used for any type of combat. It's a sentient sword with mystical power, and was manufactured by the gods, or at least a leader in command. Though it is similar to it, Comparing this Galaxia to its counterpart sustained in Kirby's franchise of games, it still acts differently, as it has a life and mind of its own.

Name: Galio
Summary: Tier: 7-C, Low 6-B against Magic | 7-A, Low 6-B against Magic

Name: Genius Loci
Summary: Genius loci, or "Local Spirit", is a section of landscape that manifests itself as a sentient creature with a mind replicated from those around it- the spirit dominates an avatar and uses it as its force, focus, or mind. Examples of genius loci include very small moons, mountains, valleys, caverns, lakes, and so on- any land mass that has remained totally undisturbed for long periods of time may form its own spirit of the land.

Name: Gibbering Orb
Summary: Gibbering Orbs are believed to be the ancestors to Beholders, giant floating masses of eyes and mouths wandering the cosmos, constantly muttering to itself about madness beyond human ken. Each mouth performs a different action- many chant, others scream, and some merely drone on and on about eldritch knowledge.

Name: Gnoll (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: It is His blessing.

Name: Hagunemnon
Summary: Hagunemnons, also known as Proteans, are a species constantly in fluid motion- even from birth they are constantly changing shape and taking on attributes of that which they imagine and those around them. They are the penultimate shapeshifters, fused with chaos so that they have no true form. A protean is a hateful being for this reason, scouring the cosmos for new forms to take.

Name: Hoary Hunter
Summary: Hoary Hunters are dreadful fey creatures given the appearance of a snowy-white human or elf. Their goals are simple- they hunt intelligent life for sport. Their goal does not end there, however- the objective is to capture, not kill, and to drag them to the Unseelie Court and imprison them there for all eternity.

Name: Hunefer
Summary: Hunefers are the mummified remains of demigods- creatures with a shred of a divine spark left over. Unlike their fellow Undead, Hunefers are agile and dexterous. They are soulless, much like all other undead- their spirits have departed to the Astral Isles, and now they seek to take back their former divine power. The Hunefer is the leftover- when a deity rises to power with a new body once more, the Hunefer is the flesh left behind.

Name: Iggwilv
Summary: The horn of Iggwilv pierces the heart look over your shoulders before you start. How many sorrow? Foolish men, because they didn't turn back then.

Name: Inevitable
Summary: Inevitables are the judges of the gods, extensions of cosmic law. Many are forged in the extraplanar city of Sigil, and are tasked with upholding specific contracts written up in the halls of the city. Originally these creatures were made by Primus, and even the most wily and secretive of traders will enter into contracts with them- nothing is more straightforward and true than the ideals that forge the Inevitable's will. Inevitables care not for intent or purpose- only for the words written in their contracts. Lethal force is used to ensure such words are stood by.

Name: Infernal (Dungeons & Dragons)
Summary: Even Gods can be seduced. Born from this unholy tryst Infernals roam the lower planes, bound to exile by divine decree. Feared and unloved by all, Infernals bide their time until they can let loose their plans to tear the multiverse into ribbons.

Name: Ithyak-Ortheel
Summary: Ityak-Ortheel is a colossal creature residing deep within the depths of the Abyss, born from the blood of the god Gruumsh following his battle with Corellon Larethian. As he was born from hatred, he is hatred- pure hatred for the Elves, seeking to destroy and annihilate them whenever possible.

Name: Jax (League of Legends)
Summary: Runeterra’s greatest weapons master, Jax is the only survivor of the Kohari—champions sworn to the defense of Icathia. But when the Void was unleashed against the Shuriman empire’s Ascended Host, Icathia was destroyed, leaving Jax without a home or purpose. He gathered the “last light of Icathia”, a symbol of his hope to one day defeat the Void, and now travels the world, searching for warriors strong enough to face the coming darkness by his side.

Name: Ketheric Thorm
Summary: How can she be gone? Where did she go? The Moonmaiden cannot be so unfeeling - so cruel. Not toward her most devoted servant. Not after Melodia. It makes no sense. It makes no sense. I won't survive it. That much I know. Forgetting is the only possibility. The embrace of oblivion. The reprieve of nothingness. It would not be possible for a man to survive knowing what he knows. Knowing what can be lost. Shar understands that. Hers is the only mercy I can comprehend. My mind is full of holes - yet not enough. The emptiness. The time. The nothingness. And still I remember. Still I remember it all. There is no mercy in this beating heart. There is no mercy in life at all.

Name: Kezef the Chaos Hound
Summary: Kezef the Chaos Hound is a powerful Elder Evil and has been referenced as a primordial by some. The hound hungers after souls, devouring them so completely that no being in the multiverse can restore them. It is famed for hunting the god Mask for all of eternity. Following his release by the Mad God Cyric, Kezef is known to target the faithful more than any other- those that believe in the gods are his victims, and those that are soon to be slain are only aware of an overwhelming aura of pure and utter hatred. He is covered with writhing maggots that spew horrific acid at his foes.

Name: Kingdom of Blackmoor
Summary: An ancient nation that predates the modern world of Mystara. Possessing hyper-advanced technology, Blackmoor was able to construct weapons of enormous destruction and objects of incredible power. Prideful and arrogant, eventually they destroyed themselves when a nuclear reactor went critical and destroyed the majority of their civilization. The survivors of Blackmoor would colonize another planet, but like before their arrogance resulted in their destruction.

Name: Klysandral
Summary: Klysandral was, in life, a proud, gallant paladin who had once stole an artifact of power from Asmodeus. His party ventured into Hell itself to gather the gem known as the Vallis Crystal and placed it in the hands of a powerful temple of Neheod. The Lord of Nessus initially chose to forget this, for holding a grudge against mere mortals was seen as a petty act- however, eventually, he began putting forth some machinations to once again gain access to the gem.

Name: Kree (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Gleen Talbot: You're telling me that we got our asses handed to us by little green men. Phil Coulson: They were big and blue.

Name: Kuva Guardian
Summary: Wearing heavy armor and adorned in red cloth, the Kuva Guardians are among the fighting elite in the Queens' army. The Kuva Guardians will surround their enemies and with just a few well-placed blows, bring Tenno to their knees. They are followed around by mischievous Jester-like creatures that are quick to attack and are quite deadly.

Name: Kyoya Tachibana (Light Novel)
Summary: Kyoya Tachibana is a summoned Otherworlder from the Farmus Kingdom. He was among a trio of Otherworlders sent to frame the monster citizens of Jura-Tempest Federation as hostile to humanity.

Name: Kyuss, the Worm that Walks
Summary: Kyuss, the Worm that Walks was once a necromantic prophet of a decadent society that was cast out for his utterings of an ominous future age, the Age of Worms, in which all would come to ruin and Kyuss would become the God-Ruler. Instead of rotting in his exile, Kyuss drew to him thousands of followers and rebuilt an ancient evil city as his citadel.

Name: LeShay
Summary: LeShay are enigmatic, immortal elf-like creatures and are believed to be one of the creator races, species that originated in Abeir-Toril and created its first empires. The LeShay are among the mightiest of the fey creatures, though prefer to not reveal their nature, pretending to merely be albino elves.

Name: Malkizid, the Branded King
Summary: Malkizid, the Branded King is a former Solar of immense power. After having been corrupted by the influences of Lolth, he fell from grace following an ill-fated rebellion; Corellon Larethian punished him for his impudence with a brand notifying all of his folly. This brand constantly bleeds and inflicts horrible things on those who witness it, courtesy of the Elven God.

Name: Marrake al-Sidan al-Hariq ben Lazan
Summary: Marrake al-Sidan al-Hariq ben Lazan is a noble Efreeti who at an unknown point in time became the Sultan of the City of Brass, and he was known for his love for gambling and great strength.

Name: Mind Flayer (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Mind Flayers are horrific, eldritch creatures associated with the dark depths of the D&D settings. They are renowned for being horrendously evil and for their mental capacities. Mind Flayers thrive by devouring the minds of other creatures, generally only interacting with other species at all to eat them or to enslave their kind.

Name: Modron
Summary: Quote? You desire a quote? The One and the Prime does not give 'quotes'.

Name: Molly McIntyre
Summary: Molly McIntyre is a student at Luna Nova Academy who came across the secret Horologium Chamber after being bullied about her lack of magical talent. With the power of the Horologium Clock, she gained the ability to control time and practice as many times as she pleased without anyone there to judge or ridicule her. However, when she abused this power to go back in time before she even attended Luna Nova, she was afflicted with the Curse of Time, and doomed to the fate of becoming the Ghost Witch with the professors having no other choice but to seal her away in the chamber. Two-hundred years later, her uncorrupted human half left Atsuko Kagari and her friends a book that gave instructions on how to unseal the chamber. This would in turn, activate the chamber's failsafe and trap them and the school in a time loop. With Akko gradually learning the truth, she makes it her mission to save Molly from her fate and end the curse for good.

Name: Mordekaiser
Summary: Tier: At least Low 6-B, possibly 4-B | 7-A | High 6-A | 4-B | Low 1-C

Name: Muu
Summary: Mū was a shinobi and the Second Tsuchikage of Iwagakure. During his lifetime, Mū was renowned as the "Non-Person" due to his ability, which left him with neither a physical form nor a detectable chakra signature. He served as the bodyguard of Ishikawa, the First Tsuchikage, during the First Five Kage Summit, and was also the mentor of Ōnoki.

Name: Obould Many-Arrows
Key: '''Orc Chief''' | '''King of the Citadel of Many-Arrows''' | '''Exarch of Gruumsh'''
Summary: Obould Many-Arrows is widely regarded as the most iconic orc in the Forgotten Realms, and a recurring opponent of Drizzt Do'Urden and Bruenor Battlehammer, among others. A cunning and intelligent creature even by human standards, Obould established himself as an Orcish power when he wiped out and took in several other orcish tribes, establishing a kingdom in the Spine of the World. Eventually, Obould signed a peace treaty (much to the dismay of his followers) with elf, human, and dwarf, cementing the existence of his kingdom as a major power in Faerun.

Name: Pandorym
Summary: They brought it. They brought it and trapped it, though many gave their lives to do so. They brought it to threaten the gods, which they did. And the gods responded. But the evil remains, imprisoned. Biding. Planning. Seething.

Name: Paracelsus (Fate)
Summary: Caster is a Caster-class Servant of Manaka Sajyou in the First Holy Grail War of Fate/Prototype: Fragments of Sky Silver. He is also able to be summoned by Ritsuka Fujimaru in the Grand Orders of Fate/Grand Order, debuting in the London Singularity.

Name: Phane
Summary: Time lost Abominations, the Phanes are the unwanted children of time deities. The Phane are not imprisoned like most Abominations, instead they are "lost" in time. Sent so far into the past or future that time itself has no meaning, the Phanes are usually stuck there in permant isolation. However sometimes a Phane manages to break through the fourth dimension to return to a more modern time, where they seek to alter the fate of nations, worlds, and planes— for the worse.

Name: Rad (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Rad is a relatively new Immortal, only being a few hundred years old. However, unlike almost every other Immortal, Rad did not complete any of the five Petitions to Immortality. Instead, he used an ancient magically enhanced nuclear reactor to transcend his mortal form. Disliked by most of the other Immortals due to this reason, Rad eventually came to blows with some of the others until the Old Ones came to claim him as one of their own.

Name: Ragnorra, Mother of Monsters
Summary: Ragnorra, Mother of Monsters, is described as "a primeval source of life" originating before the time of the gods, a pure sentient force creating monstrous life on any world she touches, aiming to fill the cosmos with the creatures she so loves. The Astral Sea bears silver runes telling of her return to the Prime Material to do much of the same to this world, and all the other worlds she has visited, with each tale ending in the destruction and corruption of all life she touches.

Name: Rakshasa (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Rakshasa''' | '''Greater Rakshasa''' | '''Ak'chazar''' | '''Naztharune''' | '''Dread Knight''' | '''Lord of Dust''' | '''Zakya''' | '''Half-Dragon Rakshasa''' | '''Naityan Rakshasa''' | '''Overlord'''
Summary: Rakshasa are fiendish creatures born from the Lower Planes with the appearance of humanoid tigers of proud stature, distinguishable from similar creatures such as Weretigers by their hands, which can bend both backwards and forwards. Extravagant and conniving by nature, Rakshasa plague all the Planes with their manipulations, constantly enacting plots to achieve greater power. They serve countless masters- their own Rajahs, demon lords[1], yugoloths, night hags, and even the mightiest of devils. As manipulators and masterminds, the Rakshasa ply their trade from their luxuriously decorated palaces, subtly tipping the scales in planar and political conflicts as it suited their wants.

Name: Red Dragon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Wyrmling to Young''' | '''Juvenile to Mature Adult''' | '''Old to Ancient''' | '''Wyrms and Great Wyrms'''
Summary: And belching fire, and began to lunge down

Name: Saryn
Summary: Saryn is a poison-themed Warframe controlled by the Tenno to undergo tasks assigned to them by The Lotus, a mysterious figure whose motive is to preserve their kind.

Name: Sertrous
Summary: Sertrous is a demonic serpent and former lesser demon lord of the Abyss who resisted the call of the Demon Queen to take up arms against their elemental enemies. Sertrous, who had slain every demon sent to recruit him, was in turn slain by the queen, who destroyed him entirely and cast him into the space between planes, where the only form he could muster was that of a feeble writhing snake.

Name: Shape of Fire
Summary: Shapes of Fire are powerful undead that result from powerful creatures perishing by the hottest flames in existence. They are the literal manifestation of flame and malice, appearing as a humanoid shape of pure white fire, with piercing red eyes.

Name: Sirrush
Summary: Sirrushes are among the most dangerous predators to wander the lands of the planes, predatory cat-like creatures of large size that specialize in the takedown of prey far more dangerous than any other predator can easily hunt. They prefer the hunting of fully-grown dragons, for even a single dragon can feed a sirrush's pack for a week.

Name: Soelma Nilaenish
Summary: Soelma Nilaenish is an ancient and scholarly elf woman who became a wizard and loremaster. After her guardian, an aunt, died, she was left alone from the young age of 196. Throughout her life she has studied much and seen all, leaving her reclusive but highly intelligent. She is considered extraordinary among scholars in her fields.

Name: Storm (Marvel Comics)
Summary: nan

Name: Tarrasque (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Tarrasque is considered to be the ultimate challenge in Dungeons and Dragons. Its origin is shrouded in mystery, often suggested to be a punishment from the gods, a personification of nature's wrath, a creation of the Primordials, or an alien force. It is recognized for its virtual invincibility, superb strength, ravenous appetite, and tendency to lie dormant for months or years before rising to devour everything in its path.

Name: The Hulks of Zoretha
Summary: The Hulks of Zoretha are an alien set of statue-like creatures that lie dormant, much akin to other Elder Evils, ever since their entering into this world. While dormant they are worshiped by many cults aiming to awaken them to begin their purification of this world.

Name: The Infinity Sword
Summary: Born from the Infinity Pool, the combined sword and gems are made into the most powerful item in the universe, with which the user will become God.

Name: The Leviathan
Key: '''Aspect of the Leviathan''' | '''Greater Aspect of the Leviathan''' | '''The Leviathan'''
Summary: Sharp tooth and merciless of fang,

Name: Tiamat (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Tiamat is the mighty Queen of the Dragons and among the most iconic enemies of Dungeons and Dragons, appearing in all media from the game itself to video games, cartoons, and so on. Long before the mortals were born, there were gods and primordials, creating chaos and law as they saw fit. One such being was Asgorath, the first dragon who battled a terrifying Primordial in an event known as the Dawn War. Despite his impressive strength, Asgorath was overcome- but from his corpse split two entities, one good, one evil, who destroyed their father's murderer and created the foundations for the Dragon Pantheon. These beings were Bahamut (the Good) and Tiamat (the Evil).

Name: Treant (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Living tree; the "'Treant"' serves as the forest's guardian. They are generally peaceful but will attack any evil creature or those who carelessly use fire. Treants come in many varieties, with some having creatures like Rot Grub on their bodies to combat pests.

Name: Trixie Lulamoon
Summary: Trixie Lulamoon is a recurring character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, being a staple of the series since Season 1.

Name: Ultra Concentrated Ether Light Sphere
Summary: The Ultra Concentrated Ether Light Sphere is a Lacrima whose destructive power is approximately 500 times that of Jupiter. It can vaporize everything within a specific area.

Name: Uvuudaum
Summary: Uvuudaums are the Lords of the Far Realm, presiding over all other things and are quite literally manifestations of the Far Realm itself, so far above those such as Father Llymic that they create such a distance between such monsters and themselves as their minions make between themselves and those of the Prime. The mere presence of an Uvuudaum is enough to drive even the strongest of wills to absolute madness.

Name: World Rune
Summary: Centuries ago, magical artifacts called World Runes were rediscovered. Over the following decades after such event, knowledge of the Runes began to spread as more were unearthed. The world’s brightest minds studied the ancient glyphs, attempting to determine the powers they possessed. Few could even begin to understand the importance of their origins, or the sheer power held within them. Some surmised that the Runes were integral to the creation of Runeterra itself. The first use of these mysterious artifacts proved catastrophic, as they reshaped the landscape of entire nations. Mistrust quickly grew as those who knew of the Runes imagined such “Makers’ Might” being used as a weapon. Conflicts later related to these magical artifacts were known as the Rune Wars.

Name: Zargon
Summary: Who can stand against the might of Zargon the Returner? Surely, no man is strong enough of courage and skill to face my master in combat. No god would dare confront him, for he has brought low others before. Nay, when Zargon awakens, all shall tremble as the world is born anew in his foul image.

Name: Zuggtmoy
Summary: In Zuggtmoy's Cradle your body shall sleep,

Name: Bad (Metal Bat)
Summary: Bad (バッド, Baddo?), also known by his hero alias Metal Bat (金きん属ぞくバット, Kinzoku Batto?), is an S-Class hero, ranked 15 in the Hero Association. Despite his low status among the S-Class heroes, he is considered one of the strongest. Metal Bat's "Kiai" (fighting spirit) is the key to his strength; the more damage he takes, the stronger he becomes. His power grows in direct proportion to his injury and mental state, to the point where he can eventually defeat superior opponents on his own. Metal Bat typically treats both his allies and enemies badly. However, he is a kind and gentle soul to his younger sister.[1]

Name: Baraggan Louisenbairn
Summary: Baraggan Louisenbairn (バラガン・ルイゼンバーン, Baragan Ruizenbān) is an Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and the Segunda (2nd) Espada.

Name: Blade Knight
Summary: Blade Knight is a character portrayed as a swordsman and knight featured in the Kirby series. He's a regular enemy across stages, which Kirby can turn into a Helper ally in some games. Blade Knight gives Kirby the Sword Copy Ability when swallowed, function he shared with Sword Knight in classic titles. Star Allies implies he wants to conquer the world.

Name: Broom Hatter
Summary: Broom Hatter is a character in the Kirby series that gives Kirby the Clean ability when swallowed.

Name: Cang Du
Summary: Cang Du (蒼都ツァン·トゥ, Tsan Tu?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Stern Ritter with the designation "I" - "The Iron".

Name: Edward Weevil
Summary: Edward Weevil is one of the Royal Shichibukai, and is the self-proclaimed son of Whitebeard. He is violent, cruel, but most notable – a momma's boy. He believes that family relates solely to blood, and thus hates the Whitebeard alliance, as they claim to be the sons of Whitebeard despite having no blood connection to him.

Name: Evil Natural Water
Summary: Evil Natural Water (エビル天然水てんねんすい, Ebiru Tennensui?) is a mighty being that works for the Monster Association, an elite group of horrifying creatures working to dismantle the Hero Association.

Name: FLDSMDFR
Origin: Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs
Summary: The Flint Lockwood Diatonic Super Mutating Dynamic Food Replicator, or FLDSMDFR for short, is the machine which the two Cloudy With A Chance Of Meatballs movies revolve around.

Name: Flint Lockwood
Origin: Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs
Summary: Flint Lockwood is an eccentric and revolutionary inventor, from the town of Swallow Falls, who dreams of creating amazing things that can change everyone's life. He is the main character and protagonist of Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs and Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs 2.

Name: Garou
Key: '''Hero Hunter''' | '''Half-Monster''' | '''Post-Darkshine''' | '''Post-Sage Centipede''' | '''Awakened Garou''' | '''Parallel Timeline Awakened Garou'''
Summary: Saitama: Hey, you got a little better again! Garou: You call this a little?!

Name: Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez
Summary: Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez (グリムジョー・ジャガージャック, Gurimujō Jagājakku?) is an Arrancar and was the Sexta (6th) Espada in Sōsuke Aizen's affiliated army.

Name: Ichigo Kurosaki (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''Substitute Soul Reaper''' | '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Post-Bankai Training''' | '''Post-Visored Training''' | '''Final Grimmjow Fight''' | '''Full Hollowfication''' | '''Post-Resurrection''' | '''Post-Dangai Training'''
Summary: Ichigo Kurosaki (黒崎くろさき 一いち護ご, Kurosaki Ichigo?) is the son of Masaki and Isshin Kurosaki, a Quincy with the powers of a Soul Reaper. Years after the death of his mother, Ichigo uses his innate spiritual awareness to help local ghosts, and unlocks his potential as a Soul Reaper when Rukia Kuchiki comes along in pursuit of a Hollow.

Name: Jesus Burgess
Summary: Jesus Burgess, nicknamed "Champion", is the helmsman and captain of the First Ship of the Black Beard Pirates. During this time his bounty was of 20,000,000 belly.

Name: Kanata Amane
Summary: Kanata Amane is an angel girl from the Celestial Academy. She's still in training and is currently studying the art of healing people. Perhaps as a way to hide her shyness, Kanata tries to act cool or pull pranks on others, backed-up by a slight sadistic streak... but her rate of success is limited. Atypical from the expectations one may have of an angel, Kanata has monstrous physical strength, a heated temper, has a knack for violence, her anger often blows up and she rarely shows angelic attributes. Her wings are detachable, but doing so causes her intense pain.

Name: Kenpachi Zaraki
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Nnoitora Fight''' | '''Yammy Fight''' | '''Post-SAFWY Novel''' | '''Post-Unohana Training''' | '''CFYOW Novel'''
Summary: Kenpachi Zaraki (更ざら木き 剣八けんぱち, Zaraki Kenpachi?) is the current captain of the 11th Division in the Gotei 13. He is the eleventh Soul Reaper to hold the position and the name Kenpachi, branding him as the strongest Soul Reaper in martial combat. True to his title, Kenpachi is bloodthirsty and reckless, loving nothing more than a good fight and intentionally impairs himself to prolong what would otherwise be an overly swift battle. Despite this, he has some level of compassion for his subordinates, and is rarely seen without his lieutenant and closest friend, Yachiru Kusajishi.

Name: Love Aikawa
Summary: Rabu Aikawa (愛川 羅武, Aikawa Rabu), more commonly referred to as Love (ラヴ, Ravu), is a Visored and the former captain of the 7th Division. His lieutenant was Jin'emon Kotsubaki.

Name: Momiji
Summary: Momiji (紅葉) is Kureha's younger sister and Ryu Hayabusa's apprentice who first appears in Ninja Gaiden Dragon Sword. She later appeared as a playable character in Ninja Gaiden Sigma 2 and an NPC in both Ninja Gaiden 3 and Yaiba: Ninja Gaiden Z. Like Kasumi, she is available as a free DLC Character in Ninja Gaiden 3: Razor's Edge for the Wii U system and as an unlockable character for the Xbox 360 and PS3 systems.

Name: NaNaNa Najahkoop
Summary: NaNaNa Najahkoop (ナナナ・ナジャークープ, Nanana Najākūpu?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "U" - The Underbelly.

Name: Nelliel Tu Odelschwanck
Summary: Nelliel Tu Odelschwanck (ネリエル・トゥ・オーデルシュヴァンク, Nerieru Tu Ōderushuvanku?) is the former Tres (three) Espada. She is also known as Nel Tu (ネル・トゥ, Neru Tu?), and she is a small, good-natured, childlike Arrancar. She lives in the desert of Hueco Mundo with her adoptive brothers and former Fracción, Dondochakka Birstanne and Pesche Guatiche, and their pet, Bawabawa.

Name: Nnoitra Gilga
Summary: Nnoitora Gilga (ノイトラ・ジルガ, Noitora Jiruga?) is the 5th Espada of Sosuke Aizen, formerly the 8th. As an Espada, the aspect of death he symbolizes is despair.

Name: Onimaru (One Piece)
Summary: Onimaru is a komagitsune who was once the companion of the late Daimyo of Ringo, Shimotsuki Ushimaru.

Name: Rojuro Otorobashi
Summary: Rojuro Otoribashi (鳳おう橋とりばし 楼ろう十じゅう郎ろう, Ōtoribashi Rōjūrō?), more commonly referred to as Rose (ローズ, Rōzu?), is the captain of the 3rd Division in the Gotei 13 and a Visored. His lieutenant is Izuru Kira. He was also a Captain over 100 years ago prior to his exile and was reinstated to his old post sometime after the battle against Sosuke Aizen.

Name: Rushia Uruha
Summary: Rushia Uruha is a talented necromancer from the Underworld Academy. She's shy and introverted, but dislikes being alone, so she often talks with spirits and the damned. Rushia appears to be sweet, soft-spoken and innocent, as she's easily impressed by others' skills or by new experiences. While not wrong, she also has a strong temper in which she becomes enraged and screams in an uncharacteristically beast-like manner when she gets angry, before regaining her composure. The switch between her two behaviors is quick and sudden. She gets along very well with Marine Houshou, though they have a complicated romantic relationship.

Name: Sage Centipede
Summary: Sage Centipede (ムカデ仙せん人にん, Mukade Sennin?) is an immensely large centipede-like monster, far surpassing the likes of Elder Centipede in both size and monstrosity, possessing an immense 6666 arms. He claims to have emerged to destroy the "abominable fist" that opposes "God".

Name: Sword Knight
Summary: Sword Knight is a character portrayed as a swordsman and knight featured in the Kirby series. In most cases, he's seen as an enemy, but in other cases, he's shown to be a temporary acquaintance, like a helper.

Name: Tier Harribel
Summary: Tier Harribel (ティア・ハリベル, Tia Hariberu?) is the 3rd Espada of Sosuke Aizen's army, and, following his defeat, the ruler of Hueco Mundo. As an Espada, the aspect of death she symbolizes is sacrifice.

Name: Todd Ingram
Summary: Todd Ingram is Ramona Flowers's third ex-boyfriend. He is in a relationship with Envy Adams (cheating on Envy with Lynette Guycott) and the bass player for The Clash at Demonhead. He is also a Vegan, though known to cheat on both his vegan diet as well as his girlfriend, believing he can get away with mostly anything because he's a rock star.

Name: Ulquiorra Cifer
Summary: I envy because of the heart

Name: Zephyr (One Piece)
Summary: "Black Arm" Zephyr, also known as Z, was the leader of the Neo Marines and the main antagonist of One Piece Film: Z. He was once a Marine admiral and instructor before his resignation.

Name: Aaroniero Arruruerie
Summary: Aaroniero Arruruerie is the 9th Espada of Sosuke Aizen's army. He is the only remaining first-generation Espada and the only one of their numbers to have once been a Gillian-class Hollow, having increased his power far beyond its former bounds by consuming tens of thousands of other Hollows and gaining their abilities. As an Espada, the aspect of death he symbolizes is greed.

Name: Agrias Oaks
Summary: Lady Agrias Oaks is a secondary character appearing in Final Fantasy Tactics, initially as a guest character working together with Ramza Beoulve through the story, finally joining him during the events of Chapter 2.

Name: Ann Takamaki
Key: '''Beginning of the Game''' | '''Early Game''' | '''Mid Game''' | '''Late Game''' | '''End Game'''
Summary: Ann Takamaki is one of the founding members of the Phantom Thieves of Hearts. The classmate of Ren Amamiya and Ryuji Sakamoto, she is one of the first playable characters in Persona 5. Ann was shunned because of her looks and didn't have many friends before meeting the protagonist. Along with the other Phantom Thieves of Hearts, Ann hopes to reform society by stealing the hearts of the corrupt.

Name: Apple Bloom
Summary: Tier: At least 9-B, likely 8-A | Likely 6-B

Name: Applejack
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Applejack is one of the main protagonists of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Ashura Doji (One Piece)
Summary: Ashura Doji is a retainer of the Kozuki Family as one of the Nine Red Scabbards once led by Kozuki Oden. After Oden's death he returned to being a criminal under the name Shutenmaru, assuming leadership of the Mt. Atama Thieves. He initially severed his ties with the Kozuki Family in the present but rejoined after witnessing Yasuie's death.

Name: Ayon
Summary: Ayon (アヨン, Ayon) is a Chimera-like Hollow created by the Quimera Parca ability, made from left arms of Tier Harribel's fraccion.

Name: Azwel
Summary: Azwel is a character who first appeared in the reboot of the Soul series Soul Calibur Vl as one of the antagonists of the series. He serves as the main antagonist of the Libra of Souls Story. He calles himself the "Leader of Humanity" and plans to gather the power of both Soul Edge and Soul Calibur in order to create the Ultimate Seed.

Name: Bambietta Basterbine
Summary: Bambietta Basterbine (バンビエッタ・バスターバイン, Banbietta Basutābain?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "E" - "The Explode".

Name: Basil Hawkins
Summary: Basil Hawkins is an infamous pirate known as the "Magician" and the captain of the Hawkins Pirates. He came from the Grand Line and is one of twelve pirates who are referred to as the "Worst Generation" (Formerly known as the "Eleven Supernovas"). His previous known bounty amounted to 249,000,000, but after the time skip it was raised to 320,000,000.

Name: Berenice Gabrielli
Summary: Berenice Gabrielli (ベレニケ・ガブリエリ, Berenike Gaburieri) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "Q" - "The Question".

Name: Big McIntosh
Summary: Big McIntosh is a supporting character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, and he is Applejack's older brother.

Name: Black Maria
Summary: Black Maria is one of the Tobiroppo, the strongest six Headliners of the Beasts Pirates, she owns her own brothel on Onigashima.

Name: Black Sperm
Summary: Black Sperm (黒くろい精せい子し, Kuroi Seishi?) is a monster who first appeared during the S-Class Heroes' raid of the Monster Association.

Name: Byakuya Kuchiki
Summary: Even if I scatter and never bloom again

Name: Cang Du
Summary: Cang Du (蒼都ツァン·トゥ, Tsan Tu?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Stern Ritter with the designation "I" - "The Iron".

Name: Charlotte Chuhlhourne
Summary: Charlotte Chuhlhourne (シャルロッテ・クールホーン|Sharurotte Kūruhōn) is the 20th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and one of Baraggan Louisenbairn's six Fracción.

Name: Charlotte Cracker
Summary: Charlotte Cracker, also known as Thousand Arms Cracker, is the 10th son of Big Mom and Totto Land's Minister of Biscuits. He has eaten the Bisu Bisu no Mi, allowing him to produce large numbers of biscuit crackers and reshape them in any form he wishes. He usually inhabits and fights from the inside of an enormous biscuit puppet crafted with his powers, to the point his bounty poster depicts the puppet and not his real face. He was first revealed within the Wholecake Island arc when encountering Monkey D. Luffy and Nami. He is the first of the Three Sweet Commanders to have been revealed.

Name: Charlotte Katakuri
Summary: The third of the Sweet Commanders to appear, Charlotte Katakuri is the second son of the Charlotte Family and the oldest of a set of fraternal triplets, his younger brothers being Daifuku and Oven.

Name: Choe Neng Poww
Summary: Choe Neng Poww (チーノン・ポウ, Chīnon Pō) is the 25th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and one of Baraggan Louisenbairn's six Fracción.

Name: Daring Do
Summary: Daring Do is a a secondary character in the show My Little Pony.

Name: Denjiro
Summary: Denjiro is a samurai who served as Kozuki Oden's retainer, being one of the Nine Red Scabbards.

Name: Derpy Hooves
Summary: Derpy Hooves is the most popular background character of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Dondochakka Birstanne
Summary: Dondochakka Birstanne (ドンドチャッカ・ビルスタン, Dondochakka Birusutan) is one of Nelliel Tu Odelschwanck's Fracciónes, alongside Pesche Guatiche.

Name: Donquixote Doflamingo
Summary: The third of the Seven Warlords to be formally introduced, Donquixote Doflamingo (ドンキホーテ・ドフラミンゴ, Donkihōte Dofuramingo?) is captain of the Donquixote Pirates and the former king of Dressrosa. Sly, rude and disrespectful towards the World Government, Doflamingo is very sadistic towards others and seems to delight in causing and participating in chaos. However, he is affectionate towards his crew, who in turn all respect him, referring to him as "Doffy".

Name: Dordoni Alessandro Del Socaccio
Summary: Dordoni Alessandro Del Socaccio (ドルドーニ・アレッサンドロ・デル・ソカッチオ, Dorudōni Aressandoro Deru Sokacchio) was Arrancar Cientecimo Tercero (103rd) in Sōsuke Aizen's army prior to being killed by Rudbornn Chelute and later resurrected by Mayuri Kurotsuchi.

Name: Driscoll Berci
Summary: Driscoll Berci (ドリスコール・ベルチ, Dorisukōru Beruchi) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "O" - "The Overkill".

Name: Edrad Liones
Summary: Edrad Liones (エドラド・リオネス, Edorado Rionesu) is Arrancar Trece (13) in Sōsuke Aizen's army and one of Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez's five Fracción.

Name: Emilou Apacci
Summary: Emilou Apacci (エミルー・アパッチ, Emirū Apacchi) is the 54th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and one of Tier Harribel's three Fracción, collectively known as the Tres Bestias.

Name: Findorr Calius
Summary: Findorr Calius (フィンドール・キャリアス, Findōru Kyariasu) is the 24th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and one of Baraggan Louisenbairn's six Fracción.

Name: Flash Magnus
Summary: Flash Magnus is one of the six Pillars of Equestria.

Name: Flashy Flash
Summary: Flashy Flash (閃せん光こうのフラッシュ, Senkō no Furasshu?) is an S-Class hero, Rank 13 for the Hero Association. As his nickname would imply, he's well known for his extraordinary speed. He was the classmate of Sonic in the 44th period of the Ninja Village. For some reason, he destroyed the Ninja Village and killed all the instructors, officials, and classmates during the graduation exams.

Name: Fluttershy
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Fluttershy is one of the main protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Franky
Key: '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: "Iron Man" Franky, real name Cutty Flam, is the shipwright of the Straw Hat Pirates under captain Monkey D. Luffy. As his epithet implies, he is a cyborg, having rebuilt his own body from iron scraps after he was run over by a sea train. He was formerly a member of a criminal shipbreaking gang called the Franky Family, which operated in the shipbuilders' haven of Water 7. He encountered the Straw Hats when he and the Franky Family brutally beat Usopp and stole a great deal of money from the crew while they were attempting to get their boat fixed on the island. However, his interests subsequently aligned with the Straw Hats' when the secret government organization CP9 kidnapped both him and their crewmate Nico Robin in a bid to construct the ancient superweapon Pluton, which he owned the blueprints to. After escaping the clutches of CP9, Franky decided to join their crew, drawn by their dedication to both their ship and their fellow crewmen.

Name: Gale Wind
Summary: Gale Wind (疾風のウィンド, Hayate no uindo) was a powerful ninja, who originated from the same village as Speed-o'-Sound Sonic and Flashy Flash. He was from the 37th graduating class, known as "Golden," along with his partner Hellfire Flame. Originally a human, he eventually decided to join the Monster Association while becoming a monster himself, as he sympathized with the association's goal of ruling over the world. However, his main goal was to kill the S-Class hero, Flashy Flash.

Name: Gantenbainne Mosqueda
Summary: Gantenbainne Mosqueda (ガンテンバイン・モスケーダ, Gantenbain Mosukēda) is the 107th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army.

Name: Gild Tesoro
Summary: Gild Tesoro is the main antagonist of One Piece Film: Gold. He is a non-canon character.

Name: Gin Ichimaru
Summary: Gin Ichimaru (市丸 ギン, Ichimaru Gin) was the captain of the 3rd Division of the Gotei 13 until he betrayed Soul Society, alongside Sōsuke Aizen and Kaname Tōsen. His lieutenant was Izuru Kira. He formerly served as the lieutenant of the 5th Division under Sōsuke Aizen and the 3rd Seat of the 5th Division under Shinji Hirako.

Name: Gouketsu
Summary: Gouketsu was a formidable monster dispatched by Psykos to infiltrate the "Super Fight" martial arts tournament, destroying anyone in his way.

Name: Grøh
Summary: Grøh is a character who appeared in the Soul series reboot Soul Calibur Vl. He serves as one of the main protagonists of the Libra of Souls storyline. He is a member of the Aval Organization, an organization form to clear the world of Malfested also known as "Outsiders" by Aval. Grøh is considered to be the strongest fighter of Aval and one of the most loyal members. Throughout the story, his goal is to hunt down and kill Azwel who betrayed the Aval Organization. But he also has a personal reason for going after Azwel as he forced him to kill his best friend Curtis after he turned him into a Malfested right before his eyes and having him try to kill Grøh. It turns out that Grøh is one of Azwel's successful experiment in terms of enhancing warriors with the power of Soul Edge shards. As such he technically counts as an "Outsider" and plans to kill himself once his job is done.

Name: Guenael Lee
Summary: Guenael Lee (グエナエル・リー, Guenaeru Rī) is a creation of Gremmy Thoumeaux's The Visionary ability, originally thought to be a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "V – Vanishing Point".

Name: Guernika (One Piece)
Summary: Guernika was one of the best agents for the World Government's top group of secret agents and assassains, known as Cipher Pol 0. He was first seen on Dressrosa, where he aided Donquixote Doflamingo in setting up a trap for Trafalgar Law by helping Doflamingo fake his resignation from the Seven Warlords.

Name: Hellfire Flame
Summary: Hellfire Flame (業火のフレイム, Gōka no fureimu) was a powerful ninja, who originated from the same village as Speed-o'-Sound Sonic and Flashy Flash. He was from the 37th graduating class, known as "Golden," along with his partner Gale Wind. Originally a human, he eventually decided to join the Monster Association while becoming a monster himself, as he sympathized with the association's goal of ruling over the world. However, his main goal was to kill the S-Class hero, Flashy Flash.

Name: Hiyori Sarugaki
Summary: Hiyori Sarugaki (猿柿 ひよ里, Sarugaki Hiyori) is the former lieutenant of the 12th Division under Captains Kirio Hikifune and Kisuke Urahara, and currently a Visored.

Name: Homeless Emperor
Summary: Homeless Emperor was once a common tramp who encountered a mysterious divine entity, who claimed to be "God", that gave him the incredible power of summoning energy spheres similar to little suns, which explode on contact and create huge flaming bursts.

Name: Ichigo Kurosaki (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''Substitute Soul Reaper''' | '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Post-Bankai Training''' | '''Post-Visored Training''' | '''Final Grimmjow Fight''' | '''Full Hollowfication''' | '''Post-Resurrection''' | '''Post-Dangai Training'''
Summary: Ichigo Kurosaki (黒崎くろさき 一いち護ご, Kurosaki Ichigo?) is the son of Masaki and Isshin Kurosaki, a Quincy with the powers of a Soul Reaper. Years after the death of his mother, Ichigo uses his innate spiritual awareness to help local ghosts, and unlocks his potential as a Soul Reaper when Rukia Kuchiki comes along in pursuit of a Hollow.

Name: Ikkaku Madarame
Summary: Ikkaku Madarame (斑目 一角, Madarame Ikkaku) is the lieutenant and former 3rd Seat officer in the 11th Division of the Gotei 13, under Captain Kenpachi Zaraki.

Name: Inuarashi
Summary: Duke Inuarashi is a canine mink and one of the two rulers of the Mokomo Dukedom, dubbed the "Ruler of Day" as he rules over the Mokomo Dukedom from 6:00 AM to 6:00 PM. He and Nekomamushi serve as retainers for the Kozuki Family of Wano Kingdom.

Name: Isane Kotetsu
Summary: Isane Kotetsu (虎徹 勇音, Kotetsu Isane) was the lieutenant of the 4th Division under Captain Retsu Unohana, but after Unohana’s death during the Thousand-Year Blood War, she was promoted to the rank of Captain.

Name: Isshin Kurosaki
Summary: Isshin Kurosaki (黒崎 一心, Kurosaki Isshin), formerly known as Isshin Shiba (志波 一心, Shiba Isshin), is the former captain of the 10th Division, husband of Masaki Kurosaki, father of Ichigo Kurosaki, Karin Kurosaki, and Yuzu Kurosaki. Isshin is the former head of a branch of the Shiba Clan and the current head of the Kurosaki family.

Name: Izou (One Piece)
Summary: Izou was the former commander of the 16th division of the Whitebeard Pirates and a former retainer of the Wano Country daimyo Kozuki Oden. He was the older brother of fellow retainer Kikunojo.

Name: Izuru Kira
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War'''
Summary: Izuru Kira (吉良 イヅル, Kira Izuru) is the lieutenant of the 3rd Division in the Gotei 13, formerly under Captain Gin Ichimaru and currently under Captain Rōjūrō Ōtoribashi.

Name: Jack (One Piece)
Summary: Jack, also known by his epithet the Drought, is an All-Star of the Beast Pirates, one of the top three executives of the crew second only to the Emperor Kaidou in terms of authority. Together with his comrades King and Queen, they are informally referred to as the Calamities, due to their respective epithets relating to natural disasters.

Name: Jerome Guizbatt
Summary: Jerome Guizbatt (ジェローム・ギズバット, Jerōmu Gizubatto) is a Quincy and member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "R" - "The Roar".

Name: Jinbe
Summary: "Knight of the Sea" Jinbe is a whale shark fishman, the helmsman of the Straw Hat Pirates, the second captain of the Sun Pirates after Fisher Tiger, and a former Shichibukai, who attained the position eleven years ago.

Name: Jūshirō Ukitake
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Jūshirō Ukitake (浮竹 十四郎, Ukitake Jūshirō) was the captain of the 13th Division in the Gotei 13. At one point in time, his lieutenant was Kaien Shiba, and later was Rukia Kuchiki, who would eventually take his place as the 13th Division Captain.

Name: Kamikaze (Atomic Samurai)
Summary: Kamikaze (カミカゼ, Kamikaze?), also known by his hero alias Atomic Samurai (アトミック侍ざむらい, Atomikku Zamurai?), is the S-Class Rank 4 professional hero for the Hero Association.

Name: Kaname Tōsen
Summary: Kaname Tosen (東仙とうせん 要かなめ, Tōsen Kaname?) was the former captain of the 9th Division until he betrayed the Soul Society alongside Sosuke Aizen and Gin Ichimaru.

Name: Kawamatsu
Summary: Kawamatsu, also known as Kawamatsu the Kappa is a fish-man who is a yokozuna-ranked sumo wrestler. As a child, he was shipwrecked in Wano and orphaned soon afterwards. After Kozuki Oden rescued him from citizens ostracizing him, he went on to serve as one of Oden's Nine Red Scabbards until Oden's death 20 years ago.

Name: Keiji Mogami
