Summary: Keiji Mogami is "This Century's Greatest Psychic" and former Psychic who turned into an evil spirit upon death.

Name: Kenpachi Zaraki
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Nnoitora Fight''' | '''Yammy Fight''' | '''Post-SAFWY Novel''' | '''Post-Unohana Training''' | '''CFYOW Novel'''
Summary: Kenpachi Zaraki (更ざら木き 剣八けんぱち, Zaraki Kenpachi?) is the current captain of the 11th Division in the Gotei 13. He is the eleventh Soul Reaper to hold the position and the name Kenpachi, branding him as the strongest Soul Reaper in martial combat. True to his title, Kenpachi is bloodthirsty and reckless, loving nothing more than a good fight and intentionally impairs himself to prolong what would otherwise be an overly swift battle. Despite this, he has some level of compassion for his subordinates, and is rarely seen without his lieutenant and closest friend, Yachiru Kusajishi.

Name: Kensei Muguruma
Summary: Kensei Muguruma (六車 拳西, Muguruma Kensei) is the Captain of the 9th Division in the Gotei 13. His lieutenants are Shūhei Hisagi and Mashiro Kuna. He is a Visored. He was also a Captain over 100 years ago prior to his exile and was reinstated to his old post sometime after the battle against Sōsuke Aizen.

Name: Kevin Flynn
Summary: Kevin Flynn: The Grid, A digital frontier. I tried to picture clusters of information as they moved through the computer. What did they look like? Ships? Motorcycles? Were the circuits like freeways? I kept dreaming of a world I thought I'd never see. And then, one day... Sam Flynn: You got in? Kevin Flynn: That's right man, I got in.

Name: Killer (One Piece)
Summary: "Massacre Soldier" Killer is a pirate and subordinate of Eustass Kid. He is one of twelve pirates who are referred to as the "Worst Generation" (formerly known as the "Eleven Supernovas"). After the timeskip, his bounty has been raised from 162,000,000 to 200,000,000.

Name: Kin'emon
Summary: Kin'emon is a samurai from the Wano Country and the leader of the Nine Red Scabbards, a group of powerful warriors at the disposal of Kozuki Oden. During the invasion that Kaido did in Wano, Kin'emon and a group of other samurais were sent into the future by the powers of Kozuki Toki's Devil Fruit.

Name: King Thorax
Summary: King Thorax is a character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Kisuke Urahara
Key: '''Early Arrancar Arc''' | '''Late Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Kisuke Urahara (浦原うらはら 喜き助すけ, Urahara Kisuke?) is the former captain of the 12th Division, as well as the founder and 1st President of the S.R.D.I. His lieutenant was Hiyori Sarugaki. He lives in the Human World where he owns a small convenience store that sells Soul Reaper items. He is assisted by his employees Tessai Tsukabishi, Jinta Hanakari, and Ururu Tsumugiya.

Name: Kurozumi Kanjuro
Summary: Kanjuro is one of the Nine Red Scabbards that served Kozuki Oden when the latter was the Daimyo of Kuri. Much like the other Scabbards, Kanjuro aligned himself with Oden on his own to become a loyal retainer.

Name: Kūkaku Shiba
Summary: Kukaku Shiba (志波しば 空鶴くうかく, Shiba Kūkaku?) is the head of the Shiba Clan. She is the older sister of Ganju Shiba, the younger sister of the late Kaien Shiba, as well as the niece of Isshin Kurosaki.[3] She is also a personal friend of Yoruichi Shihoin.

Name: Legato Bluesummers
Summary: Legato Bluesummers (レガート・ブルーサマーズ, Regāto Burūsamāzu) is a man who devoted himself to Knives. His main goal to have Vash experience eternal pain and suffering. He's the secondary antagonist of the Trigun series and serves directly under Knives, which also gives him command over the Gung-Ho-Guns, especially while Knives is injured as a result of the July Incident. He is the only one of the Gung-Ho-Guns without a number, as pointed out by Elendira the Crimsonnail, which means he's far less dispensable to Knives than the rest of them.

Name: Lisa Yadomaru
Summary: Lisa Yadōmaru (矢胴丸 リサ, Yadōmaru Risa) is a Visored and the current Captain of the 8th Division. She is the former lieutenant of the 8th Division under Captain Shunsui Kyōraku.

Name: Loly Aivirrne
Summary: Loly Aivirrne (ロリ·アイヴァーン, Rori Aivān) is the 33rd Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army. She and Menoly Mallia served as Aizen's aides.

Name: Lord Boros
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:BorosIntroduction.ogg

Name: Lord Boros' Ship
Summary: Lord Boros's Ship is the gigantic aircraft that he and the rest of the Dark Matter Thieves use to travel around space. It landed on Earth for the purpose of finding a legendary warrior of prophecy to give Boros the fight he had always yearned for.

Name: Lord Tirek
Summary: Lord Tirek is the sixth main villain of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, acting as the main antagonist for the season four finale Twilight's Kingdom.

Name: Luppi Antenor
Summary: Luppi Antenor was the 6th Espada in Sosuke Aizen's army for a short period of time, having temporarily replaced Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez after he lost his arm.

Name: Masaki Kurosaki
Summary: Masaki Kurosaki (黒崎 真咲, Kurosaki Masaki) was an Echt Quincy, the wife of Isshin Kurosaki, and mother of Ichigo Kurosaki, Karin Kurosaki, and Yuzu Kurosaki. She was the last surviving member of her family, and was taken in by the Ishida family before an incident with a Hollow led her to live a life with Isshin Kurosaki.

Name: Maser Cannon
Key: '''War of the Gargantuas''' | '''Post-War of the Gargantuas and ahead'''
Summary: The Maser Cannon (メーサー兵器) is a fictional weapon featured in many of Toho's sci-fi and fantasy films, making its first appearance in the 1966 film The War of the Gargantuas. There have been several varieties, but each function in a similar way and have a similar appearance. Variations of the Maser have appeared in 13 films thus far. Since their inception, Maser Cannons have typically been employed as anti-kaiju weapons, due to the ineffectiveness of conventional military weaponry against them.

Name: Mask De Masculine
Summary: Mask De Masculine (マスク・ド・マスキュリン, Masuku Do Masukyurin) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "S" - "The Superstar".

Name: Mayuri Kurotsuchi
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Mayuri Kurotsuchi (涅くろつち マユリ, Kurotsuchi Mayuri?) is the captain of the 12th Division in the Gotei 13 and 2nd president of the Shinigami Research Institute. His previous lieutenant was Nemu Kurotsuchi, his artificially-created "daughter" and his current lieutenant is Akon. He formerly served as the 3rd Seat of the 12th Division under Kisuke Urahara.

Name: Menoly Mallia
Summary: Menoly Mallia (メノリ•マリア, Menori Maria) is the 34th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army. She and Loly Aivirrne served as Aizen's aides.

Name: Meteor (One Punch Man)
Summary: The Meteor was a giant extraterrestrial rock from outer space in the One-Punch Man series.

Name: Momiji
Summary: Momiji (紅葉) is Kureha's younger sister and Ryu Hayabusa's apprentice who first appears in Ninja Gaiden Dragon Sword. She later appeared as a playable character in Ninja Gaiden Sigma 2 and an NPC in both Ninja Gaiden 3 and Yaiba: Ninja Gaiden Z. Like Kasumi, she is available as a free DLC Character in Ninja Gaiden 3: Razor's Edge for the Wii U system and as an unlockable character for the Xbox 360 and PS3 systems.

Name: Monkey D. Luffy (Emperor)
Summary: Monkey D. Luffy (モンキー・Ｄディー・ルフィ, Monkī Dī Rufi?), known as "Straw Hat Luffy", is the main protagonist of the manga and anime, One Piece. He's the son of Monkey D. Dragon, a revolutionary considered "The World's Most Dangerous Criminal"; the grandson of Monkey D. Garp, a powerful Marine Vice-Admiral who had cornered the late Pirate King himself on several occasions; the sworn brother of late "Fire Fist" Portgas D. Ace and Revolutionary chief of staff Sabo; and the foster son of Curly Dadan. He seeks to find One Piece and become the Pirate King; to accomplish this, he founded the Straw Hat Pirates and set out on the high seas at age 17 in search of the elusive treasure, beginning a series of increasingly odd and dangerous adventures. He has eaten the Gum-Gum Fruit, which turned his body into rubber and gives him stretching powers; he's developed great mastery and creativity with his powers, creating two unique techniques with them: Gear 2nd, which makes him much faster, and Gear 3rd, which allows him to inflate any body parts for a stronger attack. During the time-skip, he has a new technique: Gear 4th, which makes him much stronger and faster than even the other two Gears, but with a considerable cost to it. During his battle with Kaidou in Onigashima, Luffy manages to awaken the true potential of his Devil Fruit, the Hito Hito no Mi: Model Nika, tapping into his Gear 5th, granting his rubber-like body increased physical strength and freedom, limited only by his imagination.

Name: Monkey D. Luffy (Post-Timeskip)
Summary: Monkey D. Luffy (モンキー・Dディー・ルフィ, Monki Di Rufi?), known as "Straw Hat Luffy", is the main protagonist of the manga and anime, One Piece. He's the son of Monkey D. Dragon, a revolutionary considered “The World's Most Dangerous Criminal”; the grandson of Monkey D. Garp, a powerful Marine Vice-Admiral who had cornered the late Pirate King himself on several occasions; the sworn brother of late "Fire Fist" Portgas D. Ace and Revolutionary chief of staff Sabo; and the foster son of Curly Dadan. He seeks to find One Piece and become the Pirate King; to accomplish this, he founded the Straw Hat Pirates and set out on the high seas at age 17 in search of the elusive treasure, beginning a series of increasingly odd and dangerous adventures. He has eaten the Gum-Gum Fruit, which turned his body into rubber and gives him stretching powers; he's developed great mastery and creativity with his powers, creating two unique techniques with them: Gear 2nd, which makes him much faster, and Gear 3rd, which allows him to inflate any body parts for a stronger attack. During the time-skip, he has a new technique: Gear 4th, which makes him much stronger and faster than even the other two Gears, but with a considerable cost to it. With the support from Silvers Rayleigh and the desire to reunite with his crew after the Sabaody Island Incident and the Marineford War, he endured vigorous training on the island of Ruskaina where he learned the 3 forms of Haki, and out of the three, he specialized in “Haoshoku Haki”.

Name: Morgana (Persona)
Key: '''Beginning of the game''' | '''Early Game''' | '''Mid Game''' | '''Late Game''' | '''End Game'''
Summary: Morgana is a playable character in Persona 5.

Name: Mysterians
Summary: The Mysterians (ミステリアン) are a race of aliens created by Toho that first appeared in the 1957 film The Mysterians.

Name: Nami (One Piece)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypeia Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Sabaody Archipelago Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Whole Cake Arc''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Nami, also known by her epithet "Cat Burglar", is the navigator of the Straw Hats who was initially introduced as a thief who detested pirates and stole from them, tagging along Luffy with dubious loyalty to him. However, it is revealed that her surrogate home, the Conomi Archipelago, was occupied by the Arlong Pirates and she only wished to buy her home back. When Luffy freed the archipelago from Arlong’s grip, she fully joined the Straw Hats afterward.

Name: Nekomamushi
Summary: Nekomamushi is one of the two active rulers of Zou alongside Inuarashi.

Name: Nianzol Weizol
Summary: Nianzol Weizol (ニャンゾル・ワイゾル, Nyanzoru Waizoru) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "W" - "The Wind".

Name: Nico Robin
Key: '''Alabasta Arc''' | '''Skypiea Arc''' | '''Thriller Bark Arc''' - '''Sabaody Archipelago Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Adventurer, archaeologist, ex-Dragon, and Ms. Exposition, Nico Robin is one of the darker and more enigmatic members of the Straw Hats.

Name: Nightmare (New Timeline)
Summary: Nightmare is one of the two main antagonist of Soul Calibur VI alongside Azwel. He is the host, wielder and living incarnation of the cursed sword, Soul Edge, the objective of most other characters in the story. Nightmare is merely the host body of Inferno and when defeated, Inferno takes over and combats the opponent if not try and coerce them into grabbing Soul Edge, transforming them into a new Azure Knight. This particular Nightmare has Siegfried as a host.

Name: Orochi (One Punch Man)
Summary: "Monster King" Orochi is an extremely powerful Mysterious Being and one of the lead members of the Monster Association. Formerly a human, he was a fighting genius who turned his back on humanity and was transformed into a monster by Gyoro Gyoro.

Name: Page 1
Summary: Page One is a member of the Beast Pirates, holding the rank of a Head-liner and is a member of the Flying Six. He is introduced as he and X-Drake were sent to kill the Soba Shop owner by the name of Sangoro (Sanji) on the orders of Queen.

Name: PePe Waccabrada
Summary: PePe Waccabrada (ペペ・ワキャブラーダ, Pepe Wakyaburāda) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "L" - "The Love".

Name: Pesche Guatiche
Summary: Pesche Guatiche (ペッシェ・ガティーシェ, Pesshe Gatīshe) is one of Nel Tu's "brothers" and protectors.

Name: Pharynx
Summary: Pharynx a minion in the My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic series.

Name: Pinkie Pie
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''Post-bonding with Chaosville''' | '''With Chaos Magic''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Pinkie Pie is one of the main protagonists of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Psykos (One-Punch Man)
Summary: "Third Eye" Psykos (サイコス, Saikosu?) is a former friend of Fubuki that turned into a monster within One-Punch Man. She used to be the soft-spoken, dorky colleague of B-Class Fubuki that wanted to make use of her telekinetic powers to help the world. But ever since a horrifying vision of the future led her to insanity, she became the terrifying leader of the Monster Association, a group that boasts some of the mightiest Dragon level threats in the world, of which include herself. Her power is on a level that seemed to gain some respect from Orochi.

Name: Queen (One Piece)
Summary: Queen, also known by his epithet the Plague, is an All-Star of the Beast Pirates, one of the top three executives in charge of the crew, operating directly under the Emperor Kaidou. Along with his comrades King and Jack, they are informally referred to as the Calamities, for their respective epithets that each correspond to a natural disaster.

Name: Queen Chrysalis
Summary: Queen Chrysalis is the third main villain in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Quilge Opie
Summary: Quilge Opie (キルゲ・オピー, Kiruge Opī?) is the "Executive Hunting Captain" (統とう括かつ狩しゅ猟りょう隊たい長ちょう, Tōkatsu Shuryō Taichō?) of the first Jagdarmee of the Wandenreich. He is also a member of the Sternritter with the designation "J" - "The Jail", and is known as Quilge Opie of "the Jail" ("監獄ザ・ジェイル"のキルゲ・オピー, "Za Jeiru" no Kiruge Opī?).

Name: Rainbow Dash
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Rainbow Dash is one of the main protagonists of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Rangiku Matsumoto
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War'''
Summary: Rangiku Matsumoto (松本 乱菊, Matsumoto Rangiku) is the lieutenant of the 10th Division of the Gotei 13, serving under Captain Tōshirō Hitsugaya.

Name: Rarity
Key: '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Possessed by a Spell Book''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Rarity is one of the main protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Red Dragon (My Little Pony)
Summary: The Red Dragon was a dragon that lived in a mountain and decided to sleep for over a hundred years. His snoring could cause Equestria to be covered in smoke. This would cause Princess Celestia to assign the Mane 6 to tell the dragon to sleep further away from Equestria.

Name: Reigen Arataka
Summary: Arataka Reigen is Mob's mentor and boss. He is the self-proclaimed "Greatest Psychic of the 21st Century" as well as owner and operator of the Spirits and Such Consultation Office.

Name: Renji Abarai
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Post-Bankai Training''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Post-Timeskip''' | '''Post-Royal Guard Training'''
Summary: Renji Abarai (阿散あば井らい 恋れん次じ, Abarai Renji?) is the lieutenant of the 6th Division under Captain Byakuya Kuchiki. He formerly served as the 6th Seat of the 11th Division under Kenpachi Zaraki.

Name: Robert Accutrone
Summary: Robert Accutrone (ロバート・アキュトロン, Robāto Akyutoron) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "N".

Name: Rockhoof
Summary: Rockhoof is one of the six Pillars of Equestria.

Name: Roronoa Zoro (Post-Timeskip)
Summary: Roronoa Zoro (ロロノア・ゾロ?), also known by his former epithet of "Pirate Hunter" after the Raid his new title of "The King of Hell", is the premier swordsman of the Straw Hat Pirates and a member of the Monster Trio. Recruited as a mildly notorious bounty hunter (hence his “Pirate Hunter” moniker), he is a monstrously powerful man who doesn't wield the power of a Devil Fruit, using a unique Three-Sword Style in a battle of his own creation, wielding a sword in each hand along with one in the mouth. Zoro mostly drinks and sleeps in his spare time (when he is not busy training to get stronger) but can become such a real demon in battle that many people often wondered why someone of his strength isn't the captain. Whenever he engages in a serious fight, he tends to tie a bandana around his head. Also, he has a horrible sense of direction.

Name: Rudbornn Chelute
Summary: Rudbornn Chelute is the 61st Arrancar in Sosuke Aizen's army, and the leader of the Exequias, the execution division of the Arrancar forces. Besides himself, the Exequias are completely made out of Calaveras, faceless executioners created by Rudbornn using his Resurrección.

Name: Rukia Kuchiki
Summary: Rukia Kuchiki (朽くち木き ルキア, Kuchiki Rukia?) is the current Captain of the 13th Division. She formerly served as lieutenant of the 13th Division under Captain Jūshirō Ukitake. Rukia is the adoptive younger sister of Byakuya Kuchiki and a friend of Ichigo Kurosaki.

Name: Ryuji Sakamoto
Key: '''Beginning of the Game''' | '''Early Game''' | '''Mid Game''' | '''Late Game''' | '''End Game'''
Summary: Ryuji Sakamoto is one of the founding members of the Phantom Thieves of Hearts. A troublemaking delinquent at a glance, his colorful vernacular and rough appearance belie his kind and loyal heart. After awakening his Persona and obtaining the Metaverse Navigator, he and the other Thieves became determined to change the corrupted society they lived in by stealing the hearts of the wicked. With every heart he steals, he hopes to galvanize the weak and downtrodden and get them to stand up against those that would prey on their misery and suffering.

Name: Sajin Komamura
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Sajin Komamura (狛村 左陣, Komamura Sajin) is the former captain of the 7th Division. His lieutenant was Tetsuzaemon Iba.

Name: Sanji (Post-Timeskip)
Key: '''Fishman Island Saga to Early Whole Cake Island Saga''' | '''Late Whole Cake Island Saga to Early Wano Act 2''' | '''Late Wano Act 2''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Sanji Vinsmoke (サンジ・ヴィンスモーク, Sanji Vinsumōku?), more commonly known as "Sanji" is the crew's chain-smoking chef and a member of the Monster Trio. There is not a dish he cannot cook, a pretty girl he will not try to woo, or something he will not argue with Zoro over. As a chef, he believes that he cannot afford to harm his hands, and so uses a fighting style which uses only his feet called the "Black Leg Style" (Kuroashi no Waza).

Name: Sasaki (One Piece)
Summary: "Overflowing" Sasaki is a Bluespine Unicornfish Fishman and one of the Tobiroppo, the strongest six Shinuchi of the Beasts Pirates. He also leads the crew's Armored Division Before joining the Beasts Pirates, he captained his own crew called the Sasaki Pirates.

Name: Scratchmen Apoo
Summary: Scratchmen Apoo, also known as "Roar of the Sea", is an infamous music-themed pirate from the Grand line and captain of the On The Air Pirates. He is one of twelve pirates who are referred to as the "Worst Generation" (formerly known as the "Eleven Supernovas"). After the timeskip, his bounty has been raised from 198,000,000 to 350,000,000.

Name: Senna (Bleach)
Summary: Senna (茜雫) is a Shinigami that Ichigo and Rukia encounter in the real world. In actuality, Senna is the Shinenju a being that is composed entirely out of memories of lost souls.

Name: Shawlong Koufang
Summary: Shawlong Koufang is the leader of Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez's Fracción and the 11th Arrancar in Sosuke Aizen's army, making him the eldest of the Números.

Name: Shaz Domino
Summary: Shaz Domino (シャズ・ドミノ, Shazu Domino) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "Ϛ" - "The Stigma".

Name: Shigeo Kageyama
Summary: Shigeo Kageyama, also known as Mob, is the protagonist of the manga/anime series Mob Psycho 100.

Name: Shunsui Kyōraku
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc''' | '''CFYOW Novel'''
Summary: Shunsui Sakuranosuke Jiro Kyoraku (京きょう楽らく 次じ郎ろう 佐さ蔵くら総のすけ 春しゅん水すい, Kyōraku no Jirō Sakuranosuke Shunsui?) is the captain of the 1st Division and Captain-Commander of the Gotei 13. His lieutenants are Nanao Ise and Genshirō Okikiba. He is the former captain of the 8th Division.

Name: Shūhei Hisagi
Summary: Shūhei Hisagi (檜佐木ひさぎ 修しゅう兵へい, Hisagi Shūhei?) is the co-lieutenant of the 9th Division, formerly under Captain Kaname Tosen and currently under Captain Kensei Muguruma. He shares his position with Mashiro Kuna.

Name: Siegfried (Soul Calibur)
Key: '''Original Siegfried''' | '''Siegfried with True Soul Calibur''' | '''New Timeline'''
Summary: Siegfried had played host to Soul Calibur and, ultimately, destroyed Soul Edge. After that epic battle, the knight returned home and enjoyed a brief period of peace. But deep down he knew his work was not over; the cursed sword's minions—the malfested—remained a serious threat. Realizing he couldn't stop them alone, Siegfried gathered his staunchest allies from his old clan known as Schwarzwind, he reformed the clan of thieves into a clan of mercenaries.

Name: Smolder the Dragon
Summary: Smolder is a supporting character from My Little Pony: FiM.

Name: Sophitia Alexandra
Summary: Sophitia Alexandra is a major character of the Soul Calibur series. She serves as the main protagonist of the original Soul Blade and is usually a major character working behind the scenes in later Soul Calibur titles. She was sent by the Greek God of Fire and forging Hephaestus in order to destroy Soul Edge and was granted to Omega Blade and Elk Shield in order to do so. She is credited with being the one to shatter Soul Edge during her fight with Cervantes.

Name: Speed-o'-Sound Sonic
Summary: Speed-o'-Sound Sonic (音速のソニック Onsoku no Sonikku) is a villain in the series, first appearing as a bodyguard hired by Mr. Monier. He grew up in a ninja village, honing his skills to near perfection. He views Saitama as his eternal rival, ever since the hero "defeated" him in a rather embarrassing manner.

Name: Spike the Dragon
Key: '''Baby Dragon Form''' | '''Equestria Girls Dog Form''' | '''Adult Dragon Form ''' | '''Post Puberty'''
Summary: Spike the Dragon is a protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Sunset Shimmer
Key: '''Human''' | '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Element of Magic (Demon Form)''' | '''Pony-Up Form''' | '''Daydream Shimmer'''
Summary: Sunset Shimmer is a reformed villain from My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Suì-Fēng
Summary: Suì-Fēng (砕蜂 (ソイフォン), Soifon) is the commander-in-chief of the Onmitsukidō and the captain of the 2nd Division in the Gotei 13. Her lieutenant is Marechiyo Ōmaeda. She boasts one of the highest speeds as a captain and is pretty deadly in close combat.

Name: Szayelaporro Granz
Summary: Szayelaporro Granz (ザエルアポロ・グランツ, Zaeruaporo Gurantsu?) is the 8th Espada of Sosuke Aizen's army and the younger brother of Yylfordt Granz, the 15th Arrancar, and one of Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez's Fracción. As an Espada, the aspect of death he symbolizes is madness.

Name: Tesra Lindocruz
Summary: Tesra Lindocruz (テスラ·リンドクルツ, Tesura Rindokurutsu; Viz: Tesla Lindocruz) is the 50th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and Nnoitra Gilga's only Fracción.

Name: The Mean Six
Summary: The Mean Six are the main antagonists of the MLP: FiM episode of the same name. They are clones of the Mane Six created by Queen Chrysalis before they end up turning against her.

Name: The Storm King
Summary: The Storm King is the main antagonist of the My Little Pony Movie.

Name: Toichiro Suzuki
Summary: Toichiro Suzuki is a major antagonist in the Mob Psycho 100 anime and manga series. He is the leader of the worldwide organization of Espers, Claw, and uses his army of psychic individuals to attempt to take control over the governments of the world. In reality, though, Toichiro only uses this to make some sort of mark on the world. even if it means causing mass destruction with no real end-goal.

Name: Twilight Sparkle (Pony World)
Key: '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Alicorn Form''' | '''The Ending of the End Alicorn Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''All Alicorn Magic''' | '''Post-Timeskip Alicorn Form''' | '''Rainbow Power''' | '''Equestria Girls Human form'''
Summary: Twilight Sparkle is the main protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Tōshirō Hitsugaya
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Early Arrancar Arc''' | '''Late Arrancar Arc''' | '''Post-Timeskip''' | '''Post-Training''' | '''Matured Bankai'''
Summary: Toshiro Hitsugaya (日ひ番つが谷や 冬とう獅し郎ろう, Hitsugaya Tōshirō?) is the captain of the 10th Division in the Gotei 13. His lieutenant is Rangiku Matsumoto. He formerly served as the 3rd Seat of the 10th Division under Isshin Shiba.

Name: Ulti (One Piece)
Summary: Ulti is one of the Tobiroppo, the six strongest Headliners of the Beasts Pirates. and is the older sister of Page One.

Name: Uryū Ishida
Summary: Uryu Ishida (石いし田だ 雨う竜りゅう, Ishida Uryū?) is a Gemischt Quincy residing in Karakura Town. He is a doctor at Karakura Hospital, and a friend of Ichigo Kurosaki. He is also a former member of the Wandenreich with the designation "A" - "Antithesis", one of Yhwach's "Schutzstaffel" (親衛隊シュッツシュタッフェル, Shuttsushutafferu?), and his future successor.

Name: Usopp
Key: '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Water 7 Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Usopp serves as the crew's sharpshooter and previously served as the (barely competent) repairman for the ship. He's the son of Yasopp, a sharpshooter serving under Shanks, and comes from the East Blue. Usopp had a reputation on his home island of being a serial liar who claimed that pirates were attacking, which came back to haunt him when real pirates actually attacked. He's a rather boastful seventeen/nineteen-year-old who likes to tell tall tales (several of which actually do come true, after a fashion), though he's more prone to hiding behind the stronger crew members such as Zoro when he actually gets into a fight. However, when push comes to shove, he is very dependable. He specializes in the use of a slingshot, called the Galaxy Slingshot (Ginga Pachinko), which he replaced with the Kabuto and later the Black Kabuto. This slingshot, coupled with his talent in tricking enemies, and his absurd sniping skills, make him a redoubtable sniper able to intervene at a very long range.

Name: White (Bleach)
Summary: White is an artificial Hollow created by Sosuke Aizen using the souls of Shinigami killed over the course of his research.

Name: Who's-Who
Summary: Who's-Who is one of the Tobiroppo, the strongest six Shinuchi of the Beasts Pirates.

Name: X Drake
Summary: X Drake (read as "Diez Drake") is a former Marine rear admiral from North Blue who has become a pirate under the epithet of the "Red Flag". He is one of twelve pirates referred to as the "Worst Generation" (formerly as the "Eleven Supernovas"), and prior to the two-year timeskip had a bounty of 222,000,000.

Name: Yamato (One Piece)
Summary: Yamato (ヤマト?) is the child of Kaidou, one of the Four Emperors of the Sea. Groomed from a young age to be his heir, Yamato instead developed a profound admiration for the samurai Kozuki Oden. After his death, Yamato chose to become Oden, and adopted his mannerisms. This path has put Yamato at odds with Kaidou, with much of his life being spent imprisoned on Onigashima. Yamato befriended Portgas D. Ace during his visit to Wano, and after learning of Ace's death waited for the arrival of his sworn brother, Monkey D. Luffy. Together with Luffy and the Ninja-Pirate-Mink-Samurai Alliance, Yamato helped to defeat Kaidou and the Beasts Pirates.

Name: Yammy Llargo
Summary: Yammy Llargo (ヤミー・リヤルゴ, Yamī Riyarugo?) is an Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army. While he initially appeared to bear the rank of Arrancar Diez (10), Yammy is actually the Cero (0) Espada and thus the most powerful of the Espada.

Name: Yasutora Sado (Chad)
Key: '''Substitute Shinigami Arc''' | '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Lost Agent Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Yasutora Sado (茶渡 泰虎, Sado Yasutora), also known as Chad (チャド, Chado) is a human teenager who lives in Karakura Town. He is a student at Karakura High School, where he is in the same class as Ichigo Kurosaki.

Name: Yoruichi Shihoin
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Early Arrancar Arc''' | '''Late Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Yoruichi Shihōin (四楓院 夜一, Shihōin Yoruichi) is the former captain of the 2nd Division of the Gotei 13, as well as the former commander of the Onmitsukido. Her lieutenant was Marenoshin Omaeda. Having abandoned her command of both positions, she works with Kisuke Urahara and Tessai Tsukabishi, based in the Urahara Shop out in the Human World.

Name: Yumichika Ayasegawa
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Early Arrancar Arc''' | '''Late Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War'''
Summary: Yumichika Ayasegawa (綾あや瀬せ川がわ 弓ゆみ親ちか, Ayasegawa Yumichika?) is the 3rd Seat officer and former 5th Seat officer in the 11th Division of the Gotei 13, under Captain Kenpachi Zaraki.

Name: Yylfordt Granz
Summary: Yylfordt Granz (イールフォルト・グランツ, Īruforuto Gurantsu) is Arrancar Quince (15) in Sōsuke Aizen's army and one of Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez's five Fracción. He is the older brother of Szayelaporro Granz, the 8th Espada.

Name: Zasalamel
Summary: Zasalamel is a character in the Soul series of fighting games, a man with no allegiances except to himself, though some of his actions may reasonably be defined as evil.

Name: Zommari Rureaux
Summary: Zommari Rureaux (ゾマリ・ルルー, Zomari Rurū) is an Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army, and the Séptima (7th) Espada.

Name: Akuma (Street Fighter)
Summary: Akuma (悪魔 Akuma, "Devil"), known in Japan as Gouki (豪鬼 Gōki, "Great Demon", "Great Devil" or "Great Ogre") is a self-proclaimed "Supreme Master of the Fist" who wields the Satsui no Hadou ("surge of murderous intent"; also translated as the "Evil Intent", the "Killing Intent", "Dark Hadou", or the "Murder Wave").

Name: All-Hunt Grount
Summary: All-Hunt Grount is a Marine Captain and a major antagonist for the Marines Rookie filler arc. He was a subordinate to Admiral Aokiji. He was transferred to Vice Admiral Prodi's base, which is close to Big Mom's territory.

Name: Ambrosius
Summary: Ambrosius is a spirit that resides in the Relic of Creation, one of the four Relics created by the God of Light after his departure from Remnant. He can be summoned by the user, at which point he can create anything they desire. However, he is limited to one task at a time, as the previous creation is destroyed the moment a new one is made.

Name: Anguirus (Showa)
Key: '''First Generation''' | '''Second Generation''' | '''Second Generation End of Showa era'''
Summary: Anguirus is a four-legged dinosaur-like creature that looks similar to an ankylosaurus. He has several horns at the top of his head and a single horn above his nose like a rhinoceros. His face is long and drawn out, like a crocodile, and has rows of jagged, serrated teeth. His carapace is studded with long, sharp spikes. Anguirus' tail is longer than his body and makes up most of his body length, and is also covered with spikes. His hind limbs are longer than his forelimbs, enabling him to stand up on them to his full height, but he generally walks on all fours.

Name: Baby Five
Summary: Baby Five is the alias of a member of the Happo Navy who is engaged to Sai, the Happo Navy's 13th leader. She is a former servant and assassin of the Donquixote Pirates, serving as an executive in the Pica Army. Her real name has not been revealed.

Name: Baragon (GMK)
Summary: In Godzilla, Mothra and King Ghidorah: Giant Monsters All-Out Attack, Baragon is one of the three ancient Guardian Monsters of Japan, the others being Mothra and King Ghidorah.

Name: Bartolomeo
Summary: Bartolomeo the Cannibal is a Super Rookie that became a contender of the Corrida Colosseum, and won the Block B battle. He has eaten the Barrier-Barrier Fruit (Bari Bari no Mi), which allows him to generate extremely durable barriers at will.

Name: Basil Hawkins
Summary: Basil Hawkins is an infamous pirate known as the "Magician" and the captain of the Hawkins Pirates. He came from the Grand Line and is one of twelve pirates who are referred to as the "Worst Generation" (Formerly known as the "Eleven Supernovas"). His previous known bounty amounted to 249,000,000, but after the time skip it was raised to 320,000,000.

Name: Bellamy
Summary: Bellamy the Hyena is the former captain of the Bellamy Pirates, and a former member of the Donquixote Pirates.

Name: Bepo
Summary: Bepo is a polar bear mink and the navigator of the Heart Pirates. Bepo tends to get depressed easily and apologizes whenever people point out that he's a talking polar bear.

Name: Black Maria
Summary: Black Maria is one of the Tobiroppo, the strongest six Headliners of the Beasts Pirates, she owns her own brothel on Onigashima.

Name: Blueno
Summary: Blueno is one of the members of CP9.

Name: Boa Marigold
Summary: Boa Hancock's youngest sister, Boa Marigold is one of the key members of the Kuja Pirates. Along with Hancock and Boa Sandersonia, Marigold was kidnapped by slave traders at a young age and sold to the Celestial Dragons, where she endured traumatizing experiences up until Fisher Tiger, a fishman, freed many of the slaves of Mariejois.

Name: Boa Sandersonia
Summary: One of Boa Hancock's younger sisters, Boa Sandersonia is one of the key members of the Kuja Pirates. Along with Hancock and Boa Marigold, Sandersonia was kidnapped by slave traders at a young age and sold to the Celestial Dragons, where she endured traumatizing experiences up until Fisher Tiger, a fishman, freed many of the slaves of Mariejois.

Name: Brook
Summary: Brook is the crew's musician. He ate the Revive-Revive Fruit (Yomi Yomi no Mi), which enabled his spirit to reanimate his corpse after he died. Unfortunately, after his death, his spirit got lost for an entire year before finding his body, and it had decayed into a skeleton. He later developed the ability to control his own soul. Deprived of his shadow by the Warlord of the Sea, Gecko Moria, he was adrift within the gloomy Florian Triangle until he met the Straw Hats by chance.

Name: Buffalo (One Piece)
Summary: Buffalo is the alias of a combatant of the Donquixote Pirates and an officer of the Pica Army. His real name has yet to be revealed.

Name: Buggy the Clown
Summary: Buggy the Clown was initially one of the first real pirates that Luffy encountered early on in his travels. Buggy is a rather gaudy individual who used to be on the legendary Roger Pirates crew, along with Luffy's idol Shanks, who Buggy eventually bore a grudge against for unwittingly foiling a scheme to find a legendary treasure. After Gol D. Roger's death, the two went their separate ways, and while Shanks went on to become one of the Four Emperors, Buggy hung around the relatively tame East Blue.

Name: Byrnndi World
Summary: Byrnndi World is the captain of the World Pirates and the main antagonist of the 3D2Y anime special. He is a former prisoner of Impel Down Level 6.

Name: Caesar Clown
Summary: Caesar Clown, also referred to as "Master" by his subordinates, is a former colleague of Vegapunk and the primary antagonist of the Punk Hazard Arc. Caesar is the leading expert on chemical weapons of mass destruction and is a demented scientist that has a bounty of 300,000,000 on his head.

Name: Carrot (One Piece)
Summary: Carrot is a rabbit mink in the Warrior Beast Tribe, a member of the Inuarashi Musketeer Squad, and a ruler's aide. She is currently accompanying Luffy's "Sanji retrieval team" to Whole Cake Island and continued on with the crew to Wano Country.

Name: Casey Rhodes
Key: '''Casey Rhodes''' | '''Dai-Shi awakening Arc (1-10)''' | '''Overlords Arc (11-21)''' | '''Phantom Beast Arc (22-32)'''
Summary: Casey Rhodes is the Jungle Fury Red Ranger. He was a fairly new member to the Pai Zhua Academy and hence known as a cub and possessed the spirit of the tiger. He has the power to stand up for what he believes in and for others. He doesn't like other people to get picked on. When Casey stood up one day for a fellow cub who was being verbally abused by Jarrod, Master Mao (the leader of the Pai Zhua Academy) dismissed Jarrod. Master Mao saw the potential that Casey had in him and chose him instead of Jarrod, to guard Dai Shi's imprisonment box.

Name: Cavendish (One Piece)
Summary: Cavendish, also known as the "Pirate Prince" is a Super Rookie, the captain of the Beautiful Pirates, and the prince of Bourgeois Kingdom. He made a name for himself after he made it to the New World but after the events of the Battle of Marineford and being overshadowed by the rookies of the "Worst Generation", he holds a grudge against Monkey D. Luffy and the other Supernovas for stealing his spotlight away from him. He entered the Corrida Colosseum hoping to win the Flame-Flame Fruit.

Name: Charlotte Cracker
Summary: Charlotte Cracker, also known as Thousand Arms Cracker, is the 10th son of Big Mom and Totto Land's Minister of Biscuits. He has eaten the Bisu Bisu no Mi, allowing him to produce large numbers of biscuit crackers and reshape them in any form he wishes. He usually inhabits and fights from the inside of an enormous biscuit puppet crafted with his powers, to the point his bounty poster depicts the puppet and not his real face. He was first revealed within the Wholecake Island arc when encountering Monkey D. Luffy and Nami. He is the first of the Three Sweet Commanders to have been revealed.

Name: Cheer Bear (2019)
Summary: Cheer Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with exploring and protecting the Silver Lining. She's the positive, enthusiastic pilot of the Cloudseeker and the leader of the expedition. Her upbeat personality is contagious and appreciated by just about everyone who meets her. Although she's always up for a challenge, she often feels a lack of confidence in her abilities.

Name: Chinjao
Summary: A former pirate and leader of the Happo Navy and a participant in the Corrida Coliseum to compete for the Mera Mera no Mi. He holds a grudge against Garp for ruining his life. He extended this grudge onto his grandson Luffy, but Luffy, being himself, manages to make him an ally.

Name: Crocodile (One Piece)
Summary: Crocodile is the second of the Seven Warlords of the Sea to be formally introduced and serves as the main antagonist of the Alabasta Saga. He is one of the longest running primary adversaries of the series as well as the first enemy to hand Luffy a complete and utter defeat, not once but twice. He secretly formed a criminal organization called Baroque Works, whose public aim was to take over the prosperous of Alabasta and create a utopia and led it as its president. To accomplish this, he worked to undermine Alabasta King's influence by defeating criminals before the royal army could, and by exploiting a drought in order to pit the kingdom against an army of rebels. His Devil Fruit, the Sand-Sand Fruit (Suna Suna no Mi), lets him turn into and control sand, a very useful ability in the desert kingdom.

Name: Daruma (One Piece)
Summary: Daruma is a cookie-cutter shark fish-man‎ and was an officer of the New Fish-Man‎ Pirates before their downfall and disbandment.

Name: Dellinger
Summary: Dellinger is one of the Donquixote family executives who resided in the country of Dressrosa. He was first introduced when he was sent to assassinate Bellamy for his failure regarding his competence in attempting to achieve victory in the Corrida Coliseum B block and for failing to assassinate Monkey D. Luffy.

Name: Devastator (Devastation)
Summary: Devastator is the monstrous combination of the six Constructicons - Long Haul, Scrapper, Mixmaster, Bonecrusher, Scavenger, and Hook - who is the titular character of Transformers: Devastation. Immensely powerful and towering above all who dare challenge him, Devastator looks to crush everything in his path, if Megatron wishes it so.

Name: Diamante
Summary: One of the three Top Executives of the Donquixote Family, Diamante was one of the founders of the Donquixote Pirates as he helped raise and train Donquixote Doflamingo to become the man he is today.

Name: Dimple
Summary: Dimple is an on and off again antagonist and supporting character in the Mob Psycho 100 anime/manga series. He is a spirit whose goal is to become a god through gathering individuals in a cult around himself, a goal which put him at odds with espers such as Keiji Mogami and Shigeo Kageyama on multiple occasions.

Name: Donquixote Doflamingo
Summary: The third of the Seven Warlords to be formally introduced, Donquixote Doflamingo (ドンキホーテ・ドフラミンゴ, Donkihōte Dofuramingo?) is captain of the Donquixote Pirates and the former king of Dressrosa. Sly, rude and disrespectful towards the World Government, Doflamingo is very sadistic towards others and seems to delight in causing and participating in chaos. However, he is affectionate towards his crew, who in turn all respect him, referring to him as "Doffy".

Name: Dukey
Summary: Dukey is the pet dog of Johnny Test and the deuteragonist of the series. One of his most notable qualities is that he has the ability to speak. Johnny got him as a birthday gift for his 11th birthday. He's a dog mutated by Susan and Mary. Since then, he became very intelligent. He is also a master at karate, knows how to speak Chinese, play video games and gives great advice.

Name: Elizabello II
Summary: King Elizabello II was introduced in Fighting Block B within the Corrida Colosseum. He is known as "The Fighting King" and to wield a powerful attack said to be capable of defeating a Yonko].

Name: Enel
Summary: Enel is the former "God" of Skypiea and the main antagonist of the Skypiea Arc. Two years ago, after his defeat by the Straw Hat Pirates, he arrived at the moon and became its new ruler.

Name: Evil Ryu
Summary: Evil Ryu (殺意の波動に目覚めたリュウ, Ryu with the Surge of Killing Intent Awakened), is a character from the Street Fighter series who was originally featured in the 1996 Street Fighter Zero manga before appearing as a playable fighter in Street Fighter Alpha 2. This is the form Ryu takes if he ever succumbs to the Satsui no Hado. Ryu ultimately purged his evil half when he overcame the Satsui no Hado in Street Fighter V, but doing so gave birth to Kage.

Name: Flame Queen
Summary: Flame Princess (first name Phoebe and occasionally called FP) is the princess and ruler of the Fire Kingdom, as well as Finn's ex-girlfriend. When Jake asks Flambo if he knows any princesses that are Finn's age so he can fix his broken heart, he introduces Jake to Flame Princess. Flame Princess was locked away in a lantern in the main chamber of the Fire Kingdom when Jake first encounters her. It is later revealed that her father, the Flame King, put her there on Princess Bubblegum's advice when she was an infant, and she did not come out for 14 years. She has a short temper, trust issues, and a heat core that can destroy the world if overblown with emotions.

Name: Franky
Key: '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: "Iron Man" Franky, real name Cutty Flam, is the shipwright of the Straw Hat Pirates under captain Monkey D. Luffy. As his epithet implies, he is a cyborg, having rebuilt his own body from iron scraps after he was run over by a sea train. He was formerly a member of a criminal shipbreaking gang called the Franky Family, which operated in the shipbuilders' haven of Water 7. He encountered the Straw Hats when he and the Franky Family brutally beat Usopp and stole a great deal of money from the crew while they were attempting to get their boat fixed on the island. However, his interests subsequently aligned with the Straw Hats' when the secret government organization CP9 kidnapped both him and their crewmate Nico Robin in a bid to construct the ancient superweapon Pluton, which he owned the blueprints to. After escaping the clutches of CP9, Franky decided to join their crew, drawn by their dedication to both their ship and their fellow crewmen.

Name: Funshine Bear (2019)
Summary: Funshine Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with exploring and protecting the Silver Lining. He's the blindly optimistic co-pilot of the Cloudseeker who's always looking to have as much fun as possible. He rarely takes things seriously, which has both helped with the team's morale but also hindered their progress, depending on the situation. As a thrill seeker, Funshine's hobbies include hang-gliding and skating; he also is seen working on a superhero comic book from time to time.

Name: Garland (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Garland is the primary antagonist of Final Fantasy, originally a rogue knight from World A who abducted Princess Sarah before he was defeated by the Warrior of Light. But by fate, Garland was spirited away into World B where he ended up becoming the most faithful servant of Chaos in their battle against Cosmos and her warriors. But during the final cycle, as his fellow warriors have forsaken Chaos to act on their own whims, Garland reveals he and Chaos are bond by fate before serving as the god's last line of defense against the Warriors of Cosmos. Upon his defeat, Garland would end up in World A's distant past where he forged a pact with the Four Fiends and became the very creature whose memory inspired the creation of Chaos himself.

Name: Gecko Moria
Summary: Gecko Moria is a villain from One Piece, and was a member of the Shichibukai. He resided on the largest ship in the world, Thriller Bark, and his Devil Fruit powers can manipulate shadows. His former bounty is 320,000,000 Beli. He is also the main antagonist of the Thriller Bark Arc who stole Brook's and various other beings' shadows with the use of the Kage Kage no Mi. He took part in the Battle of Marineford and sided with the Marines, along with most of the other Shichibukai. Upon the war's end, he was stripped of his title, and was to be eliminated by Donquixote Doflamingo, but managed to escape before he was killed. He was last seen travelling to the island of Hachinosu in search of his subordinate Absalom, and being given an offer to join Blackbeard's crew after finding out Absalom had been killed to poach his Devil Fruit.

Name: Gen
Summary: Gen is a character from the Street Fighter series. Debuting in the first Street Fighter game, he is one of the most dangerous characters in Street Fighter lore.

Name: Geralt of Rivia (Monster Hunter)
Summary: Geralt of Rivia is a warrior from another world known as a Witcher. Transported to the New World by the magic of a Leshen, a powerful spirit of nature, he was enlisted by the Fifth Fleet to hunt down the creature, using his special skills in such a way that even the Hunter must respect.

Name: Geryuganshoop
Summary: Geryuganshoop was one of the Dark Matter Thieves, a group of alien pirates traveling across the universe. He was one of Boros' strongest fighters, claiming himself to be the greatest psychic in the universe. Despite displaying immense power, he seemed easily flustered under pressure, and even after getting serious, was effortlessly killed when Saitama split his head with a rock.

Name: Gild Tesoro
Summary: Gild Tesoro is the main antagonist of One Piece Film: Gold. He is a non-canon character.

Name: Gill
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:TheMarkOfMyDignityShallScarThyDNA.ogg

Name: Gladius
Summary: As a Donquixote Family Executive, Gladius resided close by to his master Donquixote Doflamingo, who was the king of Dressrosa.

Name: Godzilla (GMK)
Summary: The GMK Godzilla (ＧジーＭエムＫケイゴジラ, GMK Gojira?) is a kaiju that appeared in the 2001 Godzilla film, Godzilla, Mothra and King Ghidorah: Giant Monsters All-Out Attack.

Name: Godzilla (Original)
Summary: Godzilla (ゴジラ, Gojira?) was designed by Teizo Toshimitsu and Akira Watanabe under Eiji Tsuburaya's supervision. Early on, Tanaka contemplated on having the monster be gorilla-like or whale-like in design due to the name "Gojira" (a combination of the Japanese words for gorilla which is gorira, and whale which is kujira) but eventually settled on a dinosaur-like design.

Name: Godzilla (Showa)
Key: '''Godzilla Raids Again''' | '''King Kong vs. Godzilla/Mothra vs. Godzilla''' | '''Ghidorah the Three-Headed Monster and ahead/End of Zone Fighter''' | '''End of Showa era'''
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:Showa_Godzilla_Roar.ogg

Name: Good Luck Bear (2019)
Summary: Good Luck Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with exploring and protecting the Silver Lining. Due to his lucky streak and natural intuition, he's assigned the role of the Cloudseeker's navigator. His Belly Badge power ensures luck is always on his side, which has frequently helped the crew on their mission. He's often the one to reassure his companions when things are tense. On the other hand, he can also be overconfident and over-reliant on this power. On multiple occasions, he's dived headfirst into situations without thinking things through.

Name: Gouken
Summary: Gouken (ゴウケン 剛拳, Gōken) "Constitutionality", "Strong Fist", is a playable character in the Street Fighter series. He is Ryu's adoptive father, Ryu and Ken's martial arts master, Dan's former master as well as Akuma's older brother.

Name: Grumpy Bear (2019)
Summary: Grumpy Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with protecting the Silver Lining. He is the creator of the Cloudseeker, the vehicle the bears use to navigate the uncharted territory. He's frequently having to upgrade or fix it, thanks to the unpredictability of the area they explore. As the crew's resident worrywart, he often either brings up an important detail the rest of the Bears hadn't considered, or he reaches a point where his pessimism needs to be dialed back.

Name: Hajrudin
Summary: "Pirate Mercenary" Hajrudin is a giant warrior described as the "new generation" from Elbaf and joined as a gladiator at the Corrida Colosseum to compete for the Mera Mera no Mi. He was first mentioned by a Marine officer who was speaking to Vice Admiral Maynard. He is the sixth division leader of the Straw Hat Grand Fleet after the events of Dressrosa.

Name: Hina (One Piece)
Summary: "Black Cage" Hina is a Marine officer and a former classmate of Vice Admiral Smoker. Jango and Fullbody are currently her subordinates. She was originally introduced as a Captain. During the timeskip, she was promoted to the rank of Rear Admiral.

Name: Hody Jones
Summary: Hody Jones is the main antagonist of the Fishman Island Arc and a firm follower of the radical Fishman pirate Arlong. He is a great white shark Fishman who since his childhood was exposed and bathed in the hatred for the human race and grew to hold a massive disliking toward them, willing to go to extreme lengths to maintain the animosity between them.

Name: Hyouzou
Summary: Hyouzou is a poisonous blue-ringed octopus merman. Prior to his imprisonment, he was a mercenary and working as the New Fish-Man Pirates' assassin, and later became one of the officers. Hyouzou was also known as the strongest swordsman on Fish-Man Island.

Name: Ice King (Adventure Time)
Summary: The Ice King, also known as Simon Petrikov was a main recurring antagonist in Adventure Time, though now is considered something similar to a protagonist and was reverted back into his sane, non-magic human self in the finale of the main series. In the background of the show, before The Great Mushroom War, Simon was a respectable archaeologist, appearing to be mild-mannered, intelligent, kind and adventurous. On a trip to Scandinavia, Simon discovered a Crown of mysterious origin. After wearing his crown, his life changed for the worse. His relationship with his fiance was shattered and his sanity was starting to diminish. However, the crown would keep him alive, allowing him to be one of the very few human survivors of The Great Mushroom War.

Name: Ideo
Summary: "Destruction Cannon" Ideo is a XXX rank boxer who joined as a gladiator at the Corrida Colosseum to compete for the Mera Mera no Mi. He is a member of the Longarm Tribe. He formed the XXX Gym Martial Arts Alliance along with three other gladiators from the Colosseum and acts as their representative. He is the 4th division commander of the Straw Hat Grand Fleet.

Name: Jabra
Summary: Jabra is one of the assassins of CP9. He is the last to be revealed, and is the 3rd strongest behind Kaku and Rob Lucci. He is a compulsive liar and tends to be very arrogant. He verbally assaults Lucci and Kaku upon learning that they both have superior physical strength to him. He is a Wolf Zoan Devil Fruit eater.

Name: Jinbe
Summary: "Knight of the Sea" Jinbe is a whale shark fishman, the helmsman of the Straw Hat Pirates, the second captain of the Sun Pirates after Fisher Tiger, and a former Shichibukai, who attained the position eleven years ago.

Name: Johnny Test (Character)
Summary: Johnathan "Johnny" Test is a troublesome, narcissistic 11-year-old boy also known for his love of anything he considers awesome. He's the only son of Hugh and Lila and brother of Susan and Mary (who had brown hair in the 2004 pilot). Because he has Susan and Mary by his side, he can live any kid's dream, only to find that some dreams aren't worth living. He is usually seen with his partner-in-crime and best friend Dukey, his genetically altered dog. He also gives Johnny Coupons to his sisters for helping him with his daily problems. When redeemed, he does their tests for free. Johnny and his sisters are often the cause of some problems in Porkbelly.

Name: Kage
Summary: Kage (影, Shadow) is a character introduced in Street Fighter V: Arcade Edition. After Ryu overcame the temptations of the Satsui no Hado dwelling within him, it was assumed that Evil Ryu had been vanquished. Yet somehow, the Satsui no Hado developed sentience and came to manifest as its own entirely separate, physical entity, naming itself "Kagenaru Mono" (影ナル者, The Shadowed One). Kage lives to show and prove to Ryu that he is nothing without him and seeks out to challenge Akuma and Sagat, two of Ryu’s most notorious rivals. But these endeavors were ultimately fruitless for Kage, because even after fighting them, they comment on how he is nothing but an impudent, ignorant and soulless silhouette that doesn't have the strength to break a true warrior's will.

Name: Kaku
Summary: Kaku is one of the Elite members of the Cipher Pol Number Nine and second only to Lucci, and is also the youngest. He has a peculiar, "squared body" and a very long nose, similar to Usopp’s. He too can use the Rokushiki and is a master of Rankyaku, to the point that he's developed the Yontoryuu (Four-swords style) using two katanas and his legs. He also has eaten the Cow-Cow Fruit (Ushi Ushi no Mi), Model: Giraffe and can turn into a Giraffe-man, but despite his ridiculous appearance, he's still as powerful and dangerous if not more so.

Name: King Ghidorah (GMK)
Summary: In Godzilla, Mothra and King Ghidorah: Giant Monsters All-Out Attack, King Ghidorah is reinvented as a heroic monster for the first, and so far only, time. In this film, King Ghidorah is the God of the Sky and one of the three Guardian Monsters, along with Mothra and Baragon. An ancient Yamata no Orochi, an eight-headed dragon from Japanese mythology, King Ghidorah was slain by Japanese warriors thousands of years ago and laid to rest underneath Mount Fuji. The warriors prayed for King Ghidorah's soul, and over the next several centuries he slowly regenerated, empowered by the souls of Japan's honorable dead. However, he was awakened before he could grow back all eight of his heads, instead growing only three.

Name: Koby
Summary: Koby is first introduced as a cowardly chore boy on board Alvida's ship. Through fear of being smashed by her Iron Mace, whenever she asked him who was the loveliest on the sea, he would reply, "You are, Miss Alvida". Eventually, with the help of Luffy, he found the courage to pursue his dream of leaving her and becoming a Marine.

Name: Kyros
Summary: Kyros is a legendary gladiator, who fought at the Corrida Coliseum until 20 years ago. A great bronze statue of him is held at the Corrida Colosseum.

Name: Lao G
Summary: Lao G is an officer of the Donquixote Pirates Diamante Army and a major antagonist in the Dressrosa Arc.

Name: Machvise
Summary: Machvise is an officer of the Donquixote Pirates' Diamante Army with a bounty of 11,000,000 Berries. He has the power of the "Ton-Ton Fruit" which lets him manipulate his body weight in increments of tons.

Name: Megatron (Devastation)
Summary: Megatron is the tyrannical and oppressive commander of the Decepticons, and acts as the main antagonist of Transformers: Devastation.

Name: Mizutsune
Summary: Mizutsune is a Leviathan first introduced in Monster Hunter Generations.

Name: MOGERA (Showa)
Summary: Moguera (モゲラ, Mogera?) is a Mysterian mecha that first appeared in the 1957 Toho film, The Mysterians.

Name: Monet
Summary: A former member of the Donquixote Pirate crew, Monet served as Caesar Clown's assistant and guard on Punk Hazard.

Name: Monkey D. Luffy (Emperor)
Summary: Monkey D. Luffy (モンキー・Ｄディー・ルフィ, Monkī Dī Rufi?), known as "Straw Hat Luffy", is the main protagonist of the manga and anime, One Piece. He's the son of Monkey D. Dragon, a revolutionary considered "The World's Most Dangerous Criminal"; the grandson of Monkey D. Garp, a powerful Marine Vice-Admiral who had cornered the late Pirate King himself on several occasions; the sworn brother of late "Fire Fist" Portgas D. Ace and Revolutionary chief of staff Sabo; and the foster son of Curly Dadan. He seeks to find One Piece and become the Pirate King; to accomplish this, he founded the Straw Hat Pirates and set out on the high seas at age 17 in search of the elusive treasure, beginning a series of increasingly odd and dangerous adventures. He has eaten the Gum-Gum Fruit, which turned his body into rubber and gives him stretching powers; he's developed great mastery and creativity with his powers, creating two unique techniques with them: Gear 2nd, which makes him much faster, and Gear 3rd, which allows him to inflate any body parts for a stronger attack. During the time-skip, he has a new technique: Gear 4th, which makes him much stronger and faster than even the other two Gears, but with a considerable cost to it. During his battle with Kaidou in Onigashima, Luffy manages to awaken the true potential of his Devil Fruit, the Hito Hito no Mi: Model Nika, tapping into his Gear 5th, granting his rubber-like body increased physical strength and freedom, limited only by his imagination.

Name: Monkey D. Luffy (Post-Timeskip)
Summary: Monkey D. Luffy (モンキー・Dディー・ルフィ, Monki Di Rufi?), known as "Straw Hat Luffy", is the main protagonist of the manga and anime, One Piece. He's the son of Monkey D. Dragon, a revolutionary considered “The World's Most Dangerous Criminal”; the grandson of Monkey D. Garp, a powerful Marine Vice-Admiral who had cornered the late Pirate King himself on several occasions; the sworn brother of late "Fire Fist" Portgas D. Ace and Revolutionary chief of staff Sabo; and the foster son of Curly Dadan. He seeks to find One Piece and become the Pirate King; to accomplish this, he founded the Straw Hat Pirates and set out on the high seas at age 17 in search of the elusive treasure, beginning a series of increasingly odd and dangerous adventures. He has eaten the Gum-Gum Fruit, which turned his body into rubber and gives him stretching powers; he's developed great mastery and creativity with his powers, creating two unique techniques with them: Gear 2nd, which makes him much faster, and Gear 3rd, which allows him to inflate any body parts for a stronger attack. During the time-skip, he has a new technique: Gear 4th, which makes him much stronger and faster than even the other two Gears, but with a considerable cost to it. With the support from Silvers Rayleigh and the desire to reunite with his crew after the Sabaody Island Incident and the Marineford War, he endured vigorous training on the island of Ruskaina where he learned the 3 forms of Haki, and out of the three, he specialized in “Haoshoku Haki”.

Name: Monkey D. Luffy (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''Young''' | '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Arc''' | '''Water 7 Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Paramount War Saga'''
Summary: Monkey D. Luffy (モンキー・Ｄディー・ルフィ, Monkī Dī Rufi?), known as "Straw Hat Luffy", is the main protagonist of the manga and anime, One Piece. He's the son of Monkey D. Dragon, a revolutionary considered “The World's Most Dangerous Criminal”; the grandson of Monkey D. Garp, a powerful Marine Vice-Admiral who had cornered the late Pirate King himself on several occasions; the sworn brother of late "Fire Fist" Portgas D. Ace and Revolutionary chief of staff Sabo; and the foster son of Curly Dadan. He seeks to find One Piece and become the Pirate King; to accomplish this, he founded the Straw Hat Pirates and set out on the high seas at age 17 in search of the elusive treasure, beginning a series of increasingly odd and dangerous adventures. He has eaten the Gomu Gomu no Mi, which gives him stretching powers that he has become quite a master of and he's quite creative with them as he has developed two unique techniques with them: Gear 2nd, which makes him much faster, and Gear 3rd, which allows him to inflate any body parts for a stronger attack.

Name: Mothra (GMK)
Summary: Tier: At least 6-C | Unknown

Name: Mysterians
Summary: The Mysterians (ミステリアン) are a race of aliens created by Toho that first appeared in the 1957 film The Mysterians.

Name: Nami (One Piece)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypeia Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Sabaody Archipelago Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Whole Cake Arc''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Nami, also known by her epithet "Cat Burglar", is the navigator of the Straw Hats who was initially introduced as a thief who detested pirates and stole from them, tagging along Luffy with dubious loyalty to him. However, it is revealed that her surrogate home, the Conomi Archipelago, was occupied by the Arlong Pirates and she only wished to buy her home back. When Luffy freed the archipelago from Arlong’s grip, she fully joined the Straw Hats afterward.

Name: Nico Robin
Key: '''Alabasta Arc''' | '''Skypiea Arc''' | '''Thriller Bark Arc''' - '''Sabaody Archipelago Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Adventurer, archaeologist, ex-Dragon, and Ms. Exposition, Nico Robin is one of the darker and more enigmatic members of the Straw Hats.

Name: Oars
Summary: Oars is Gekko Moriah's most prized Zombie, as he is known to have been an ancient monster that wreaked havoc. He was reanimated after Moriah stored his body and waited for a powerful pirate to arrive that could make Oars into the most powerful zombie. In this case, it was Monkey D. Luffy, who at the time scored a bounty of 300,000,000 Belis. Oars was Moriah's 900th Zombie soldier.

Name: Optimus Prime (Devastation)
Summary: Optimus Prime is the courageous and powerful leader of the Autobots. He serves as the main protagonist to Transformers: Devastation.

Name: Optimus Prime (Robots in Disguise 2001)
Summary: Optimus Prime is the strong and courageous Autobot leader who feels his role is the protection of all life, including Earth-life. He fights unceasingly to defeat the Decepticons, though not without honor. Optimus values peace over chaos, and life over destruction, often using words before weapons. Many have remarked that if he was more ruthless, he would be a better military leader. But if he was more ruthless, he wouldn't be Optimus Prime.

Name: Oro
Summary: Oro is an ancient, mysterious hermit who seeks a fighter that is worthy to inherit his fighting style. He is of Japanese descent and hails from the Amazon Jungle, where he lives in a cave with his many pets, including a turtle and a dog.

Name: Ozpin
Summary: Professor Ozpin is the headmaster of Beacon Academy, first seen in Volume 1 inquiring Ruby Rose about where she learned how to fight, her future goals, and her desire to join his school. He is frequently seen with his cane despite having no visible motor impairment.

Name: Pacifista (One Piece)
Summary: Taking on the image of one of the royal Shichibukai Bartholomew Kuma, the Pacifista are an army of prototype weapons of mass destruction created by the scientist Dr. Vegapunk. These machines were created with the costs of an entire battleship, and are intent on exterminating pirates of considerably high bounties: Often being sent to deal with pirates holding bounties of around 100,000,000 berries both pre timeskip, and post timeskip.

Name: Page 1
Summary: Page One is a member of the Beast Pirates, holding the rank of a Head-liner and is a member of the Flying Six. He is introduced as he and X-Drake were sent to kill the Soba Shop owner by the name of Sangoro (Sanji) on the orders of Queen.

Name: Patience St. Pim
Summary: Patience St. Pim is the current Ice Elemental. She is discovered by the Ice King, Finn, and Jake, who then requests the other elementals. Patience attempted to reunite the reincarnations of the elementals, unfortunately they escaped with little care for her.

Name: Perona
Summary: Perona is the former "Wild Zombies" and "Surprise Zombies Commander" of Thriller Bark before the collapse of Gecko Moriah's zombie army. She can produce ghosts from her body through the powers of the Horo Horo no Mi.

Name: Pica
Summary: Pica is one of the top three executives of the Donquixote Pirates. He occupies the Spade seat of the Donquixote Family and is the leader of the crew's Pica Army subdivision.

Name: Psycho Helmet
Summary: Psycho Helmet is an entity born from the Divine Tree, a massive stalk of broccoli that originated in the aftermath of Toichiro and Mob's fight. Originally the result of Dimple fusing with the Divine Tree, it later became an entirely separate entity from him, only keeping Dimple's original goal of becoming the 'God of the modern world'.

Name: Rebecca (One Piece)
Summary: Rebecca is the former crown princess of Dressrosa who's title was taken after Donquixote Doflamingo's takeover of the country. She was imprisoned and forced to fight in the Corrida Colosseum, where she never inflicted a single injury nor lost a battle. Upon Doflamingo's defeat, she forfeited her title in order to live with her father.

Name: RJ
Summary: Robert James, usually referred to as RJ, is the laid-back and carefree master and instructor of the Jungle Fury Power Rangers, as well as, the boss and owner of a pizza restaurant that serves as their headquaters. During his childhood, his father, Master Finn, constantly tried to force RJ to learn the Shark Technique in order become a Shark Master. RJ, being against this, left home and found his own master, who instructed him in the ways of the Wolf. Upon mastering his Wolf Spirit, RJ became the new Wolf Master and eventually the Jungle Fury Wolf Ranger after his students help him revert from his werewolf form, a curse inflicted by Da' Shi.

Name: Rob Lucci
Summary: “The Murder Machine” Rob Lucci was the strongest member of Cipher Pol Number Nine, a top-secret group of eight assassins tasked with various undercover operations for the World Government.

Name: Roronoa Zoro (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc'''
Summary: Roronoa Zoro (ロロノア・ゾロ?), also known by his epithet “Pirate Hunter”, is the premier swordsman of the Straw Hat Pirates and a member of the Monster Trio.

Name: Rudbornn Chelute
Summary: Rudbornn Chelute is the 61st Arrancar in Sosuke Aizen's army, and the leader of the Exequias, the execution division of the Arrancar forces. Besides himself, the Exequias are completely made out of Calaveras, faceless executioners created by Rudbornn using his Resurrección.

Name: Ryu (Street Fighter)
Summary: The lead character of the Street Fighter franchise and a fighting game character, Ryu is a stoic Japanese martial artist who wanders the globe seeking the meaning of being a "true warrior". He can be recognized by his sleeveless white karate gi and a red or white hachimaki/headband depending on the game. He trained alongside his friendly rival Ken under their mutual master Gouken and was the victor of the first Street Fighter tournament. His encounter with his master's nemesis Akuma during the Street Fighter Alpha sub-series awoke the untapped Satsui no Hadou or "murderous intent" within him although this power was eventually overwhelmed in Street Fighter V, when he mastered the Power of Nothingness, a source of higher power arising from a state of consciousness in which the mind is free from thoughts and emotions. In Street Fighter III, he continues to travel the world in search of strong opponents.

Name: Sai (One Piece)
Summary: Sai, also known as Don Sai, is a member of the Chinjao Family and the 13th leader of the Happo Navy. He is also a martial artist who joined as a gladiator at the Corrida Colosseum to compete for the Mera Mera no Mi. He is the 3rd division commander of the Straw Hat Grand Fleet.

Name: Sanji (Post-Timeskip)
Key: '''Fishman Island Saga to Early Whole Cake Island Saga''' | '''Late Whole Cake Island Saga to Early Wano Act 2''' | '''Late Wano Act 2''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Sanji Vinsmoke (サンジ・ヴィンスモーク, Sanji Vinsumōku?), more commonly known as "Sanji" is the crew's chain-smoking chef and a member of the Monster Trio. There is not a dish he cannot cook, a pretty girl he will not try to woo, or something he will not argue with Zoro over. As a chef, he believes that he cannot afford to harm his hands, and so uses a fighting style which uses only his feet called the "Black Leg Style" (Kuroashi no Waza).

Name: Sanji (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc'''
Summary: Sanji Vinsmoke, more commonly known as "Sanji" is the crew's chain-smoking chef and a member of the Monster Trio. There is not a dish he cannot cook, a pretty girl he will not try to woo, or something he will not argue with Zoro over. As a chef, he believes that he cannot afford to harm his hands, and so uses a fighting style which uses only his feet called the "Black Leg Style" (Kuroashi no Waza).

Name: Sasaki (One Piece)
Summary: "Overflowing" Sasaki is a Bluespine Unicornfish Fishman and one of the Tobiroppo, the strongest six Shinuchi of the Beasts Pirates. He also leads the crew's Armored Division Before joining the Beasts Pirates, he captained his own crew called the Sasaki Pirates.

Name: Scourge (Robots in Disguise 2001)
Summary: Scourge was an Autobot protoform, part of a group of six Autobots sent to earth to reactivate Fortress Maximus. However, he would be stolen by Megatron and be used to bolster his forces, he corrupted the protoform by infusing it with his own evil spark. Due to Optimus Prime also being scanned when Megatron was searching for a suitable alternate mode for Scourge, Scourge would receive several attributes from Optimus himself.

Name: Senor Pink
Summary: Senor Pink is an officer of the Donquixote Pirates' Diamante Army, with a bounty of 58,000,000 Berry. He was also the widower of Russian and is the father of the late Gimlet.

Name: Share Bear (2019)
Summary: Share Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with exploring and protecting the Silver Lining. She is the team's communicator, receiving and relaying information from the Caring Tower. Additionally, she acts as the point of contact for any new species and civilizations the crew encounters. While Share is more than happy to help others however she can, this often leads her to putting a lot of pressure on herself and getting discouraged whenever she makes mistakes.

Name: Shigeo Kageyama
Summary: Shigeo Kageyama, also known as Mob, is the protagonist of the manga/anime series Mob Psycho 100.

Name: Smoker (One Piece)
Summary: Smoker is a tough Marine, who, when first introduced, was tasked with catching pirates that visited Loguetown before sailing for the Grand Line.

Name: Soundwave (Devastation)
Summary: Soundwave is Megatron's loyal communications officer. At all times, he is with his five Minicons: Buzzsaw, Laserbeak, Rumble, Ravage, and Frenzy.

Name: Subspace Army
Summary: The Subspace Army is an organization hailing from Subspace led by Tabuu. It is the main antagonistic force of the Subspace Emissary, acting as the source behind most threats faced by the heroes. Its goal is the absorption of the World of Trophy into Subspace, done by the usage of Subspace Bombs. As Tabuu cannot leave Subspace, most of the forces are located in the World of Trophy while Tabuu manipulates them from Subspace. Those include the Isle of the Ancients, the Halberd (Piloted by Mr. Game & Watch) and the Koopa Troop. Most relations within the army are quite fragile, however, as a lot of them are done either through force or trickery. Notably, almost no one knows the existence of Tabuu, as the latter hides behind Master Hand to communicate his orders to his commanders.

Name: Subspace Bomb
Summary: The Subspace Bomb is a powerful weapon used in the Super Smash Bros. story mode. A large portion of the game is set to keep them from being set.

Name: Sung Jin-Woo (Novel)
Summary: nan

Name: Surume (One Piece)
Summary: Surume is a kraken which dwells in the deepest parts of the ocean, and was enslaved by the New Fishman Pirates, but later became Luffy's pet. Luffy was the one who gave Surume his name.

Name: Tashigi
Summary: Tashigi was first introduced when the Straw Hat Pirates docked in Loguetown, where she was stationed. Smoker, her superior officer, seems to regard her as a protege; the two work very well together.

Name: Tony Tony Chopper
Key: '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Tony Tony Chopper serves as the ship's doctor. He's a reindeer who was cast out of his herd for having a blue nose, later compounded by eating the Human-Human Fruit (Hito Hito no Mi) and being feared by the people of Drum Island as a monster. Although he initially mistrusted humans, after having met and joined the Straw Hats, he has become very curious about the world and is eager to please.

Name: Trafalgar Law
Summary: Trafalgar D. Water Law is the captain of the Heart Pirates and one of the eleven pirates dubbed with the moniker "Supernova". He's a very laid-back person, and while his speech is very polite, he has no problem with taking mocking jabs at people or giving them the middle finger.

Name: Trebol
Summary: Probably one of the most impacting of the Donquixote Family's three Top Executives, Trebol has taken a huge part regarding the development of Donquixote Doflamingo's rise to power.

Name: Ulti (One Piece)
Summary: Ulti is one of the Tobiroppo, the six strongest Headliners of the Beasts Pirates. and is the older sister of Page One.

Name: Urouge
Summary: Urouge, also known as Mad Monk, is a pirate who hails from a sky island and is the captain of the Fallen Monk Pirates. He is one of twelve pirates who are referred to as the "Worst Generation " (formerly known as the "Eleven Supernovas"). and prior to the two-year timeskip had a bounty of 108,000,000.

Name: Usopp
Key: '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Water 7 Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Usopp serves as the crew's sharpshooter and previously served as the (barely competent) repairman for the ship. He's the son of Yasopp, a sharpshooter serving under Shanks, and comes from the East Blue. Usopp had a reputation on his home island of being a serial liar who claimed that pirates were attacking, which came back to haunt him when real pirates actually attacked. He's a rather boastful seventeen/nineteen-year-old who likes to tell tall tales (several of which actually do come true, after a fashion), though he's more prone to hiding behind the stronger crew members such as Zoro when he actually gets into a fight. However, when push comes to shove, he is very dependable. He specializes in the use of a slingshot, called the Galaxy Slingshot (Ginga Pachinko), which he replaced with the Kabuto and later the Black Kabuto. This slingshot, coupled with his talent in tricking enemies, and his absurd sniping skills, make him a redoubtable sniper able to intervene at a very long range.

Name: Vergo
Summary: Vergo is one of the four High Executives of the Donquixote Pirates and a Marine Vice Admiral.

Name: Wadatsumi
Summary: Wadatsumi is a giant tiger blowfish fish-man and a member of the Sun Pirates. He was formerly a member of the Flying Pirates under captain Vander Decken IX before they were defeated.

Name: Who's-Who
Summary: Who's-Who is one of the Tobiroppo, the strongest six Shinuchi of the Beasts Pirates.

Name: Zunesha
Summary: Zunesha is a colossal, sentient elephant that carries the entire country of Zou on its back. In the ancient past, Zunesha was sentenced to walk the seas for eternity and only act upon being ordered to do so for committing an unspecified crime. Since then, it has wandered the sea of the New World and lived for centuries carrying the Mink Tribe and the other lifeforms on Zou. The elephant comes from an unusual species with multi-jointed legs that are incredibly long and reach far down into the ocean floor.

Name: Aaroniero Arruruerie
Summary: Aaroniero Arruruerie is the 9th Espada of Sosuke Aizen's army.
