He is the only remaining first-generation Espada and the only one of their numbers to have once been a Gillian-class Hollow, having increased his power far beyond its former bounds by consuming tens of thousands of other Hollows and gaining their abilities. As an Espada, the aspect of death he symbolizes is greed.

Name: AC-3 White Heron
Summary: The AC-3 White Heron (-しらさぎ) is a support vehicle used by the JSDF which first appeared in the 2002 Godzilla film, Godzilla Against Mechagodzilla.

Name: Achilles (Fate)
Summary: Rider of "Red" ("赤あか"のライダー, "Aka" no Raidā?) is the Rider-class Servant of the Red Faction of the Great Holy Grail War. While he is originally summoned by one of the Pentel brothers, he later becomes one of the Servants of Shirou Kotomine.

Name: Agrias Oaks
Summary: Lady Agrias Oaks is a secondary character appearing in Final Fantasy Tactics, initially as a guest character working together with Ramza Beoulve through the story, finally joining him during the events of Chapter 2.

Name: Akane Yashiro (Kiryu Saga)
Key: '''Akane Yashiro''' | '''Piloting Maser Cannon''' | '''Piloting AC-3 White Heron''' | '''Piloting Kiryu'''
Summary: Akane Yashiro (家城茜) is the human protagonist of the 2002 Toho Godzilla film Godzilla Against Mechagodzilla, also appearing in a minor role in its 2003 sequel Godzilla: Tokyo SOS. First Lieutenant Akane Yashiro A Type 90 Maser Cannon operator for the JSDF's Anti-Megalosaurus Force, Akane unintentionally caused the death of her comrades in a battle against Godzilla in 1999. Subsequently reassigned to a desk job, Akane was recruited to become a pilot for the Kiryu Squad in 2003, receiving the rank of Second Lieutenant. A member of the Kiryu team and the pilot of Kiryu Type-3. She is an excellent operator, but as the only member without relatives, she can be a bit awkward due to not being good at reading the feelings of others. Despite the odds against her, Akane earned the respect of her squad and played a key role in the battle between Kiryu and Godzilla in Tokyo. By 2004, she had been promoted to First Lieutenant and sought further training in the United States.

Name: Akantor
Summary: Akantor are Flying Wyvern in Monster Hunter.

Name: Akuma (Street Fighter)
Summary: Akuma (悪魔 Akuma, "Devil"), known in Japan as Gouki (豪鬼 Gōki, "Great Demon", "Great Devil" or "Great Ogre") is a self-proclaimed "Supreme Master of the Fist" who wields the Satsui no Hadou ("surge of murderous intent"; also translated as the "Evil Intent", the "Killing Intent", "Dark Hadou", or the "Murder Wave").

Name: Alatreon
Summary: Alatreon is a monster capable of destroying the world. Some locals even believe that the Alatreon is a god or demon which is transformed into an Elder Dragon. Alatreons are very territorial. This may be the reason why no other monsters live in the Sacred Land. Alatreon might attack most of its prey from the air, giving it an advantage over most other monsters. It also is very aggressive towards flying objects, mainly airships.

Name: All For One
Summary: All For One (オール・フォー・ワン Ōru Fō Wan) is the true leader and benefactor of the League of Villains who bears the title of the world's Symbol of Evil, the primary antagonist of the Hideout Raid Arc and the central antagonist of the series, along with Tomura Shigaraki.

Name: All-Hunt Grount
Summary: All-Hunt Grount is a Marine Captain and a major antagonist for the Marines Rookie filler arc. He was a subordinate to Admiral Aokiji. He was transferred to Vice Admiral Prodi's base, which is close to Big Mom's territory.

Name: Amatsu
Summary: Also known as the "Storm Dragon", Amatsu is an Elder Dragon with a unique body structure, similar to that of sea life, but floats in midair. Its body is covered with fin-like protrusions, and has a small head in relation to the rest of its body. Its body mass is assumed to be quite light, as it is able to literally swim through the storm that is always surrounding it. It resides on the Sacred Mountain, a mountain located in the Yukumo region near the Misty Peaks. It is said to be the personification of the storm and its power is comparable to a natural disaster. As a result, its appearance has become a Yakumo Village tradition.

Name: Ambrosius
Summary: Ambrosius is a spirit that resides in the Relic of Creation, one of the four Relics created by the God of Light after his departure from Remnant. He can be summoned by the user, at which point he can create anything they desire. However, he is limited to one task at a time, as the previous creation is destroyed the moment a new one is made.

Name: Ancient Leshen (Monster Hunter)
Summary: An old Leshen that arrived through a portal to assume control over the Ancient Forest. Sometimes revered as an indigenous deity. Dwelling deep inside the forest, this creature uses their innate magic to control all flora and fauna within their territory. Resulted from a crossover between Monster Hunter World and The Witcher 3.

Name: Anguirus (Showa)
Key: '''First Generation''' | '''Second Generation''' | '''Second Generation End of Showa era'''
Summary: Anguirus is a four-legged dinosaur-like creature that looks similar to an ankylosaurus. He has several horns at the top of his head and a single horn above his nose like a rhinoceros. His face is long and drawn out, like a crocodile, and has rows of jagged, serrated teeth. His carapace is studded with long, sharp spikes. Anguirus' tail is longer than his body and makes up most of his body length, and is also covered with spikes. His hind limbs are longer than his forelimbs, enabling him to stand up on them to his full height, but he generally walks on all fours.

Name: Ann Takamaki
Key: '''Beginning of the Game''' | '''Early Game''' | '''Mid Game''' | '''Late Game''' | '''End Game'''
Summary: Ann Takamaki is one of the founding members of the Phantom Thieves of Hearts. The classmate of Ren Amamiya and Ryuji Sakamoto, she is one of the first playable characters in Persona 5. Ann was shunned because of her looks and didn't have many friends before meeting the protagonist. Along with the other Phantom Thieves of Hearts, Ann hopes to reform society by stealing the hearts of the corrupt.

Name: Apple Bloom
Summary: Tier: At least 9-B, likely 8-A | Likely 6-B

Name: Applejack
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Applejack is one of the main protagonists of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Arcee (IDW)
Summary: An ancient warrior from the dawn of Cybertronian history, sibling to the equally powerful warrior Galvatron, Arcee arose from the ashes of her mysterious, traumatic past to become one of the most feared Transformers of her era and beyond. Cold and detached off the battlefield and utterly ruthless in combat, Arcee's single-minded bloodlust put her at odds with both the Autobots and Decepticons for most of the Great War.

Name: As Nodt
Summary: Äs Nödt (エス・ノト, Esu Noto?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "F" - "The Fear".

Name: Ashura Doji (One Piece)
Summary: Ashura Doji is a retainer of the Kozuki Family as one of the Nine Red Scabbards once led by Kozuki Oden. After Oden's death he returned to being a criminal under the name Shutenmaru, assuming leadership of the Mt. Atama Thieves. He initially severed his ties with the Kozuki Family in the present but rejoined after witnessing Yasuie's death.

Name: Askin Nakk Le Vaar
Summary: Askin Nakk Le Vaar (アスキン・ナックルヴァール, Asukin Nakkuruvāru?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "D" - "The Deathdealing", as well as one of Yhwach's Schutzstaffel (親衛隊シュッツシュタッフェル, Shuttsushutafferu?) German for "Protective Echelon", Japanese for "Elite/Imperial Guards".

Name: Astaroth (Soul Calibur)
Summary: Ares, the god of destruction, desired Soul Edge to dethrone his father, Zeus, so he ordered Kunpaetku, the grand priest of the cult order Fygul Cestemus, to seek it out. Astaroth, a golem, was created in hellish heat under the divine protection of Ares to head up the quest. Kunpaetku ordered his creation, Astaroth, to find the demonic blade. As he watched Astaroth depart from the shrine, the grand priest laughed to himself as he planned to keep the Soul Edge and become a god himself. Unknown to Kunpaetku, however, Ares had possessed Astaroth with his servants, the Keres, to ensure that Kunpaetku would not betray him.

Name: Astolfo (Rider of Black)
Summary: Template:Astolfo

Name: Atalanta (Fate)
Summary: Archer of "Red" is the Archer-class Servant of the Red Faction in the Great Holy Grail War. While she is originally summoned by Rottweil Berzinsky, she later becomes one of the Servants of Shirou Kotomine. She also appears in the First and Third Singularities of the Grand Orders, Orleans and Okeanos.

Name: Avicebron (Fate)
Summary: Caster of "Black" is the Caster-class Servant of the Black Faction in the Great Holy Grail War, summoned by Roche Frain Yggdmillennia.

Name: Ayon
Summary: Ayon (アヨン, Ayon) is a Chimera-like Hollow created by the Quimera Parca ability, made from left arms of Tier Harribel's fraccion.

Name: Azwel
Summary: Azwel is a character who first appeared in the reboot of the Soul series Soul Calibur Vl as one of the antagonists of the series. He serves as the main antagonist of the Libra of Souls Story. He calles himself the "Leader of Humanity" and plans to gather the power of both Soul Edge and Soul Calibur in order to create the Ultimate Seed.

Name: Baby Five
Summary: Baby Five is the alias of a member of the Happo Navy who is engaged to Sai, the Happo Navy's 13th leader. She is a former servant and assassin of the Donquixote Pirates, serving as an executive in the Pica Army. Her real name has not been revealed.

Name: Bad (Metal Bat)
Summary: Bad (バッド, Baddo?), also known by his hero alias Metal Bat (金きん属ぞくバット, Kinzoku Batto?), is an S-Class hero, ranked 15 in the Hero Association. Despite his low status among the S-Class heroes, he is considered one of the strongest. Metal Bat's "Kiai" (fighting spirit) is the key to his strength; the more damage he takes, the stronger he becomes. His power grows in direct proportion to his injury and mental state, to the point where he can eventually defeat superior opponents on his own. Metal Bat typically treats both his allies and enemies badly. However, he is a kind and gentle soul to his younger sister.[1]

Name: Bahamut (Final Fantasy)
Summary: A recurring summon in the games, Bahamut is a force to be reckoned as one of the most powerful summons, if not the most powerful summon the player can acquire on their journey. He is most frequently found as part of a sidequest and is not relevant to the main plot, but in some cases he takes a much more active role, such as empowering the Warriors of Light in the original game with their job changes. His demeanor, behavior, and alignment change from appearance to appearance, but all recognize him as the King of Dragons and the Ruler of the Skies.

Name: Bambietta Basterbine
Summary: Bambietta Basterbine (バンビエッタ・バスターバイン, Banbietta Basutābain?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "E" - "The Explode".

Name: Bang (Silver Fang)
Summary: Bang (バング) also known as Silver Fang (シルバーファング Shirubā Fangu) is the now-retired former S-Class rank 3 superhero for the Hero Association. Settled in Z-City, Bang owns a dojo passed down from generations and uses the fighting style the Water Stream Rock Smashing Fist. He has an older brother named Bomb, who is the master of Whirlwind Iron Cutting Fist. He was also Garou's former mentor, but after the events of the monster association arc, they are once again master and disciple.

Name: Baraggan Louisenbairn
Summary: Baraggan Louisenbairn (バラガン・ルイゼンバーン, Baragan Ruizenbān) is an Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and the Segunda (2nd) Espada.

Name: Baragon (GMK)
Summary: In Godzilla, Mothra and King Ghidorah: Giant Monsters All-Out Attack, Baragon is one of the three ancient Guardian Monsters of Japan, the others being Mothra and King Ghidorah.

Name: Baragon (Showa)
Summary: Baragon is a reptilian kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1965 Toho film, Frankenstein Conquers the World.

Name: Bartolomeo
Summary: Bartolomeo the Cannibal is a Super Rookie that became a contender of the Corrida Colosseum, and won the Block B battle. He has eaten the Barrier-Barrier Fruit (Bari Bari no Mi), which allows him to generate extremely durable barriers at will.

Name: Basil Hawkins
Summary: Basil Hawkins is an infamous pirate known as the "Magician" and the captain of the Hawkins Pirates. He came from the Grand Line and is one of twelve pirates who are referred to as the "Worst Generation" (Formerly known as the "Eleven Supernovas"). His previous known bounty amounted to 249,000,000, but after the time skip it was raised to 320,000,000.

Name: Bazelguese
Summary: Bazelgeuse are Flying Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Bazz-B
Summary: Bazzard Black (バザード・ブラック, Bazādo Burakku?), more commonly known as Bazz-B (バズビー, Bazubī?), is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter, with the designation "H" - "The Heat".

Name: Beef
Summary: Beef is a member of the Best Fitness Friends and one of the main antagonists introduced in Mario & Luigi: Bowser's Inside Story + Bowser Jr's Journey.

Name: Behemoth (Monster Hunter)
Summary: The Behemoth is a crossover monster introduced in Monster Hunter World.

Name: Beldam (Mario Bros)
Summary: Beldam is a notable antagonist of Paper Mario: The Thousand Year Door. She is the leader of the Shadow Sirens, a group which comprises of herself and her two sisters Marilyn and Vivian (Later Doopliss, as Vivian leaves the group and joins Mario). Beldam is an ally of the X-Nauts who want to summon the Shadow Queen, and kidnaps Peach at the beginning of the game as a vessel for the Shadow Queen. Beldam attempts to slow down Mario on his adventure, but eventually fails to do so. After the Shadow Queen is defeated, Beldam settles down in Twilight Town and reforms.

Name: Bellamy
Summary: Bellamy the Hyena is the former captain of the Bellamy Pirates, and a former member of the Donquixote Pirates.

Name: Benben Tsukumo
Summary: Benben Tsukumo is one of the Tsukumogami sister. She was transformed into a Youkai from a simple tool due to the Miracle Mallet's magical powers.

Name: Benn Beckman
Summary: Benn Beckman is the first mate of the Red Hair Pirates, which is led by Shanks.

Name: Bepo
Summary: Bepo is a polar bear mink and the navigator of the Heart Pirates. Bepo tends to get depressed easily and apologizes whenever people point out that he's a talking polar bear.

Name: Berenice Gabrielli
Summary: Berenice Gabrielli (ベレニケ・ガブリエリ, Berenike Gaburieri) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "Q" - "The Question".

Name: Berukyurosu
Summary: Berukyurosu are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Season 4.0.

Name: Best Fitness Friends (Fusion)
Summary: Best Fitness Friends is the final boss of Bowser Jr's story in Mario & Luigi: Bowser's Inside Story + Bowser Jr's Journey.

Name: BG9
Summary: BG9 (ベー・ゲー・ノイン, Bē Gē Noin?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "K".

Name: Big McIntosh
Summary: Big McIntosh is a supporting character in My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic, and he is Applejack's older brother.

Name: Birdo
Summary: Birdo, Catherine (キャサリン Kyasarin), is a recurring character in the Mario series. While most commonly depicted as a single character, multiple Birdos have been seen on occasion. The central Birdo character wears a red bow and often a diamond ring. She also has some sort of relationship with Yoshi, as they are default partners in various competitions. She originally appeared as a part of the 8-Bits, an army led by Wart in the Subcon realm to thwart Mario's dreams. In later games, she would either help or hinder Mario, depending on her role in the story, and partake in various sports games.

Name: Black Maria
Summary: Black Maria is one of the Tobiroppo, the strongest six Headliners of the Beasts Pirates, she owns her own brothel on Onigashima.

Name: Black Sperm
Summary: Black Sperm (黒くろい精せい子し, Kuroi Seishi?) is a monster who first appeared during the S-Class Heroes' raid of the Monster Association.

Name: Blade Knight
Summary: Blade Knight is a character portrayed as a swordsman and knight featured in the Kirby series. He's a regular enemy across stages, which Kirby can turn into a Helper ally in some games. Blade Knight gives Kirby the Sword Copy Ability when swallowed, function he shared with Sword Knight in classic titles. Star Allies implies he wants to conquer the world.

Name: Blueno
Summary: Blueno is one of the members of CP9.

Name: Boa Marigold
Summary: Boa Hancock's youngest sister, Boa Marigold is one of the key members of the Kuja Pirates. Along with Hancock and Boa Sandersonia, Marigold was kidnapped by slave traders at a young age and sold to the Celestial Dragons, where she endured traumatizing experiences up until Fisher Tiger, a fishman, freed many of the slaves of Mariejois.

Name: Boa Sandersonia
Summary: One of Boa Hancock's younger sisters, Boa Sandersonia is one of the key members of the Kuja Pirates. Along with Hancock and Boa Marigold, Sandersonia was kidnapped by slave traders at a young age and sold to the Celestial Dragons, where she endured traumatizing experiences up until Fisher Tiger, a fishman, freed many of the slaves of Mariejois.

Name: Bofoi (Metal Knight)
Summary: Bofoi, also known by his hero name of Metal Knight is an S-Class, Rank 6 superhero for the Hero Association. A genius, Bofoi is the creator of the Hero Association's headquarters and combats foes through remote-controlled combat drones. He seems to be uninterested in actual heroics and much more focused on his research.

Name: Bomb (One Punch Man)
Summary: Bomb (ボンブ, Bonbu?) is Bang's older brother as well as a dojo master. Even in his old age, Bomb remains tough and daring. His martial talents are on par with, if not superior than, Bang's. Bomb had defeated Bang in a duel when they were younger. Bang, who was misguided and belligerent at the time, eventually reconciled with his brother and followed in his footsteps, enrolling pupils and establishing a martial arts dojo.

Name: Bonetail
Summary: Bonetail is an enemy appearing in Paper Mario: The Thousand-Year Door. It is the elder sibling of Hooktail and Gloomtail, and was once a pet of the Shadow Queen, but died of starvation after being stuck in the bottom of the Pit of 100 Trials.

Name: Boom Boom
Summary: Boom Boom is a short-tempered brute who works for Bowser.

Name: Bowser
Summary: Bowser, sometimes known as King Koopa (Japanese: 大魔王クッパ, Daimaō Kuppa or "Great Demon King Koopa"), is the main antagonist of the Mario series and the King of the Koopas. He has repeatedly kidnapped or attempted to kidnap Princess Peach and take over the Mushroom Kingdom. He has also attempted to conquer other lands, such as the Mushroom World, Dinosaur Land, Sprixie Kingdom, and even the entire universe. Despite his villainous nature, he has occasionally helped the heroes of the Mushroom Kingdom against common threats and participates with them in their numerous sporting events in spin-off games.

Name: Bowser Jr.
Summary: Bowser Jr., known in Japan as Koopa Jr. (not to be confused with Koopa Kid), is the secondary antagonist of the Mario series, and the youngest child of Bowser and the apparent heir of the Dark Land. He debuted in Super Mario Sunshine. He acts as the main antagonist of both Super Mario Sunshine, and New Super Mario Bros., with his father only playing a minor role in each. He is a playable character in various multiplayer Mario games. Since his debut, he has stolen the spotlight as the main villain from his father in a few Mario games.

Name: Brachydios
Summary: Brachydios is the Flagship Monster of Monster Hunter 3 Ultimate.

Name: Brook
Summary: Brook is the crew's musician. He ate the Revive-Revive Fruit (Yomi Yomi no Mi), which enabled his spirit to reanimate his corpse after he died. Unfortunately, after his death, his spirit got lost for an entire year before finding his body, and it had decayed into a skeleton. He later developed the ability to control his own soul. Deprived of his shadow by the Warlord of the Sea, Gecko Moria, he was adrift within the gloomy Florian Triangle until he met the Straw Hats by chance.

Name: Broom Hatter
Summary: Broom Hatter is a character in the Kirby series that gives Kirby the Clean ability when swallowed.

Name: Buffalo (One Piece)
Summary: Buffalo is the alias of a combatant of the Donquixote Pirates and an officer of the Pica Army. His real name has yet to be revealed.

Name: Buggy the Clown
Summary: Buggy the Clown was initially one of the first real pirates that Luffy encountered early on in his travels. Buggy is a rather gaudy individual who used to be on the legendary Roger Pirates crew, along with Luffy's idol Shanks, who Buggy eventually bore a grudge against for unwittingly foiling a scheme to find a legendary treasure. After Gol D. Roger's death, the two went their separate ways, and while Shanks went on to become one of the Four Emperors, Buggy hung around the relatively tame East Blue.

Name: Byakuya Kuchiki
Summary: Even if I scatter and never bloom again

Name: Byrnndi World
Summary: Byrnndi World is the captain of the World Pirates and the main antagonist of the 3D2Y anime special. He is a former prisoner of Impel Down Level 6.

Name: Cackletta
Summary: Cackletta is an evil witch from Beanbean Kingdom and a major antagonist in Mario & Luigi: Superstar Saga.

Name: Caesar Clown
Summary: Caesar Clown, also referred to as "Master" by his subordinates, is a former colleague of Vegapunk and the primary antagonist of the Punk Hazard Arc. Caesar is the leading expert on chemical weapons of mass destruction and is a demented scientist that has a bounty of 300,000,000 on his head.

Name: Candice Catnipp
Summary: Candice Catnipp (キャンディス・キャットニップ, Kyandisu Kyatonippu?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter, possessing the designation "T" - The Thunderbolt.

Name: Cang Du
Summary: Cang Du (蒼都ツァン·トゥ, Tsan Tu?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Stern Ritter with the designation "I" - "The Iron".

Name: Capone Bege
Summary: Coming from the West Blue, Capone "Gang" Bege is one of twelve pirates who are referred to as the "Worst Generation" and also the captain of the Firetank Pirates. Once a powerful Mafia boss in his native Blue, he became bored with his dominance of the underworld and decided to head out to sea to conquer and loot as many powerful pirate crews as he can. He's rather infamous for his sadism, high class attitude, and very short temper. However, his most prominent attribute is his direct approach to victory. Bege is a cunning and crafty opportunist who always goes after the head honchos and no one else, just to enjoy watching their organizations dissolve into chaos after he knocks off the boss.

Name: Captain Falcon (Smash Bros)
Summary: Captain Falcon is a character that first appeared in the F-Zero series and eventually became famous thanks to his appearance in the very first Super Smash Bros game.

Name: Carnage Kabuto
Summary: Carnage Kabuto (阿あ修しゅ羅らカブト, Ashura Kabuto?) was an artificial mutant created by Dr. Genus of the House of Evolution and is by far their strongest creation. He is an extremely unstable being while also being very intelligent (which Dr. Genus also confirmed to be true), but has an insatiable bloodlust and thus had to be locked up because he kept killing anything that got near him. He considers himself far superior to humans, calling himself a 'new human' that Dr. Genus was looking for, and believing that all should bow to his will. Carnage Kabuto is also very sarcastic and low-tempered, which is considered by Genus to be one of his main failures.

Name: Carrot (One Piece)
Summary: Carrot is a rabbit mink in the Warrior Beast Tribe, a member of the Inuarashi Musketeer Squad, and a ruler's aide. She is currently accompanying Luffy's "Sanji retrieval team" to Whole Cake Island and continued on with the crew to Wano Country.

Name: Casey Rhodes
Key: '''Casey Rhodes''' | '''Dai-Shi awakening Arc (1-10)''' | '''Overlords Arc (11-21)''' | '''Phantom Beast Arc (22-32)'''
Summary: Casey Rhodes is the Jungle Fury Red Ranger. He was a fairly new member to the Pai Zhua Academy and hence known as a cub and possessed the spirit of the tiger. He has the power to stand up for what he believes in and for others. He doesn't like other people to get picked on. When Casey stood up one day for a fellow cub who was being verbally abused by Jarrod, Master Mao (the leader of the Pai Zhua Academy) dismissed Jarrod. Master Mao saw the potential that Casey had in him and chose him instead of Jarrod, to guard Dai Shi's imprisonment box.

Name: Cathleen Bate (Star and Stripe)
Summary: Cathleen Bate (キャスリーン・ベイト Kyasurīn Beito), also known as Star and Stripe (スターアンドストライプ Sutā Ando Sutoraipu), is the No. 1 Hero of the United States of America.

Name: Cavendish (One Piece)
Summary: Cavendish, also known as the "Pirate Prince" is a Super Rookie, the captain of the Beautiful Pirates, and the prince of Bourgeois Kingdom. He made a name for himself after he made it to the New World but after the events of the Battle of Marineford and being overshadowed by the rookies of the "Worst Generation", he holds a grudge against Monkey D. Luffy and the other Supernovas for stealing his spotlight away from him. He entered the Corrida Colosseum hoping to win the Flame-Flame Fruit.

Name: Ceadeus
Summary: Ceadeus is a massive underwater Elder Dragon which was introduced in Monster Hunter Tri/Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Chameleos
Summary: Chameleos are Elder Dragons introduced in Monster Hunter 2.

Name: Charlotte Chuhlhourne
Summary: Charlotte Chuhlhourne (シャルロッテ・クールホーン|Sharurotte Kūruhōn) is the 20th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and one of Baraggan Louisenbairn's six Fracción.

Name: Charlotte Cracker
Summary: Charlotte Cracker, also known as Thousand Arms Cracker, is the 10th son of Big Mom and Totto Land's Minister of Biscuits. He has eaten the Bisu Bisu no Mi, allowing him to produce large numbers of biscuit crackers and reshape them in any form he wishes. He usually inhabits and fights from the inside of an enormous biscuit puppet crafted with his powers, to the point his bounty poster depicts the puppet and not his real face. He was first revealed within the Wholecake Island arc when encountering Monkey D. Luffy and Nami. He is the first of the Three Sweet Commanders to have been revealed.

Name: Charlotte Daifuku
Summary: Charlotte Daifuku is a member of the Big Mom pirates and the third son of the Charlotte family, as a minister he has a high standing within the Big Mom pirates and is highly respected by his siblings, he was referred to as a "Monster" by Vito whilst mentioned in the same breath as his siblings Charlotte Katakuri and Smoothie.

Name: Charlotte Katakuri
Summary: The third of the Sweet Commanders to appear, Charlotte Katakuri is the second son of the Charlotte Family and the oldest of a set of fraternal triplets, his younger brothers being Daifuku and Oven.

Name: Charlotte Oven
Summary: The fourth son of the Charlotte family and a member of the Big Mom Pirates, he resides over Totto Land as its Minister of Browned Food. He is loyal to his family and was noted as one of several monsters by Vito who compared him to his siblings Katakuri and Smoothie.

Name: Charlotte Perospero
Summary: As the eldest son of the Charlotte family, Perospero is the Minister of Candy. He is highly respected among the Big Mom crew, and was entrusted with Caesar Clown's heart, and ensuring that he would finish the task assigned to him.

Name: Charlotte Smoothie
Summary: The second Sweet Commander to appear, Charlotte Smoothie is a longleg-human hybrid, the 14th daughter of Big Mom and the oldest in a set of triplets, her younger sisters being Citron and Cinnamon. She's Totto Land's Minister of Juice, and has eaten the Shibo Shibo no Mi, which allows her to squeeze juice out of any object, as well as absorb the liquid into her body or weapons to increase their size and power.

Name: Cheer Bear (2019)
Summary: Cheer Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with exploring and protecting the Silver Lining. She's the positive, enthusiastic pilot of the Cloudseeker and the leader of the expedition. Her upbeat personality is contagious and appreciated by just about everyone who meets her. Although she's always up for a challenge, she often feels a lack of confidence in her abilities.

Name: Chinjao
Summary: A former pirate and leader of the Happo Navy and a participant in the Corrida Coliseum to compete for the Mera Mera no Mi. He holds a grudge against Garp for ruining his life. He extended this grudge onto his grandson Luffy, but Luffy, being himself, manages to make him an ally.

Name: Chiron (Fate)
Summary: Archer of "Black" is the Archer-class Servant of the Black Faction in the Great Holy Grail War, summoned by Fiore Forvedge Yggdmillennia.

Name: Chizuru Kagura
Key: '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '96 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Chocobo (Chocobo's Dungeon)
Summary: Chocobo is the protagonist of the Chocobo series of Final Fantasy games. Young, brave, and curious, he is the partner of treasure hunter Cid.

Name: Choe Neng Poww
Summary: Choe Neng Poww (チーノン・ポウ, Chīnon Pō) is the 25th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and one of Baraggan Louisenbairn's six Fracción.

Name: Coyote Starrk
Summary: Why do I have to fight with a strong guy like this? I always envied the weak. Whenever we made friends, their souls would waste away just from being near us. Because we were so alone, we split our soul in two. I don't know which was our original form. Or perhaps, it was neither. But this was the only way we had to escape from our isolation. I so envied the weak. The weak can always find others to be around. I want to be weak. And if that's impossible, I at least want to find companions who are as strong as I...

Name: Crazy Hand
Summary: Crazy Hand is the left hand, and as the name implies, chaotic counterpart of Master Hand. Originating in Super Smash Bros. Melee, he is an ally of Master Hand and can be fought together at a high enough difficulty, always on final destination. He returns in future games as a boss, having prominent roles in Super Smash Bros. for Wii U, where he has his own mode known Crazy Orders, along with Super Smash Bros. Ultimate, where he is a major character in the story mode.

Name: Crocodile (One Piece)
Summary: Crocodile is the second of the Seven Warlords of the Sea to be formally introduced and serves as the main antagonist of the Alabasta Saga. He is one of the longest running primary adversaries of the series as well as the first enemy to hand Luffy a complete and utter defeat, not once but twice. He secretly formed a criminal organization called Baroque Works, whose public aim was to take over the prosperous of Alabasta and create a utopia and led it as its president. To accomplish this, he worked to undermine Alabasta King's influence by defeating criminals before the royal army could, and by exploiting a drought in order to pit the kingdom against an army of rebels. His Devil Fruit, the Sand-Sand Fruit (Suna Suna no Mi), lets him turn into and control sand, a very useful ability in the desert kingdom.

Name: Crust
Summary: Shield Hero: Crust (シールドヒーロー クラスト Shīrudo Hīrō Kurasuto) was the No. 6 ranked Pro Hero of Japan.

Name: Crystal King
Summary: The Crystal King is one of the henchmen picked by Paper Bowser to guard a Star Spirit. When Paper Mario reaches the top of the Crystal Palace, the Crystal King fights him, but is defeated and disappears.

Name: Dabi
Summary: Dabi (荼毘) is a villain affiliated with the League of Villains and was a member of the organization's Vanguard Action Squad. Later on, his organization and the Meta Liberation Army merged into the Paranormal Liberation Front, and became one of its nine lieutenants.

Name: Dalamadur
Summary: Dalamadur is a massive snake-like Elder Dragon approximately which dwarfs most other monsters in the series in terms of size. Dalamadur has razor sharp blades covering its whole body, and two large arms with sharp claws.

Name: Daring Do
Summary: Daring Do is a a secondary character in the show My Little Pony.

Name: Dark Bowser
Summary: Dark Bowser is Bowser's final boss in Mario & Luigi: Bowser's Inside Story.

Name: Daruma (One Piece)
Summary: Daruma is a cookie-cutter shark fish-man‎ and was an officer of the New Fish-Man‎ Pirates before their downfall and disbandment.

Name: Dellinger
Summary: Dellinger is one of the Donquixote family executives who resided in the country of Dressrosa. He was first introduced when he was sent to assassinate Bellamy for his failure regarding his competence in attempting to achieve victory in the Corrida Coliseum B block and for failing to assassinate Monkey D. Luffy.

Name: Denjiro
Summary: Denjiro is a samurai who served as Kozuki Oden's retainer, being one of the Nine Red Scabbards.

Name: Derpy Hooves
Summary: Derpy Hooves is the most popular background character of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Devastator (Devastation)
Summary: Devastator is the monstrous combination of the six Constructicons - Long Haul, Scrapper, Mixmaster, Bonecrusher, Scavenger, and Hook - who is the titular character of Transformers: Devastation. Immensely powerful and towering above all who dare challenge him, Devastator looks to crush everything in his path, if Megatron wishes it so.

Name: Deviljho
Key: '''Deviljho/Savage Deviljho/Starving Deviljho''' | '''Aberrant Deviljho''' | '''Four Heavenly King Deviljho'''
Summary: Deviljho is a Brute Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Diablos
Key: '''Diablos/HC Diablos/Gilded Diablos''' | '''Black Diablos''' | '''HC Black Diablos''' | '''Bloodbath Diablos''' | '''Varusaburosu'''
Summary: Diablos is a large dangerous Flying Wyvern which inhabits the Monster Hunter world's desert regions. Despite being a herbivore, it's incredibly aggressive which has earned it the title of "Tyrant of the Desert".

Name: Diamante
Summary: One of the three Top Executives of the Donquixote Family, Diamante was one of the founders of the Donquixote Pirates as he helped raise and train Donquixote Doflamingo to become the man he is today.

Name: Diddy Kong
Summary: Diddy Kong (ディディーコング Didī Kongu?) is a fictional character in the Donkey Kong series of video games, first appearing in the 1994 game Donkey Kong Country.

Name: Dieter
Summary: Dieter is a member of the Best Fitness Friends and one of the main antgonists introduced in Mario & Luigi: Bowser's Inside Story + Bowser Jr's Journey.

Name: Dimple
Summary: Dimple is an on and off again antagonist and supporting character in the Mob Psycho 100 anime/manga series. He is a spirit whose goal is to become a god through gathering individuals in a cult around himself, a goal which put him at odds with espers such as Keiji Mogami and Shigeo Kageyama on multiple occasions.

Name: Dire Miralis
Summary: Dire Miralis is extremely hostile to all living things and can destroy an entire ecosystem just from its intense heat. A Dire Miralis actually destroyed the Tainted Sea and killed all living things in the area, filling the water with blood, until it was driven off in ancient times. This monster is one that many hunters don't live to tell about.

Name: Disufiroa
Summary: Disufiroa is an Elder Dragon introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G2.

Name: Dondochakka Birstanne
Summary: Dondochakka Birstanne (ドンドチャッカ・ビルスタン, Dondochakka Birusutan) is one of Nelliel Tu Odelschwanck's Fracciónes, alongside Pesche Guatiche.

Name: Donkey Kong (Character)
Summary: Donkey Kong, (often abbreviated as "DK", or rarely Donkey), is a major character in the Super Mario franchise and the main protagonist of the Donkey Kong franchise. He is a powerful and carefree Kong that lives in Donkey Kong Island. He likes to collect bananas and spend time with his friends, particularly his best friend, nephew, and sidekick Diddy Kong. However, he has also been portrayed as an antagonist on multiple occasions, mainly in the Mario vs. Donkey Kong series.

Name: Donkey Kong (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Donkey Kong (ドンキーコング, Donkey Kong), oftentimes shortened to DK, is the eponymous protagonist of the Donkey Kong series. First premiering in the video game of the same name alongside Mario, he has since starred in a plethora of his own adventures while persisting in his rivalry against the plumber. As a member of the "perfect-attendance crew", Donkey Kong has been featured as a playable character in every installment of the Super Smash Bros. series.

Name: Donquixote Doflamingo
Summary: The third of the Seven Warlords to be formally introduced, Donquixote Doflamingo (ドンキホーテ・ドフラミンゴ, Donkihōte Dofuramingo?) is captain of the Donquixote Pirates and the former king of Dressrosa. Sly, rude and disrespectful towards the World Government, Doflamingo is very sadistic towards others and seems to delight in causing and participating in chaos. However, he is affectionate towards his crew, who in turn all respect him, referring to him as "Doffy".

Name: Doopliss
Summary: Doopliss is a reoccurring villain in Paper Mario The Thousand Year Door.

Name: Dordoni Alessandro Del Socaccio
Summary: Dordoni Alessandro Del Socaccio (ドルドーニ・アレッサンドロ・デル・ソカッチオ, Dorudōni Aressandoro Deru Sokacchio) was Arrancar Cientecimo Tercero (103rd) in Sōsuke Aizen's army prior to being killed by Rudbornn Chelute and later resurrected by Mayuri Kurotsuchi.

Name: Driscoll Berci
Summary: Driscoll Berci (ドリスコール・ベルチ, Dorisukōru Beruchi) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "O" - "The Overkill".

Name: Drive Knight
Summary: Drive Knight is the S-Class Rank 9 superhero of the Hero Association.

Name: Duck Hunt Dog (Super Smash Bros)
Summary: Duck Hunt Dog, also known as Duck Hunt Duo, which comprises of the classic dog, a duck, and the hunter, is a playable character in the Super Smash Bros. series. Originating in Super Smash Bros. for 3DS and Wii U, the dog throws various projectiles, the duck carries it around and assists the dog by extending its melee range, and the hunter fires at their opponents from far away.

Name: Dukey
Summary: Dukey is the pet dog of Johnny Test and the deuteragonist of the series. One of his most notable qualities is that he has the ability to speak. Johnny got him as a birthday gift for his 11th birthday. He's a dog mutated by Susan and Mary. Since then, he became very intelligent. He is also a master at karate, knows how to speak Chinese, play video games and gives great advice.

Name: Duon
Summary: Duon is a giant mechanical being constructed out of Shadow Bugs. It was created after Mr. Game & Watch's defeat, although it was defeated again.

Name: Dyuragaua
Summary: Dyuragaua is a Flying Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Season 8.0.

Name: Edrad Liones
Summary: Edrad Liones (エドラド・リオネス, Edorado Rionesu) is Arrancar Trece (13) in Sōsuke Aizen's army and one of Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez's five Fracción.

Name: Edward Weevil
Summary: Edward Weevil is one of the Royal Shichibukai, and is the self-proclaimed son of Whitebeard. He is violent, cruel, but most notable – a momma's boy. He believes that family relates solely to blood, and thus hates the Whitebeard alliance, as they claim to be the sons of Whitebeard despite having no blood connection to him.

Name: Elder Centipede
Summary: Elder Centipede was a high ranking member of the Monster Association who first appeared in S-City, wreaking havoc and fighting the S-Class heroes Metal Bat and Bofoi.

Name: Elder Princess Shroob
Summary: Elder Princess Shroob, or Princess Shroob, is the leader of the Shroob race who invade the Mushroom Kingdom in Mario & Luigi: Partners in Time.

Name: Elizabello II
Summary: King Elizabello II was introduced in Fighting Block B within the Corrida Colosseum. He is known as "The Fighting King" and to wield a powerful attack said to be capable of defeating a Yonko].

Name: Emilou Apacci
Summary: Emilou Apacci (エミルー・アパッチ, Emirū Apacchi) is the 54th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and one of Tier Harribel's three Fracción, collectively known as the Tres Bestias.

Name: Empress of the Skies
Summary: The Empress of the Skies governs nature itself. At the beginning of it all, the Empress struck a deal with the Goddess of Decay, agreeing that the latter would be responsible for deciding how all living things should die. All the Empress had to do was ensure no organism would perish before their time.

Name: En'enra
Summary: En'enra is an ancient smoke-based youkai long since sealed. It has been recently unsealed by Kosuzu in order to get rid of a word-eating youkai, but broke free and started attacking Gensokyo. It was eventually sealed and defeated by Reimu and Marisa.

Name: Enel
Summary: Enel is the former "God" of Skypiea and the main antagonist of the Skypiea Arc. Two years ago, after his defeat by the Straw Hat Pirates, he arrived at the moon and became its new ruler.

Name: Enji Todoroki (Endeavor)
Summary: Enji Todoroki (轟炎司 Todoroki Enji), also known as Endeavor (エンデヴァー Endevā), is the Pro Hero with the highest tally of resolved cases in history, husband to Rei Todoroki, and father of Toya, Fuyumi, Natsuo, and Shoto Todoroki. Formerly the No. 2 Hero, he took the place of No. 1 after the retirement of All Might.

Name: Eo Garudia
Summary: Tier: High 6-C

Name: Eruzerion
Summary: Eruzerion is an Elder Dragon introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Z.

Name: Espinas
Summary: Espinas, also known as the Thorn Wyvern, is an incredibly powerful species of Flying Wyvern that spends much of its time asleep within its territory. Infamously, its shell is so tough that it can simply sleep through most creatures' attempts to attack it, while its thorny exterior envenoms the same would-be attackers. Should a determined or dangerous foe cause it to stir, however, it flies into a murderous rage that can quell even Elder Dragons. It was first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Season 2.0.

Name: Evil Natural Water
Summary: Evil Natural Water (エビル天然水てんねんすい, Ebiru Tennensui?) is a mighty being that works for the Monster Association, an elite group of horrifying creatures working to dismantle the Hero Association.

Name: Evil Ryu
Summary: Evil Ryu (殺意の波動に目覚めたリュウ, Ryu with the Surge of Killing Intent Awakened), is a character from the Street Fighter series who was originally featured in the 1996 Street Fighter Zero manga before appearing as a playable fighter in Street Fighter Alpha 2. This is the form Ryu takes if he ever succumbs to the Satsui no Hado. Ryu ultimately purged his evil half when he overcame the Satsui no Hado in Street Fighter V, but doing so gave birth to Kage.

Name: Fatalis
Summary: When the world is full of wyverns The legend is revived Meat is eaten, Bone is crunched. And blood is sucked up dry He burns the earth And melts through iron He boils the rivers And mows down trees He awakens the winds And lights an inferno He is called Fatalis The wyvern of destiny He is called Fatalis The wyvern of destruction Call for help Run for your lives And don't forget to Pray to the skies He is called Fatalis The wyvern of destiny He is called Fatalis The wyvern of destruction Fatalis, Fatalis Heaven and Earth are yours Fatalis, Fatalis Heaven and Earth are yours

Name: Fawful
Summary: Fawful is a citizen of the Beanbean Kingdom who serves as a major antagonist in Mario & Luigi: Superstar Saga and Mario and Luigi: Bowser's Inside Story.

Name: Findorr Calius
Summary: Findorr Calius (フィンドール・キャリアス, Findōru Kyariasu) is the 24th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and one of Baraggan Louisenbairn's six Fracción.

Name: Flame Queen
Summary: Flame Princess (first name Phoebe and occasionally called FP) is the princess and ruler of the Fire Kingdom, as well as Finn's ex-girlfriend. When Jake asks Flambo if he knows any princesses that are Finn's age so he can fix his broken heart, he introduces Jake to Flame Princess. Flame Princess was locked away in a lantern in the main chamber of the Fire Kingdom when Jake first encounters her. It is later revealed that her father, the Flame King, put her there on Princess Bubblegum's advice when she was an infant, and she did not come out for 14 years. She has a short temper, trust issues, and a heat core that can destroy the world if overblown with emotions.

Name: Flash Magnus
Summary: Flash Magnus is one of the six Pillars of Equestria.

Name: Flashy Flash
Summary: Flashy Flash (閃せん光こうのフラッシュ, Senkō no Furasshu?) is an S-Class hero, Rank 13 for the Hero Association. As his nickname would imply, he's well known for his extraordinary speed. He was the classmate of Sonic in the 44th period of the Ninja Village. For some reason, he destroyed the Ninja Village and killed all the instructors, officials, and classmates during the graduation exams.

Name: FLDSMDFR
Origin: Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs
Summary: The Flint Lockwood Diatonic Super Mutating Dynamic Food Replicator, or FLDSMDFR for short, is the machine which the two Cloudy With A Chance Of Meatballs movies revolve around.

Name: Flint Lockwood
Origin: Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs
Summary: Flint Lockwood is an eccentric and revolutionary inventor, from the town of Swallow Falls, who dreams of creating amazing things that can change everyone's life. He is the main character and protagonist of Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs and Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs 2.

Name: Fluttershy
Key: '''Base Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''Rainbow Power'''
Summary: Fluttershy is one of the main protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Frankenstein (Godzilla)
Summary: Frankenstein (フランケンシュタイン), otherwise known as Frankenstein's monster, is a creature from the 1818 horror novel Frankenstein; or, the Modern Prometheus by Mary Shelley.

Name: Frankenstein's Monster (Berserker of Black)
Summary: nan

Name: Franky
Key: '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: "Iron Man" Franky, real name Cutty Flam, is the shipwright of the Straw Hat Pirates under captain Monkey D. Luffy. As his epithet implies, he is a cyborg, having rebuilt his own body from iron scraps after he was run over by a sea train. He was formerly a member of a criminal shipbreaking gang called the Franky Family, which operated in the shipbuilders' haven of Water 7. He encountered the Straw Hats when he and the Franky Family brutally beat Usopp and stole a great deal of money from the crew while they were attempting to get their boat fixed on the island. However, his interests subsequently aligned with the Straw Hats' when the secret government organization CP9 kidnapped both him and their crewmate Nico Robin in a bid to construct the ancient superweapon Pluton, which he owned the blueprints to. After escaping the clutches of CP9, Franky decided to join their crew, drawn by their dedication to both their ship and their fellow crewmen.

Name: Fubuki (Blizzard of Hell)
Summary: Fubuki (フブキ?), also known by her hero alias Blizzard of Hell is the B-Class Rank 1 professional hero of the Hero Association. She is an Esper, the younger sister of Tatsumaki, and the leader of the Blizzard Group, a B-Class hero faction. She and her sister are known as the Psychic Sisters. Fubuki is one of the few people who are aware of Saitama's strength and is currently trying to recruit him into her group. She's also a self-declared member of the Saitama Group.

Name: Fuhrer Ugly
Summary: Fuhrer Ugly is a Dragon level Mysterious Being and a member of the Monster Association. He is an Ugmon, an ugly human that became a monster due to his extreme amount of jealousy and self hatred.

Name: Fumikage Tokoyami (Tsukuyomi)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Fumikage Tokoyami (常闇踏陰 Tokoyami Fumikage), also known as Tsukuyomi (ツクヨミ Tsukuyomi), is a member of Class 1-A at U.A. High School. An oddly dark and serious individual, his strange mannerisms belie his powerful Quirk and the heart of a true hero, earning him an internship under Hawks, one of Japan's top Pro Heroes.

Name: Funshine Bear (2019)
Summary: Funshine Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with exploring and protecting the Silver Lining. He's the blindly optimistic co-pilot of the Cloudseeker who's always looking to have as much fun as possible. He rarely takes things seriously, which has both helped with the team's morale but also hindered their progress, depending on the situation. As a thrill seeker, Funshine's hobbies include hang-gliding and skating; he also is seen working on a superhero comic book from time to time.

Name: Gaira
Summary: Gaira (ガイラ) is a Frankenstein-spawn kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1966 Toho film, The War of the Gargantuas.

Name: Gaismagorm
Summary: Gaismagorm, also known as the Abyssal Archdemon, is an enormous Elder Dragon that lurks in the depths of the earth. It possesses great physical strength as well as the ability to command swarms of flying lamprey-like Qurio, draining the life from entire ecosystems and empowering itself before emerging on the surface. Fifty years prior to the events of Monster Hunter Rise, it attempted to surface in the Kingdom and clashed with an Elder Dragon who had already claimed the region as its territory, Malzeno. It was first introduced in Monster Hunter Rise: Sunbreak.

Name: Gale Wind
Summary: Gale Wind (疾風のウィンド, Hayate no uindo) was a powerful ninja, who originated from the same village as Speed-o'-Sound Sonic and Flashy Flash. He was from the 37th graduating class, known as "Golden," along with his partner Hellfire Flame. Originally a human, he eventually decided to join the Monster Association while becoming a monster himself, as he sympathized with the association's goal of ruling over the world. However, his main goal was to kill the S-Class hero, Flashy Flash.

Name: Galleom
Summary: Galleom is a boss in the Super Smash Bros. series, appearing first as a member of the Subspace Army serving Tabuu, and latter as a lackey of Galeem and Dharkon.

Name: Gantenbainne Mosqueda
Summary: Gantenbainne Mosqueda (ガンテンバイン・モスケーダ, Gantenbain Mosukēda) is the 107th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army.

Name: Garland (Final Fantasy I)
Summary: Garland is the primary antagonist of Final Fantasy, originally a rogue knight from World A who abducted Princess Sarah before he was defeated by the Warrior of Light. But by fate, Garland was spirited away into World B where he ended up becoming the most faithful servant of Chaos in their battle against Cosmos and her warriors. But during the final cycle, as his fellow warriors have forsaken Chaos to act on their own whims, Garland reveals he and Chaos are bond by fate before serving as the god's last line of defense against the Warriors of Cosmos. Upon his defeat, Garland would end up in World A's distant past where he forged a pact with the Four Fiends and became the very creature whose memory inspired the creation of Chaos himself.

Name: Garou
Key: '''Hero Hunter''' | '''Half-Monster''' | '''Post-Darkshine''' | '''Post-Sage Centipede''' | '''Awakened Garou''' | '''Parallel Timeline Awakened Garou'''
Summary: Saitama: Hey, you got a little better again! Garou: You call this a little?!

Name: Gearsper
Summary: Gearsper, C-Class Rank 133, is a professional hero and member of the hero association. He believes himself to have telekinetic powers similar to the esper sisters, and wears a large helmet so as to be able to control his full output. His belief was revealed to be true during his confrontation against Nyan, where he unleashed his full telekinetic output against the cadre before knocking himself unconscious.

Name: Gecko Moria
Summary: Gecko Moria is a villain from One Piece, and was a member of the Shichibukai. He resided on the largest ship in the world, Thriller Bark, and his Devil Fruit powers can manipulate shadows. His former bounty is 320,000,000 Beli. He is also the main antagonist of the Thriller Bark Arc who stole Brook's and various other beings' shadows with the use of the Kage Kage no Mi. He took part in the Battle of Marineford and sided with the Marines, along with most of the other Shichibukai. Upon the war's end, he was stripped of his title, and was to be eliminated by Donquixote Doflamingo, but managed to escape before he was killed. He was last seen travelling to the island of Hachinosu in search of his subordinate Absalom, and being given an offer to join Blackbeard's crew after finding out Absalom had been killed to poach his Devil Fruit.

Name: Gen
Summary: Gen is a character from the Street Fighter series. Debuting in the first Street Fighter game, he is one of the most dangerous characters in Street Fighter lore.

Name: Geno
Summary: Geno (whose real name is ♥♪!?) is a warrior from Star Road and one of Mario's partners in Super Mario RPG: Legend of the Seven Stars.

Name: Genos (Demon Cyborg)
Key: '''Beginning of Series''' | '''House of Evolution to Alien Conquerors Arc''' | '''Post-VGS''' | '''Post-G4''' | '''Post-Superfight''' | '''Post-Elder Centipede'''
Summary: King: Mr. Genos risked his life to save Miss Tatsumaki. It was truly admirable! Saitama: So that's why! You really hung in there, Genos! Nice fight! Genos: Master... when the time came for me to self-destruct, I was no longer able to do it. Can one truly say I've become stronger? Saitama: I don't really get it, but you didn't blow up, right? [touches his core] That means this part here got stronger too, doesn't it?

Name: Gensokyo
Key: '''Average Humans''' | '''Fairies''' | '''Average Youkai''' | '''Stronger Individuals''' | '''Dragon God & Eirin Yagakoro'''
Summary: Gensokyo is a land hidden somewhere in Japan. Formerly mere an isolated region of the country infested by Youkai, it has now since been separated from the "Outside World" and now exists as one of the last places where Youkai and fantasy can thrive.

Name: Geralt of Rivia (Monster Hunter)
Summary: Geralt of Rivia is a warrior from another world known as a Witcher. Transported to the New World by the magic of a Leshen, a powerful spirit of nature, he was enlisted by the Fifth Fleet to hunt down the creature, using his special skills in such a way that even the Hunter must respect.

Name: Gerard Valkyrie
Summary: Gerard Valkyrie (ジェラルド・ヴァルキリー, Jerarudo Varukirī?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "M" - The Miracle, as well as one of Yhwach's Schutzstaffel (親衛隊シュッツシュタッフェル, Shuttsushutafferu?, German for "Protective Echelon", Japanese for "Elite/Imperial Guards"). He is also the heart of the Soul King.

Name: Geryuganshoop
Summary: Geryuganshoop was one of the Dark Matter Thieves, a group of alien pirates traveling across the universe. He was one of Boros' strongest fighters, claiming himself to be the greatest psychic in the universe. Despite displaying immense power, he seemed easily flustered under pressure, and even after getting serious, was effortlessly killed when Saitama split his head with a rock.

Name: Geten
Summary: Geten is a former member of the Meta Liberation Army and is currently one of the nine lieutenants of the Paranormal Liberation Front. He's never attended a hero school and has spent most of his life training his Quirk. He firmly believes that strength equals one's worth and those who lack strength are worthless.

Name: Giant Catfish
Summary: The Giant Catfish (大ナマズ Oo Namazu) is a villainous avatar of Taisui Xingjun, a God of Calamity who sent assassins (disguised as familiar characters) to attack Hong Meiling in her dreams. Its objective, as it claims, was to drain her of her power so that it could move the Earth and return to this world once again. It also spoke quite strongly of its plans to cause various disasters to Gensokyo. ZUN and Twilight Frontier has left no official comment about the catfish and its gender is unknown.

Name: Giant Toad
Summary: The Giant Toad is the guardian of the pond named after itself. It is usually calm and gentle, even protecting the pond.

Name: Giga Bowser
Summary: Giga Bowser is the non-canon, more monstrous super form of Bowser in the Super Smash Bros. series, and the boss of the Adventure Mode and the final event of the Event mode in Super Smash Bros. Melee. He comes to be if one clears Adventure Mode on the Normal difficulty level or higher without using any continues. If so, after one beats Bowser, his trophy flies back up on the stage, gets struck by lightning, and Giga Bowser breaks out. During Super Smash Bros. Brawl and onwards, this form was relegated to Bowser's Final Smash.

Name: Gigantomachia
Summary: Gigantomachia (ギガントマキア Gigantomakia) is a villain associated with the League of Villains. He is one of All For One's faithful servants and his former bodyguard, later serving his successor, Tomura Shigaraki. He is an incredibly powerful force, considered a "walking disaster" by heroes.

Name: Gild Tesoro
Summary: Gild Tesoro is the main antagonist of One Piece Film: Gold. He is a non-canon character.

Name: Gill
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:TheMarkOfMyDignityShallScarThyDNA.ogg

Name: Gin Ichimaru
Summary: Gin Ichimaru (市丸 ギン, Ichimaru Gin) was the captain of the 3rd Division of the Gotei 13 until he betrayed Soul Society, alongside Sōsuke Aizen and Kaname Tōsen. His lieutenant was Izuru Kira. He formerly served as the lieutenant of the 5th Division under Sōsuke Aizen and the 3rd Seat of the 5th Division under Shinji Hirako.

Name: Giselle Gewelle
Summary: Giselle Gewelle (ジゼル・ジュエル, Jizeru Jueru?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Stern Ritter, possessing the designation "Z" - The Zombie.

Name: Gladius
Summary: As a Donquixote Family Executive, Gladius resided close by to his master Donquixote Doflamingo, who was the king of Dressrosa.

Name: Godzilla (GMK)
Summary: The GMK Godzilla (ＧジーＭエムＫケイゴジラ, GMK Gojira?) is a kaiju that appeared in the 2001 Godzilla film, Godzilla, Mothra and King Ghidorah: Giant Monsters All-Out Attack.

Name: Godzilla (Godzilla 2000: Millennium)
Summary: The Millennium Godzilla (ミレニアムゴジラ, Mireniamu Gojira?) is a kaiju that appeared in the 1999 Godzilla film, Godzilla 2000: Millennium.

Name: Godzilla (Kiryu Saga)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:Godzilla1999-2004SFX.ogg

Name: Godzilla (Original)
Summary: Godzilla (ゴジラ, Gojira?) was designed by Teizo Toshimitsu and Akira Watanabe under Eiji Tsuburaya's supervision. Early on, Tanaka contemplated on having the monster be gorilla-like or whale-like in design due to the name "Gojira" (a combination of the Japanese words for gorilla which is gorira, and whale which is kujira) but eventually settled on a dinosaur-like design.

Name: Godzilla (Showa)
Key: '''Godzilla Raids Again''' | '''King Kong vs. Godzilla/Mothra vs. Godzilla''' | '''Ghidorah the Three-Headed Monster and ahead/End of Zone Fighter''' | '''End of Showa era'''
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:Showa_Godzilla_Roar.ogg

Name: Gogmazios
Summary: Gogmazios is a giant Elder Dragon which was introduced in Monster Hunter 4 Ultimate. It utilizes the fire element, a special tar-like substance, which it uses to incapacitate its prey, and its giant size against those who dare attack it.

Name: Good Luck Bear (2019)
Summary: Good Luck Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with exploring and protecting the Silver Lining. Due to his lucky streak and natural intuition, he's assigned the role of the Cloudseeker's navigator. His Belly Badge power ensures luck is always on his side, which has frequently helped the crew on their mission. He's often the one to reassure his companions when things are tense. On the other hand, he can also be overconfident and over-reliant on this power. On multiple occasions, he's dived headfirst into situations without thinking things through.

Name: Goomboss
Summary: Tier: High 6-A

Name: Gore Magala
Key: '''Gore Magala''' | '''Chaotic Gore Magala''' | '''Shagaru Magala''' | '''Risen Shagaru Magala'''
Summary: Gore Magala debuted as the flagship monster of "Monster Hunter 4", being the main antagonist of the games low rank story.

Name: Gorosaurus (Showa)
Summary: Gorosaurus (ゴロザウルス Gorozaurusu) is a dinosaur kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1967 Toho film, King Kong Escapes.

Name: Goto Imasuji (Muscular)
Summary: Goto Imasuji (今筋強斗 Imasuji Gōto), also known as Muscular (マスキュラー Masukyurā), was a member of the League of Villain's Vanguard Action Squad. He lost his left eye to the efforts of Water Hose, a pair of Pro Heroes who defended a town he was attacking. Because of this, he appears at U.A.'s secret summer training camp to attack Water Hose's only son, Kota Izumi, forcing Deku to intervene and save the boy from the villain's wrath.

Name: Gouken
Summary: Gouken (ゴウケン 剛拳, Gōken) "Constitutionality", "Strong Fist", is a playable character in the Street Fighter series. He is Ryu's adoptive father, Ryu and Ken's martial arts master, Dan's former master as well as Akuma's older brother.

Name: Gouketsu
Summary: Gouketsu was a formidable monster dispatched by Psykos to infiltrate the "Super Fight" martial arts tournament, destroying anyone in his way.

Name: Great Jagras
Summary: Great Jagras is a monster introduced in Monster Hunter World.

Name: Gremmy Thoumeaux
Summary: Gremmy Thoumeaux (グレミィ・トゥミュー, Guremī Tumyū?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "V" - "The Visionary".

Name: Greninja (Super Smash Bros)
Summary: Greninja is a Water/Dark type Pokemon and the final evolution of Froakie. They are hailed as being as dangerous as any other known ninja. This specific Greninja witnessed the intense battles the Smash Bros fighters undertook, and entered it himself as a surprise entrance. He has stayed with his newfound fighting partners ever since.

Name: Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez
Summary: Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez (グリムジョー・ジャガージャック, Gurimujō Jagājakku?) is an Arrancar and was the Sexta (6th) Espada in Sōsuke Aizen's affiliated army.

Name: Groribas
Summary: Groribas was a member of the Dark Matter Thieves, a group of alien pirates that traveled across the universe. Despite being one of Boros' top fighters, he was killed instantly by Saitama.

Name: Grumpy Bear (2019)
Summary: Grumpy Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with protecting the Silver Lining. He is the creator of the Cloudseeker, the vehicle the bears use to navigate the uncharted territory. He's frequently having to upgrade or fix it, thanks to the unpredictability of the area they explore. As the crew's resident worrywart, he often either brings up an important detail the rest of the Bears hadn't considered, or he reaches a point where his pessimism needs to be dialed back.

Name: Grøh
Summary: Grøh is a character who appeared in the Soul series reboot Soul Calibur Vl. He serves as one of the main protagonists of the Libra of Souls storyline. He is a member of the Aval Organization, an organization form to clear the world of Malfested also known as "Outsiders" by Aval. Grøh is considered to be the strongest fighter of Aval and one of the most loyal members. Throughout the story, his goal is to hunt down and kill Azwel who betrayed the Aval Organization. But he also has a personal reason for going after Azwel as he forced him to kill his best friend Curtis after he turned him into a Malfested right before his eyes and having him try to kill Grøh. It turns out that Grøh is one of Azwel's successful experiment in terms of enhancing warriors with the power of Soul Edge shards. As such he technically counts as an "Outsider" and plans to kill himself once his job is done.

Name: Guanzorumu
Summary: Guanzorumus are Elder Dragons introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G10.

Name: Guenael Lee
Summary: Guenael Lee (グエナエル・リー, Guenaeru Rī) is a creation of Gremmy Thoumeaux's The Visionary ability, originally thought to be a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "V – Vanishing Point".

Name: Guernika (One Piece)
Summary: Guernika was one of the best agents for the World Government's top group of secret agents and assassains, known as Cipher Pol 0. He was first seen on Dressrosa, where he aided Donquixote Doflamingo in setting up a trap for Trafalgar Law by helping Doflamingo fake his resignation from the Seven Warlords.

Name: Hajrudin
Summary: "Pirate Mercenary" Hajrudin is a giant warrior described as the "new generation" from Elbaf and joined as a gladiator at the Corrida Colosseum to compete for the Mera Mera no Mi. He was first mentioned by a Marine officer who was speaking to Vice Admiral Maynard. He is the sixth division leader of the Straw Hat Grand Fleet after the events of Dressrosa.

Name: Hariet
Summary: Hariet is the second Broodal fought in Super Mario Odyssey. She is the only female Broodal. Although it is not confirmed, she seems to be the second-in-command of the 4 main Broodals, due to being fought right before Topper in Bowser's kingdom.

Name: Harudomeguru
Summary: Harudomerugu is an Elder Dragon first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G7.

Name: Heavy Lobster
Summary: Heavy Lobster is a mechanical lobster-esque boss character who first appeared in Kirby Super Star.

Name: Heihachi Mishima
Summary: Heihachi Mishima (roughly translates to "Eighth Peace of the Third Island") is a fictional Japanese character in the Tekken fighting game series serving as one of the main antagonists. He is the son of Jinpachi Mishima, the father of Kazuya Mishima and Lars Alexandersson, the adopted father of Lee Chaolan and the grandfather of Jin Kazama.

Name: Hellfire Flame
Summary: Hellfire Flame (業火のフレイム, Gōka no fureimu) was a powerful ninja, who originated from the same village as Speed-o'-Sound Sonic and Flashy Flash. He was from the 37th graduating class, known as "Golden," along with his partner Gale Wind. Originally a human, he eventually decided to join the Monster Association while becoming a monster himself, as he sympathized with the association's goal of ruling over the world. However, his main goal was to kill the S-Class hero, Flashy Flash.

Name: Hero Association
Summary: The Hero Association is an organization founded by the multi-millionaire Agoni after his grandson was saved from a monster by a passerby. Operating independently of the government, the Hero Association recruits various individuals, ordinary and extraordinary alike, to fight for justice against the evil in the world. Those registered within the National Hero Registry database are tasked with protecting civilians from harm against monsters, villains, natural disasters, and other threats and are compensated for their efforts.

Name: Hikone Ubuginu
Summary: Hikone Ubuginu (産絹彦禰, Ubuginu Hikone) a hybrid soul created by Tokinada to become the new Soul King.

Name: Hina (One Piece)
Summary: "Black Cage" Hina is a Marine officer and a former classmate of Vice Admiral Smoker. Jango and Fullbody are currently her subordinates. She was originally introduced as a Captain. During the timeskip, she was promoted to the rank of Rear Admiral.

Name: Hiyori Sarugaki
Summary: Hiyori Sarugaki (猿柿 ひよ里, Sarugaki Hiyori) is the former lieutenant of the 12th Division under Captains Kirio Hikifune and Kisuke Urahara, and currently a Visored.

Name: Hody Jones
Summary: Hody Jones is the main antagonist of the Fishman Island Arc and a firm follower of the radical Fishman pirate Arlong. He is a great white shark Fishman who since his childhood was exposed and bathed in the hatred for the human race and grew to hold a massive disliking toward them, willing to go to extreme lengths to maintain the animosity between them.

Name: Hole Punch (Paper Mario)
Summary: Hole Punch is the eighth boss of The Origami King. After removing the sun from the sky, he hid within the singing Toad Temple.

Name: Homeless Emperor
Summary: Homeless Emperor was once a common tramp who encountered a mysterious divine entity, who claimed to be "God", that gave him the incredible power of summoning energy spheres similar to little suns, which explode on contact and create huge flaming bursts.

Name: Hong Meiling
Summary: Hong Meiling (紅 美鈴) is a youkai, though it isn't currently known which specific category she actually belongs to. She's the gatekeeper of the Scarlet Devil Mansion. She is known for her mastery of the martial arts, part of which can be seen from her movement which is performed with Shin-Kyaku (a move in Chinese martial arts).

Name: Hood (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Hood (フード Fūdo), also known simply as High-End (ハイエンド Hai Endo), was one of Dr. Garaki's intelligent High-End Nomu and the primary antagonist of the Pro Hero Arc.

Name: Huff N. Puff
Summary: Huff N. Puff is the leader of the Ruff Puffs and main antagonist of the sixth chapter of Paper Mario. He uses a Puff-Puff Machine to cover Flower Fields in clouds, which threatens the lives of its plant inhabitants. When Paper Mario reaches him in Cloudy Climb, they fight, and Huff N. Puff is defeated.

Name: Hyouzou
Summary: Hyouzou is a poisonous blue-ringed octopus merman. Prior to his imprisonment, he was a mercenary and working as the New Fish-Man Pirates' assassin, and later became one of the officers. Hyouzou was also known as the strongest swordsman on Fish-Man Island.

Name: Ice Climbers (Smash Bros.)
Summary: The Ice Climbers are fighters from the iconic NES game Ice Climbers. First originating in Super Smash Bros. Melee, the Climbers, comprised of Popo and Nana, fight as a team together and use various ice-based moves based off their games. They appeared in it's sequel, Super Smash Bros. Brawl, but did not appear in Super Smash Bros. 4. They returned in 2018 in Super Smash Bros. Ultimate

Name: Ice King (Adventure Time)
Summary: The Ice King, also known as Simon Petrikov was a main recurring antagonist in Adventure Time, though now is considered something similar to a protagonist and was reverted back into his sane, non-magic human self in the finale of the main series. In the background of the show, before The Great Mushroom War, Simon was a respectable archaeologist, appearing to be mild-mannered, intelligent, kind and adventurous. On a trip to Scandinavia, Simon discovered a Crown of mysterious origin. After wearing his crown, his life changed for the worse. His relationship with his fiance was shattered and his sanity was starting to diminish. However, the crown would keep him alive, allowing him to be one of the very few human survivors of The Great Mushroom War.

Name: Ichigo Kurosaki (Post-Timeskip)
Summary: Ichigo Kurosaki (黒崎くろさき 一いち護ご, Kurosaki Ichigo?) is the son of Masaki Kurosaki and Isshin Kurosaki, a Quincy with the powers of a Soul Reaper. Years after the death of his mother, Ichigo uses his innate spiritual awareness to help local ghosts, and unlocks his potential as a Soul Reaper when Rukia Kuchiki comes along in pursuit of a Hollow.

Name: Ichigo Kurosaki (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''Substitute Soul Reaper''' | '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Post-Bankai Training''' | '''Post-Visored Training''' | '''Final Grimmjow Fight''' | '''Full Hollowfication''' | '''Post-Resurrection''' | '''Post-Dangai Training'''
Summary: Ichigo Kurosaki (黒崎くろさき 一いち護ご, Kurosaki Ichigo?) is the son of Masaki and Isshin Kurosaki, a Quincy with the powers of a Soul Reaper. Years after the death of his mother, Ichigo uses his innate spiritual awareness to help local ghosts, and unlocks his potential as a Soul Reaper when Rukia Kuchiki comes along in pursuit of a Hollow.

Name: Ideo
Summary: "Destruction Cannon" Ideo is a XXX rank boxer who joined as a gladiator at the Corrida Colosseum to compete for the Mera Mera no Mi. He is a member of the Longarm Tribe. He formed the XXX Gym Martial Arts Alliance along with three other gladiators from the Colosseum and acts as their representative. He is the 4th division commander of the Straw Hat Grand Fleet.

Name: Iggy Koopa
Summary: Iggy Koopa is one of the Koopalings, a clan of seven siblings that act as leaders of the Koopa Troop under Bowser (originally considered his children). Iggy is depicted as a crazed, mechanical genius and childish in personality when together with Lemmy Koopa. His two main outstanding physical characteristics are his glasses and light green hair (originally pink, light blue, and yellow). In later appearances, he is shown to be the thinnest and fastest of the Koopalings. Iggy is named after Iggy Pop, a famous punk rock singer and leader of the band The Stooges.

Name: Ikkaku Madarame
Summary: Ikkaku Madarame (斑目 一角, Madarame Ikkaku) is the lieutenant and former 3rd Seat officer in the 11th Division of the Gotei 13, under Captain Kenpachi Zaraki.

Name: Ikomikidomoe
Summary: Ikomikidomoe (已己巳己巴) is an ancient Hollow that attacked Soul Society in the past but was defeated by Ichibē Hyōsube and was sealed inside a Zanpakutō by Ōetsu Nimaiya.

Name: Inagami
Summary: Inagami is an Elder Dragon first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G5.

Name: Incineroar (Super Smash Bros)
Summary: Incineroar is a fiery hotshot newcomer to the Super Smash Bros roster, being the only new Pokemon in its latest game. But he can more than back it up with his strength in the ring, his battle prowess earning him a spot as one of the toughest combatants to ever come out of the Pokemon series, his abilities allowing him to already fight blow for blow with the veterans. Like any cat however, he has a softer side, making friends with many of the younger, smaller Pokemon outside the ring.

Name: Inuarashi
Summary: Duke Inuarashi is a canine mink and one of the two rulers of the Mokomo Dukedom, dubbed the "Ruler of Day" as he rules over the Mokomo Dukedom from 6:00 AM to 6:00 PM. He and Nekomamushi serve as retainers for the Kozuki Family of Wano Kingdom.

Name: Isabelle (Smash Bros.)
Summary: Isabelle (しずえ, Shizue) is a playable character in Super Smash Bros. Ultimate. She is the 68th fighter overall. While she shares many moves with Villager, Isabelle is not an Echo Fighter and is instead a semi-clone.

Name: Isamu (Child Emperor)
Summary: Child Emperor (童帝, Dōtei) is the S-Class Rank 5 hero for the Hero Association. So far, he is the youngest hero in the Hero Association. He has his own laboratory in Y-City.

Name: Isane Kotetsu
Summary: Isane Kotetsu (虎徹 勇音, Kotetsu Isane) was the lieutenant of the 4th Division under Captain Retsu Unohana, but after Unohana’s death during the Thousand-Year Blood War, she was promoted to the rank of Captain.

Name: Isshin Kurosaki
Summary: Isshin Kurosaki (黒崎 一心, Kurosaki Isshin), formerly known as Isshin Shiba (志波 一心, Shiba Isshin), is the former captain of the 10th Division, husband of Masaki Kurosaki, father of Ichigo Kurosaki, Karin Kurosaki, and Yuzu Kurosaki. Isshin is the former head of a branch of the Shiba Clan and the current head of the Kurosaki family.

Name: Ivan (Power Rangers)
Summary: Ivan, commonly refereed to as Sir Ivan of Zandar is a main character of Power Rangers: Dino Charge and Power Rangers: Dino Super Charge. He once lived as a proud knight of the kingdom of Zandar, but one day while waking the then prince of Zandar on an unknown trip, he encountered the ruthless Fury. After a fierce but short lived battle, he was captured by Fury but the prince managed to escape.

Name: Ivy Valentine
Summary: Isabella "Ivy" Valentine is a character in the Soul series of fighting games and a staple character of the franchise. Ivy is the daughter of Cervantes de Leon and is of cursed blood due to Cervantes having been possessed by Soul Edge when she was conceived. Her goal is to find a way to erase Soul Edge from existence, even if it means her dying because of her connection to the blade. Her Whip Blade Valentine is a living sword that was granted life by Nightmare's hand.

Name: Izou (One Piece)
Summary: Izou was the former commander of the 16th division of the Whitebeard Pirates and a former retainer of the Wano Country daimyo Kozuki Oden. He was the older brother of fellow retainer Kikunojo.

Name: Izuku Midoriya (Deku) (Final Act)
Summary: Izuku Midoriya (緑谷出久 Midoriya Izuku), also known as the One For All Hero: Deku (ワン・フォー・オール ヒーロー デク Wan Fō Ōru Hīrō: Deku), is one of the 20% of people on Earth who were born without a Quirk, a natural superpower that is a basic biological function in modern society, causing him endless torment at school. However, thanks to his innate heroism, he was able to earn the Quirk "One For All", bestowed upon him by his idol All Might, and use it to grow into one of the world's greatest heroes.

Name: Izuku Midoriya (Deku) (Pre-Final Act)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Endeavor Agency Arc'''
Summary: Izuku Midoriya (緑谷出久 Midoriya Izuku), also known as Deku (デク Deku), was one of the 20 percent of people on Earth to be born without a quirk, a natural superpower that is a basic biological function in the modern society, earning him endless amounts of torment and bullying in school.

Name: Izuru Kira
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War'''
Summary: Izuru Kira (吉良 イヅル, Kira Izuru) is the lieutenant of the 3rd Division in the Gotei 13, formerly under Captain Gin Ichimaru and currently under Captain Rōjūrō Ōtoribashi.

Name: Jabra
Summary: Jabra is one of the assassins of CP9. He is the last to be revealed, and is the 3rd strongest behind Kaku and Rob Lucci. He is a compulsive liar and tends to be very arrogant. He verbally assaults Lucci and Kaku upon learning that they both have superior physical strength to him. He is a Wolf Zoan Devil Fruit eater.

Name: Jack (One Piece)
Summary: Jack, also known by his epithet the Drought, is an All-Star of the Beast Pirates, one of the top three executives of the crew second only to the Emperor Kaidou in terms of authority. Together with his comrades King and Queen, they are informally referred to as the Calamities, due to their respective epithets relating to natural disasters.

Name: Jack the Ripper (Assassin of Black)
Summary: Assassin of Black is the Assassin-class Servant of the Black Faction in the Great Holy Grail War, originally summoned by Hyouma Sagara. However, she rejects him as a Master and instead chooses Reika Rikudou as her surrogate mother.

Name: Jackie Tristan
Summary: Jackie Tristan (ジャッキー トリスタン, Jakkī Torisutan) is a Human who formerly possessed Fullbring powers and is a former member of the organization known as Xcution.

Name: Jeanne d'Arc (Ruler)
Summary: nan

Name: Jerome Guizbatt
Summary: Jerome Guizbatt (ジェローム・ギズバット, Jerōmu Gizubatto) is a Quincy and member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "R" - "The Roar".

Name: Jesus Burgess
Summary: Jesus Burgess, nicknamed "Champion", is the helmsman and captain of the First Ship of the Black Beard Pirates. During this time his bounty was of 20,000,000 belly.

Name: Jigglypuff (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Jigglypuff (プリン, Purin), is a creature from the Pokémon series. It debuted in the series' first generation, and is considered part of the "perfect-attendance crew" throughout the entire Super Smash Bros. series.

Name: Jin Kazama
