Summary: Saitama (サイタマ?) is a human from Z-City who; through rigorous (sort of) training broke through his human limiters and achieved unbelievable strength and abilities. Never breaking a sweat, the name One Punch Man is fitting for the effortless wins Saitama has achieved through the series. Never going beyond a simple brawl, his sheer strength, speed, and power have effortlessly mowed down anyone in his way.

Name: Sajin Komamura
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Sajin Komamura (狛村 左陣, Komamura Sajin) is the former captain of the 7th Division. His lieutenant was Tetsuzaemon Iba.

Name: Salem
Summary: An incredibly enigmatic figure from Remnant's forgotten past, Salem is the true main antagonist of RWBY.

Name: Sanda
Summary: Sanda (サンダ Sanda) is a Frankenstein-spawn kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1966 Toho film, The War of the Gargantuas.

Name: Sandbag
Summary: Sandbag is a recurring character in the Smash Bros. series. It usually serves as the target of the Home-Run Contest.

Name: Sanji (Post-Timeskip)
Key: '''Fishman Island Saga to Early Whole Cake Island Saga''' | '''Late Whole Cake Island Saga to Early Wano Act 2''' | '''Late Wano Act 2''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Sanji Vinsmoke (サンジ・ヴィンスモーク, Sanji Vinsumōku?), more commonly known as "Sanji" is the crew's chain-smoking chef and a member of the Monster Trio. There is not a dish he cannot cook, a pretty girl he will not try to woo, or something he will not argue with Zoro over. As a chef, he believes that he cannot afford to harm his hands, and so uses a fighting style which uses only his feet called the "Black Leg Style" (Kuroashi no Waza).

Name: Sanji (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc'''
Summary: Sanji Vinsmoke, more commonly known as "Sanji" is the crew's chain-smoking chef and a member of the Monster Trio. There is not a dish he cannot cook, a pretty girl he will not try to woo, or something he will not argue with Zoro over. As a chef, he believes that he cannot afford to harm his hands, and so uses a fighting style which uses only his feet called the "Black Leg Style" (Kuroashi no Waza).

Name: Sasaki (One Piece)
Summary: "Overflowing" Sasaki is a Bluespine Unicornfish Fishman and one of the Tobiroppo, the strongest six Shinuchi of the Beasts Pirates. He also leads the crew's Armored Division Before joining the Beasts Pirates, he captained his own crew called the Sasaki Pirates.

Name: Satan (VShojo Mythos)
Summary: Eternal bliss. Fueled by a thousand, thousand souls that knew no better. Everlasting beauty. Fabricated. Unending peace. Upheld by condemning all who display excess of emotion. The blinding vanity of this shameless monument, made in praise to a creator that's been asleep for a billion years. It's palpable. Welcome, human souls, to the tenth circle of hell! A true testament to self-importance! Blind faith made manifest! Would be a shame if somebody fucked it up.

Name: Satori Komeiji
Summary: Satori Komeiji (古明地 さとり) is the mistress of the Palace of the Earth Spirits, and the elder sister of Koishi Komeiji. Her ability to passively read the minds of others has caused her to be loathed and feared by humans and youkai, but she finds love in the animals that cannot normally be understood by others. She has many pets, including Utsuho Reiuji and Rin Kaenbyou.

Name: Scourge (Robots in Disguise 2001)
Summary: Scourge was an Autobot protoform, part of a group of six Autobots sent to earth to reactivate Fortress Maximus. However, he would be stolen by Megatron and be used to bolster his forces, he corrupted the protoform by infusing it with his own evil spark. Due to Optimus Prime also being scanned when Megatron was searching for a suitable alternate mode for Scourge, Scourge would receive several attributes from Optimus himself.

Name: Scratchmen Apoo
Summary: Scratchmen Apoo, also known as "Roar of the Sea", is an infamous music-themed pirate from the Grand line and captain of the On The Air Pirates. He is one of twelve pirates who are referred to as the "Worst Generation" (formerly known as the "Eleven Supernovas"). After the timeskip, his bounty has been raised from 198,000,000 to 350,000,000.

Name: Sea Serpent (Godzilla)
Summary: Giant Sea Serpent (大ウミヘビ) is a giant serpent kaiju created by Toho that first appeared in the 1967 Toho film, King Kong Escapes.

Name: Seija Kijin
Summary: Seija Kijin (鬼人 正邪) is an amanojaku, a type of youkai that feeds on hate and anger and instigates others to do horrible things. As an amanojaku, Seija is unhappy when she is liked, pleased when she is hated, and is devoted to causing destruction and chaos for the sake of destruction and chaos. She eventually becomes a wanted youkai for her crimes, and is hunted down by humans and youkai across Gensokyo, who resort to using illegal spellcards considered "impossible to dodge" to defeat her.

Name: Seiran
Summary: Seiran (清蘭 Seiran) is a moon rabbit, and the stage 1 boss of Legacy of Lunatic Kingdom.

Name: Semiramis (Fate)
Summary: Assassin of Red is the Assassin-class Servant of the Red Faction in the Great Holy Grail War, summoned by Shirou Kotomine.

Name: Senna (Bleach)
Summary: Senna (茜雫) is a Shinigami that Ichigo and Rukia encounter in the real world. In actuality, Senna is the Shinenju a being that is composed entirely out of memories of lost souls.

Name: Senor Pink
Summary: Senor Pink is an officer of the Donquixote Pirates' Diamante Army, with a bounty of 58,000,000 Berry. He was also the widower of Russian and is the father of the late Gimlet.

Name: Seong Mi-na
Summary: Seong Mi-Na is a fictional character in Namco's Soul series of fighting games. Min-Na is one of the reoccuring characters within the series and is known for her upbeat personality and nature. She has a notable connection to Yun-Seong as well as Talim. She is close friends with Hwang.

Name: Setsuka
Summary: Setsuka is a character in the Soul series of fighting games. She is a wandering foreign swordswoman who seeks revenge against Mitsurugi for killing her master/adoptive father. She is currently hunting the Soul Edge to find the target of her vengeance, as she knows that he is searching for it as well.

Name: Shadoo
Summary: Shadoo is the secret boss in Super Paper Mario after completing the Flopside Pit of 100 Trials.

Name: Shadow Bugs
Summary: The Shadow Bugs are the mysterious embodiment of a primordial substance in the Smash Bros. universe. They are seemingly extracted from Mr. Game & Watch's body. They can take the form of nearly anything the user desire, even copying powers from the enemy.

Name: Shadow Queen
Summary: The Shadow Queen is a shadow demon sealed for over a thousand years who serves as the final boss of Paper Mario: The Thousand Year Door.

Name: Shantien
Summary: Shantien is an Elder Dragon first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G1.

Name: Share Bear (2019)
Summary: Share Bear is one of the five Care Bears tasked with exploring and protecting the Silver Lining. She is the team's communicator, receiving and relaying information from the Caring Tower. Additionally, she acts as the point of contact for any new species and civilizations the crew encounters. While Share is more than happy to help others however she can, this often leads her to putting a lot of pressure on herself and getting discouraged whenever she makes mistakes.

Name: Shawlong Koufang
Summary: Shawlong Koufang is the leader of Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez's Fracción and the 11th Arrancar in Sosuke Aizen's army, making him the eldest of the Números.

Name: Shaz Domino
Summary: Shaz Domino (シャズ・ドミノ, Shazu Domino) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "Ϛ" - "The Stigma".

Name: Shigeo Kageyama
Summary: Shigeo Kageyama, also known as Mob, is the protagonist of the manga/anime series Mob Psycho 100.

Name: Shingo Yabuki
Key: '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of NESTS Saga (KOF '99 to KOF 2001)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Shinji Hirako
Summary: Shinji Hirako (平ひら子こ 真しん子じ, Hirako Shinji?) is the captain of the 5th Division in the Gotei 13. His lieutenant is Momo Hinamori. He also served as a recruiter and the de facto leader of the Visored.

Name: Shinya Kamihara (Edgeshot)
Summary: Shinya Kamihara (紙原伸也 Kamihara Shinya), also known as Ninja Hero: Edgeshot (忍者ヒーロー エッジショット Ninja Hīrō Ejjishotto), is the former No. 5, now No. 4, Pro Hero and leader of The Lurkers.

Name: Shoto Todoroki (Shoto)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Endeavor Agency Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Shoto Todoroki (轟焦凍 Todoroki Shōto), also known as Shoto (ショート Shōto), is one of main protagonists of the My Hero Academia manga and anime series.

Name: Shroob
Summary: The Shroobs are a race of purple Toad-like aliens from the Shroob Planet, which was ruled by Princess Shroob and her older sister.

Name: Shunsui Kyōraku
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc''' | '''CFYOW Novel'''
Summary: Shunsui Sakuranosuke Jiro Kyoraku (京きょう楽らく 次じ郎ろう 佐さ蔵くら総のすけ 春しゅん水すい, Kyōraku no Jirō Sakuranosuke Shunsui?) is the captain of the 1st Division and Captain-Commander of the Gotei 13. His lieutenants are Nanao Ise and Genshirō Okikiba. He is the former captain of the 8th Division.

Name: Shūhei Hisagi
Summary: Shūhei Hisagi (檜佐木ひさぎ 修しゅう兵へい, Hisagi Shūhei?) is the co-lieutenant of the 9th Division, formerly under Captain Kaname Tosen and currently under Captain Kensei Muguruma. He shares his position with Mashiro Kuna.

Name: Shūkurō Tsukishima
Summary: Shūkurō Tsukishima (月島 秀九郎, Tsukishima Shūkurō) is a Fullbringer and a former member of Xcution.

Name: Sieg (Fate/Apocrypha)
Summary: nan

Name: Siegfried (Fate)
Summary: Saber of Black is the Saber-class Servant of the Black Faction during the Great Holy Grail War, summoned by Gordes Musik Yggdmillennia.

Name: Siegfried (Soul Calibur)
Key: '''Original Siegfried''' | '''Siegfried with True Soul Calibur''' | '''New Timeline'''
Summary: Siegfried had played host to Soul Calibur and, ultimately, destroyed Soul Edge. After that epic battle, the knight returned home and enjoyed a brief period of peace. But deep down he knew his work was not over; the cursed sword's minions—the malfested—remained a serious threat. Realizing he couldn't stop them alone, Siegfried gathered his staunchest allies from his old clan known as Schwarzwind, he reformed the clan of thieves into a clan of mercenaries.

Name: Silver Crystal (Sailor Moon)
Summary: The Silver Crystal (幻の銀水晶, Maboroshi no Ginzuishou; often translated as "the Illusionary Silver Crystal"), was a crystalline object of great and immeasurable power.it is the center of the plot of the Manga Sailor Moon, because of its power, All the Antagonist of the manga have tried to Get it in vain, It was used by Queen Serenity and Usagi. there are variant of the Silver Crystal like the Millennium Crystal which is a palace formed by the Silver Crystal when Usagi becomes queen in the future.

Name: Sir Grodus
Summary: Sir Grodus is the secondary antagonist of Paper Mario: The Thousand Year Door. He is the leader of the X-Nauts, an evil organization who wants to summon the Shadow Queen via the ancient crystal stars so they could conquer the world. While Grodus succeeds in summoning the Shadow Queen, the Shadow Queen rejects him and blasts him away with only his head remaining. Grodus has since reformed, last seen with some X-Nauts and Lord Crump.

Name: Skids (IDW)
Summary: Before the war, Skids of Nova Cronum trained as a theoretician at Senator Shockwave's Academy of Advanced Technology, secretly recruited to the school because of his status as an "outlier" with special powers—in Skids's case, a "super-learning" ability that allowed him to master many skills.

Name: Smithy
Summary: Smithy is the main antagonist and final boss of Super Mario RPG: Legend of the Seven Stars and leader of the Smithy Gang, an organization that attempts to rule over Mario's World during the events of the game.

Name: Smoker (One Piece)
Summary: Smoker is a tough Marine, who, when first introduced, was tasked with catching pirates that visited Loguetown before sailing for the Grand Line.

Name: Smolder the Dragon
Summary: Smolder is a supporting character from My Little Pony: FiM.

Name: Sophitia Alexandra
Summary: Sophitia Alexandra is a major character of the Soul Calibur series. She serves as the main protagonist of the original Soul Blade and is usually a major character working behind the scenes in later Soul Calibur titles. She was sent by the Greek God of Fire and forging Hephaestus in order to destroy Soul Edge and was granted to Omega Blade and Elk Shield in order to do so. She is credited with being the one to shatter Soul Edge during her fight with Cervantes.

Name: Sorahiko Torino (Gran Torino)
Summary: Sorahiko Torino (酉野空彦 Torino Sorahiko), also known by his hero name Gran Torino (グラントリノ Guran Torino), is a retired Pro Hero, formerly a homeroom teacher at U.A. High School, and a mentor to Toshinori Yagi and Izuku Midoriya.

Name: Soul Edge
Summary: Soul Edge also known as the Cursed Sword serves as the main weapon of Nightmare and overall the main antagonist of the entire Soulcalibur franchise. Soul Edge serves as the catalyst on basically all the events in the franchise. All Soul Edge cares for is the devouring of souls and pure destruction. It's release of the Evil Seed corrupted countless people across the world, driving them mad or even transforming them into monsters. Soul Edge's counterpart is Soul Calibur. Soul Edge is known to be able to shape shift in order to morph into a form that best fits its wielder.

Name: Soundwave (Devastation)
Summary: Soundwave is Megatron's loyal communications officer. At all times, he is with his five Minicons: Buzzsaw, Laserbeak, Rumble, Ravage, and Frenzy.

Name: Soundwave (IDW)
Summary: An outlier with extremely powerful hearing and limited telepathic capabilities, Soundwave's unusual powers made him a freak and an outcast in the stifling days of functionist Cybertron. But after finding a mentor in Ravage, Soundwave's aspirations saw him join up with Megatron's Decepticon movement, dreaming of a Cybertron where every Cybertronian could stand as true equals.

Name: Spartacus (Fate)
Summary: Berserker of "Red" is the Berserker-class Servant of the Red Faction in the Great Holy Grail War of Fate/Apocrypha. It is unknown which of the five puppet Masters of the Red Faction first summoned him, and unlike the rest who eventually become the Servants of Shirou Kotomine, he forms a contract with Caster of Black when captured by the Black Faction.

Name: Speed-o'-Sound Sonic
Summary: Speed-o'-Sound Sonic (音速のソニック Onsoku no Sonikku) is a villain in the series, first appearing as a bodyguard hired by Mr. Monier. He grew up in a ninja village, honing his skills to near perfection. He views Saitama as his eternal rival, ever since the hero "defeated" him in a rather embarrassing manner.

Name: Spewart
Summary: Spewart is Broodal, a rabbit-like species that originated from the moon, one of the wedding planners hired by Bowser to deal with Mario and steal some of the world's most prized possessions, and an entertainer, whose poison spitting abilities are described as artistic.

Name: Spike the Dragon
Key: '''Baby Dragon Form''' | '''Equestria Girls Dog Form''' | '''Adult Dragon Form ''' | '''Post Puberty'''
Summary: Spike the Dragon is a protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Star Rod (Paper Mario)
Summary: The Star Rod is a magical artifact from Paper Mario. Made with ancient magic,[1] it has been guarded by the seven Star Spirits at the sanctuary of Star Haven since the beginning of time.[2] During the events of the game, Paper Bowser invades Star Haven, steals the Star Rod, and captures the Star Spirits, leaving each under the guard of one of his followers. The next day, he lifts Paper Princess Peach's castle high up into the sky atop his own castle and empowers himself with the Star Rod to such a degree that Paper Mario is unable to damage him, being quickly defeated and blasted out of the castle. Once Paper Mario rescues the seven Star Spirits, he returns to Paper Princess Peach's castle and rematches Paper Bowser, being able to overpower the latter's invulnerability with the Star Spirits' Star Beam. Paper Bowser retreats to a platform built by Kammy Koopa to power him up even further, to the point of being unaffected by the Star Beam. However, the combined strength of Twink and the wishes of the entire Mushroom Kingdom upgrade the Star Beam into the Peach Beam, with which Paper Mario is able to defeat Paper Bowser and reclaim the Star Rod, which the Star Spirits return to Star Haven.

Name: Subspace Army
Summary: The Subspace Army is an organization hailing from Subspace led by Tabuu. It is the main antagonistic force of the Subspace Emissary, acting as the source behind most threats faced by the heroes. Its goal is the absorption of the World of Trophy into Subspace, done by the usage of Subspace Bombs. As Tabuu cannot leave Subspace, most of the forces are located in the World of Trophy while Tabuu manipulates them from Subspace. Those include the Isle of the Ancients, the Halberd (Piloted by Mr. Game & Watch) and the Koopa Troop. Most relations within the army are quite fragile, however, as a lot of them are done either through force or trickery. Notably, almost no one knows the existence of Tabuu, as the latter hides behind Master Hand to communicate his orders to his commanders.

Name: Subspace Bomb
Summary: The Subspace Bomb is a powerful weapon used in the Super Smash Bros. story mode. A large portion of the game is set to keep them from being set.

Name: Sung Jin-Woo (Novel)
Summary: nan

Name: Sunset Shimmer
Key: '''Human''' | '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Element of Magic (Demon Form)''' | '''Pony-Up Form''' | '''Daydream Shimmer'''
Summary: Sunset Shimmer is a reformed villain from My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Superalloy Darkshine
Summary: Superalloy Darkshine (超ちょう合ごう金きんクロビカリ, Chōgōkin Kurobikari?) is the Rank 11 S-Class hero of One-Punch Man. He is among the strongest heroes in the Hero Association and one of the few capable of fighting Dragon-level threats.

Name: Surume (One Piece)
Summary: Surume is a kraken which dwells in the deepest parts of the ocean, and was enslaved by the New Fishman Pirates, but later became Luffy's pet. Luffy was the one who gave Surume his name.

Name: Suì-Fēng
Summary: Suì-Fēng (砕蜂 (ソイフォン), Soifon) is the commander-in-chief of the Onmitsukidō and the captain of the 2nd Division in the Gotei 13. Her lieutenant is Marechiyo Ōmaeda. She boasts one of the highest speeds as a captain and is pretty deadly in close combat.

Name: Sword Knight
Summary: Sword Knight is a character portrayed as a swordsman and knight featured in the Kirby series. In most cases, he's seen as an enemy, but in other cases, he's shown to be a temporary acquaintance, like a helper.

Name: Szayelaporro Granz
Summary: Szayelaporro Granz (ザエルアポロ・グランツ, Zaeruaporo Gurantsu?) is the 8th Espada of Sosuke Aizen's army and the younger brother of Yylfordt Granz, the 15th Arrancar, and one of Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez's Fracción. As an Espada, the aspect of death he symbolizes is madness.

Name: T-Rex (Mario Bros)
Summary: T-Rex, short for "Tyrannosaurus rex", is an extinct dinosaur species in real life. Within the Super Mario franchise, the T-Rex is shown to be the ancestor of President Koopa in the 1993 Super Mario Bros. film. Members of this species notably appear in Super Mario Odyssey as enemies that can be captured by Cappy, being alternatively nicknamed "Prehistoric Tyrants" and occasionally referred to simply as "dinosaurs."

Name: Tabuu
Summary: Tabuu is the leader of the Subspace Army, the main antagonist and final boss of Super Smash Bros. Brawls Adventure Mode: The Subspace Emissary. He is a powerful, supernatural entity who resides in Subspace. He uses the Subspace Bombs to send entire locations to his dimension, where he absorbs their power to increase his own.

Name: Taki
Summary: Taki is a fictional character designed for the Soul series of fighting games, making her debut in the first game of the series, Soul Edge (Soul Blade). She has thus far appeared in all the following games with the exception of Soulcalibur V, in which she was replaced by her student Natsu, who is now searching for her master.

Name: Talim
Summary: Talim is nicknamed The Last Priestess of the Winds, and true to that nickname, has the power to sway the wind and relies on earth's nature to guide her in her adventures, and most importantly in battle. She fights with dual Elbow Blades, and as said earlier, uses her advantage of wind control to give her an unpredictable edge during combat, being able to hop around and over the opponent at any moment.

Name: Tamago
Summary: Baron Tamago is a combatant of the Big Mom Pirates, who originates from the Longleg Tribe. He and his partner Pekoms are responsible for collecting the monthly payment of sweets from Fishman Island in exchange for Big Mom's protection.

Name: Tamaki Amajiki (Suneater)
Summary: Tamaki Amajiki (天喰 環 Amajiki Tamaki), also known as Suneater (サンイーター San'ītā), is a recently graduated hero from U.A. High School and a former member of the Big 3.

Name: Tartaronis
Summary: Tartaronis is an Elder Dragon, first introduced in Monster Hunter Online.

Name: Tashigi
Summary: Tashigi was first introduced when the Straw Hat Pirates docked in Loguetown, where she was stationed. Smoker, her superior officer, seems to regard her as a protege; the two work very well together.

Name: Tatsumaki (Tornado of Terror)
Summary: Tatsumaki (戦慄のタツマキ, Senritsu no Tatsumaki) also known as Tornado of Terror is the S-Class Rank 2 superhero, an esper and the older sister of Fubuki. Tatsumaki is one of the most powerful heroes in the entire Hero Association and is treated as one of their ultimate weapons to be used as a last resort. Despite her young appearance, she is an incredibly skilled and powerful esper. Her personality, on the other hand, can be incredibly childish, and she is fully willing to throw her power around to get her way, or when someone annoys her.

Name: Teostra
Summary: Teostra are Elder Dragons introduced in Monster Hunter 2.

Name: Terry Bogard (The King of Fighters)
Key: '''Prologue Chapter (KOF '94) ''' | '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '95 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of NESTS Saga (KOF '99 to KOF 2001)''' | '''KOF Sky Stage''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Tesra Lindocruz
Summary: Tesra Lindocruz (テスラ·リンドクルツ, Tesura Rindokurutsu; Viz: Tesla Lindocruz) is the 50th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and Nnoitra Gilga's only Fracción.

Name: The Admiral
Summary: The Admiral is one of the members of the First Fleet of the research commission, who ventured to the New World to colonize it and discover the mystery of the Elder Crossing. In this, The Admiral dedicated himself to exploring the locale, finding the Elder's Recess and tracking down Nergigante.

Name: The Hunter (Monster Hunter)
Summary: Hunters are the playable avatar of the Monster Hunter series.

Name: The Mean Six
Summary: The Mean Six are the main antagonists of the MLP: FiM episode of the same name. They are clones of the Mane Six created by Queen Chrysalis before they end up turning against her.

Name: The Storm King
Summary: The Storm King is the main antagonist of the My Little Pony Movie.

Name: Tier Harribel
Summary: Tier Harribel (ティア・ハリベル, Tia Hariberu?) is the 3rd Espada of Sosuke Aizen's army, and, following his defeat, the ruler of Hueco Mundo. As an Espada, the aspect of death she symbolizes is sacrifice.

Name: Tigrex
Summary: Tigrex are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom 2.

Name: Tira
Summary: Tira is a major antagonist from the Soulcalibur franchise and first appeared in Soulcalibur lll. Tira serves as by far the most faithful servant of Soul Edge and does anything to find suitable hosts for Soul Edge while helping it gather souls. Tira is a former member of the "Birds of Passage" assassin organization and is known as the "Bird of Death". One of Tira's most notable traits is the fact that she has a split personality.

Name: Titan (Final Fantasy)
Key: '''Final Fantasy IV''' | '''Final Fantasy IV: The After Years/Final Fantasy XIV''' | '''Final Fantasy V'''
Summary: Titan is a recurring summon in Final Fantasy. Befitting of his name, Titan is often portrayed as being a giant in comparison to the other characters, striking them with powerful earth-based moves. His personality varies across his appearances, but he is consistently depicted has having monstrous physical strength.

Name: Toad (Mario)
Summary: Toad is a recurring character in the Mario series, who usually reprises as a stewart of Princess Peach. He usually has the role of a supporting character who tries to help Mario and Luigi on their adventures, although he occasionally has been as a main protagonist, such as in Super Mario Bros. 2 and Wario's Woods. He is usually happy, polite, and can be benevolent to a fault as his species can be frightened easily whenever a crisis arise.

Name: Toadette
Summary: Tier: High 6-A, far higher with certain power-ups and equipment

Name: Todd Ingram
Summary: Todd Ingram is Ramona Flowers's third ex-boyfriend. He is in a relationship with Envy Adams (cheating on Envy with Lynette Guycott) and the bass player for The Clash at Demonhead. He is also a Vegan, though known to cheat on both his vegan diet as well as his girlfriend, believing he can get away with mostly anything because he's a rock star.

Name: Toichiro Suzuki
Summary: Toichiro Suzuki is a major antagonist in the Mob Psycho 100 anime and manga series. He is the leader of the worldwide organization of Espers, Claw, and uses his army of psychic individuals to attempt to take control over the governments of the world. In reality, though, Toichiro only uses this to make some sort of mark on the world. even if it means causing mass destruction with no real end-goal.

Name: Tokinada Tsunayashiro
Summary: If the world is so unscrupulous, then should I not be unscrupulous too?

Name: Tomura Shigaraki (Post-Surgery)
Summary: Tomura Shigaraki (死柄木 弔 Shigaraki Tomura), original name Tenko Shimura (志村転弧 Shimura Tenko), was the protégé of All For One and the leader of the League of Villains. A dangerously unstable individual who looks up to his "Sensei" with the utmost awe and respect, Shigaraki plans on tearing down the society of heroes built up by All Might by any means necessary. His organization and the Meta Liberation Army later merged to create the Paranormal Liberation Front, and he became its Grand Commander.

Name: Tony Tony Chopper
Key: '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Tony Tony Chopper serves as the ship's doctor. He's a reindeer who was cast out of his herd for having a blue nose, later compounded by eating the Human-Human Fruit (Hito Hito no Mi) and being feared by the people of Drum Island as a monster. Although he initially mistrusted humans, after having met and joined the Straw Hats, he has become very curious about the world and is eager to please.

Name: Topper
Summary: Topper is the first boss you encounter in Super Mario Odyssey, and the leader of the Broodals (Although Madame Broode is their boss). He and his gang had struck a deal with Bowser to help plan Peach's wedding and stop Mario. His main method of attack is using hats to attack his opponents.

Name: Tori Hanson
Summary: Tori Hanson is the Blue Wind Ranger and is the first female Blue Power Ranger, in the show's history.

Name: Toshinori Yagi (All Might)
Summary: Toshinori Yagi (八木俊典 Yagi Toshinori), most commonly known as All Might (オールマイト Ōru Maito), is the former No. 1 Hero who bore the title of the world's Symbol of Peace and inspired a whole generation of heroes, including Izuku Midoriya, whom he passed the torch of One For All to. He teaches Foundational Hero Studies at U.A. High School.

Name: Trafalgar Law
Summary: Trafalgar D. Water Law is the captain of the Heart Pirates and one of the eleven pirates dubbed with the moniker "Supernova". He's a very laid-back person, and while his speech is very polite, he has no problem with taking mocking jabs at people or giving them the middle finger.

Name: Trebol
Summary: Probably one of the most impacting of the Donquixote Family's three Top Executives, Trebol has taken a huge part regarding the development of Donquixote Doflamingo's rise to power.

Name: Trunkle
Summary: Trunkle is a boss in Mario & Luigi: Superstar Saga and its remake. Blocking the entrance to Little Fungitown and intimidating its Toads, it is eventually battled and defeated by Mario and Luigi after it attacks Princess Peach.

Name: Tsunagu Hakamada (Best Jeanist)
Summary: Tsunagu Hakamata (袴田はかまだ維つなぐ Hakamata Tsunagu), also known as Fiber Hero: Best Jeanist (ファイバーヒーロー ベストジー二スト Faibā Hīrō Besuto Jīnisuto), is the formerly No. 4, now No. 3 Pro Hero and recipient of the "Best Jeanist" award for eight consecutive years.

Name: Twilight Sparkle (Pony World)
Key: '''Unicorn Form''' | '''Alicorn Form''' | '''The Ending of the End Alicorn Form''' | '''Elements of Harmony/Magic of Friendship''' | '''All Alicorn Magic''' | '''Post-Timeskip Alicorn Form''' | '''Rainbow Power''' | '''Equestria Girls Human form'''
Summary: Twilight Sparkle is the main protagonist of My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic.

Name: Tōshirō Hitsugaya
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Early Arrancar Arc''' | '''Late Arrancar Arc''' | '''Post-Timeskip''' | '''Post-Training''' | '''Matured Bankai'''
Summary: Toshiro Hitsugaya (日ひ番つが谷や 冬とう獅し郎ろう, Hitsugaya Tōshirō?) is the captain of the 10th Division in the Gotei 13. His lieutenant is Rangiku Matsumoto. He formerly served as the 3rd Seat of the 10th Division under Isshin Shiba.

Name: Ukanlos
Summary: Ukanlos are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom Unite.

Name: Ulquiorra Cifer
Summary: I envy because of the heart

Name: Ulti (One Piece)
Summary: Ulti is one of the Tobiroppo, the six strongest Headliners of the Beasts Pirates. and is the older sister of Page One.

Name: Unknown (Monster Hunter)
Summary: Unknown is a species of Flying Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Forward.1.

Name: Urouge
Summary: Urouge, also known as Mad Monk, is a pirate who hails from a sky island and is the captain of the Fallen Monk Pirates. He is one of twelve pirates who are referred to as the "Worst Generation " (formerly known as the "Eleven Supernovas"). and prior to the two-year timeskip had a bounty of 108,000,000.

Name: Uryū Ishida
Summary: Uryu Ishida (石いし田だ 雨う竜りゅう, Ishida Uryū?) is a Gemischt Quincy residing in Karakura Town. He is a doctor at Karakura Hospital, and a friend of Ichigo Kurosaki. He is also a former member of the Wandenreich with the designation "A" - "Antithesis", one of Yhwach's "Schutzstaffel" (親衛隊シュッツシュタッフェル, Shuttsushutafferu?), and his future successor.

Name: Ushoda Hachigen
Summary: Hachigen Ushōda (有昭田 鉢玄, Ushōda Hachigen) is a Visored, formerly the lieutenant of the Kidō Corps under Tessai Tsukabishi. He is usually referred to as Hacchi (ハッチ; sometimes translated as "Hutch").

Name: Usopp
Key: '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Water 7 Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Usopp serves as the crew's sharpshooter and previously served as the (barely competent) repairman for the ship. He's the son of Yasopp, a sharpshooter serving under Shanks, and comes from the East Blue. Usopp had a reputation on his home island of being a serial liar who claimed that pirates were attacking, which came back to haunt him when real pirates actually attacked. He's a rather boastful seventeen/nineteen-year-old who likes to tell tall tales (several of which actually do come true, after a fashion), though he's more prone to hiding behind the stronger crew members such as Zoro when he actually gets into a fight. However, when push comes to shove, he is very dependable. He specializes in the use of a slingshot, called the Galaxy Slingshot (Ginga Pachinko), which he replaced with the Kabuto and later the Black Kabuto. This slingshot, coupled with his talent in tricking enemies, and his absurd sniping skills, make him a redoubtable sniper able to intervene at a very long range.

Name: Vaal Hazak
Summary: Vaal Hazak is an Elder Dragon first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Valdo Gollini (Dark Might)
Summary: Valdo Gollini (バルド・ゴリーニ Barudo Gorīni), also known as Dark Might (ダークマイト Dākumaito), is the main antagonist of My Hero Academia: You're Next. He is the leader of the Gollini Family mafia.[1]

Name: Valstrax
Summary: Crimson Glow Valstrax are Elder Dragons introduced in Monster Hunter Rise.

Name: Velkhana
Summary: Velkhana, also known as the Ice Dragon or the Iceborne Wyvern, is a powerful and elegant Elder Dragon capable of controlling the cold via its icy breath and armor forged out of crystallized water vapor from the air. It is an exceptionally dangerous, but reclusive, monster that is known to most as just a fairy tale, but its ability to freeze large monsters solid in mere moments with its breath is no myth. It was first introduced in Monster Hunter World: Iceborne as its flagship monster.

Name: Vergo
Summary: Vergo is one of the four High Executives of the Donquixote Pirates and a Marine Vice Admiral.

Name: Vincent Valentine
Summary: nan

Name: Vinsmoke Ichiji
Summary: "Sparking Red" Vinsmoke Ichiji is the eldest son of the Vinsmoke Famiy, making him both a prince of the Germa Kingdom and a commander in its military arm, Germa 66.

Name: Vinsmoke Judge
Summary: Vinsmoke Judge, also known as Garuda, is the king of the Germa Kingdom, the supreme commander of the Germa 66, and the patriarch of the Vinsmoke Family. He is also a skilled scientist, and a former research partner to the leading World Government scientist Vegapunk.

Name: Vinsmoke Niji
Summary: Electric Blue Vinsmoke Niji is the 2nd son of the Vinsmoke Family. Like the rest of his family, he is proud of his royal status and does not care for his servants.

Name: Vinsmoke Reiju
Summary: "Poison Pink" Vinsmoke Reiju is the eldest child and only daughter of the Vinsmoke Family, making her both the princess of the Germa Kingdom and a commander in its military arm, Germa 66.

Name: Vinsmoke Yonji
Summary: "Winch Green" Vinsmoke Yonji is the fourth son and youngest child of the Vinsmoke Family, making him both a prince of the Germa Kingdom and a commander in its military arm, Germa 66.

Name: Vivian (Paper Mario)
Summary: Vivian was originally a villain working with the Shadow Sirens with her sisters. She was often put down by her oldest sister until she met a shadow Mario and decided to help him get his body back when he helped her out. Once realizing the shadow she was helping was Mario, she fled as she was sent to capture him. She later comes back and helps Mario, leaving her sisters and helps him in finding all the Crystal Stars.

Name: Vlad III (Lancer of Black)
Summary: nan

Name: Voldo
Summary: Born in 16th century Italy, Voldo was a servant of the weapons merchant Vercci. Known as the Merchant of Death due to his business with the Spanish Armada, Vercci desired the Soul Edge for his collection and had Voldo to attempt expeditions with Cervantes de Leon. When Vercci heard that his possessions have been ransacked as a result of civil war in Italy, he had his personal fleet travel to an uninhabited island off the coast of Sicily in the Mediterranean Sea and dug a 50-mt deep shaft that would serve as his tomb and as a vault for his remaining fortune. After killing off the sailors under Vercci's orders, Voldo becomes the guardian of the Money Pit. But he would emerge from the Money Pit, either to continue the search for the Soul Edge or hunt down thieves that steal from the vault in his absence.

Name: Wadatsumi
Summary: Wadatsumi is a giant tiger blowfish fish-man and a member of the Sun Pirates. He was formerly a member of the Flying Pirates under captain Vander Decken IX before they were defeated.

Name: Waluigi
Summary: Waluigi (Japanese: ワルイージ, Waruīji) is Luigi's very tall and skinny rival and Wario's partner. Waluigi made his debut in Mario Tennis, and since then, he has made playable appearances in many of the Mario series' spin-off titles. He has been voiced by Charles Martinet ever since his debut. His name is a portmanteau of the Japanese words, Warui and Ruīji, meaning "bad" and "Luigi". In addition, his name is an anagram to the Japanese word Ijiwaru, which can mean "ill-tempered" or "cruel".

Name: Waluigi (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Waluigi is a Mario Bros. Character that can spawn from a Assist Trophy in Super Smash Bros.

Name: Wario
Summary: Wario (Japanese: ワリオ, Wario) is a recurring character in the Mario series. He is an obese, muscular, hot-tempered, and greedy man, and Mario's yellow-and-purple clad arch-rival. He usually appears as an antagonist, or in some cases an anti-hero. His name is a combination of Mario's name and the Japanese word warui (悪い), meaning "bad". Wario's greed pushes him to commit malevolent acts, such as the seizing of Mario's castle. Wario has also proven to be very cunning as he has tricked Mario on many occasions. He often goes out on his own adventures, from stealing treasure to running a microgame making company. Wario has helped heroes of the Mushroom Kingdom on a few separate occasions as well.

Name: Watt (Paper Mario)
Summary: Watt is one of Paper Mario's partners during his quest to defeat Paper Bowser. Watt was kidnapped by a Big Lantern Ghost and used inside a lantern, but was released by Paper Mario. She accompanies him through the rest of the game, using her ability to light dark places.

Name: Wendy O. Koopa
Summary: Wendy O. Koopa is one of the members of a clan composed of elite warrior siblings known as the Koopalings and the sole female of the family. She had always taken high delight in her femininity, shown to be elegant via her emphasis on skating, swimming, and aquatic combat and has an arrogant and vain demeanor with difficulty in admitting defeat, likely due to her high ranking position or said feminine qualities mentioned earlier. Despite this, she has shown to be tough with tomboyish qualities as well. Like most of the Koopalings, she is named after a famous musician. She's named after the songwriter, actress, lead singer of the punk rock band Plasmatics, Wendy Orlean Williams.

Name: White (Bleach)
Summary: White is an artificial Hollow created by Sosuke Aizen using the souls of Shinigami killed over the course of his research.

Name: Who's-Who
Summary: Who's-Who is one of the Tobiroppo, the strongest six Shinuchi of the Beasts Pirates.

Name: Wii Fit Trainer (Smash Bros.)
Summary: Wii Fit Trainer is a fighter in the Super Smash Bros. series originating from the popular Wii game Wii Fit. Wii Fit Trainer's moveset takes heavy inspiration from Wii Fit, with his/her fighting style being based on various acrobatic moves and fitness equipment. Wii Fit Trainer is often portrayed as female, but can be swapped out for a male version

Name: William Shakespeare (Fate)
Summary: Caster of "Red" is the Caster-class Servant of the Red Faction in the Great Holy Grail War. While he is originally summoned by Jean Rum, he later becomes one of the Servants of Shirou Kotomine.

Name: Wind Serpent Ibushi
Summary: Wind Serpent Ibushi, also known as the Wind God Dragon, is a graceful azure Elder Dragon that spends its life high up in the atmosphere using special organs called "windsacs" across its body. It possesses great control over the wind and flight, able to create immense windstorms and move freely while twirling its body or while upside down without disorientation, giving it a divine, otherworldly mien. Its mate is Thunder Serpent Narwa. It was first introduced in Monster Hunter Rise.

Name: Wolfram (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Wolfram is a greedy and manipulative villain who will crush anything or anyone to get what he wants. He lusts for money and works as the leader of a company of thieves. They even posed as fake villains for hire to gain David Shield's trust just so they could steal his invention.

Name: Wonderweiss Margela
Summary: Wonderweiss Margela (ワンダーワイス・マルジェラ, Wandāwaisu Marujera) is the 77th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and the only modified Arrancar under Aizen's command. Though not an actual Espada, Soul Society ranks his Spiritual Energy in the same class as theirs.

Name: X Drake
Summary: X Drake (read as "Diez Drake") is a former Marine rear admiral from North Blue who has become a pirate under the epithet of the "Red Flag". He is one of twelve pirates referred to as the "Worst Generation" (formerly as the "Eleven Supernovas"), and prior to the two-year timeskip had a bounty of 222,000,000.

Name: X-66
Summary: The X-66 is a single seat, combat-oriented aircraft developed by the U.S. military forces with the purpose of assisting Star and Stripe in her missions, acting as a transport and collector of information during mid-air battles.

Name: Xeno'Jiiva
Summary: Tier: At least Low 6-B | At least Low 6-B, higher with Sapphire of the Emperor

Name: Xianghua
Summary: Chai Xianghua is a major character of the Soulcalibur series. She serves as the main heroine of Soulcalibur alongside Kilik and Maxi. She is a member of the Imperial Guard and is the chosen wielder of Soul Calibur (before Siegfried and later Patroklos) and aided Kilik in defeating Nightmare.

Name: Xiba
Summary: Xiba is a character that appears in Soul Calibur V. He is the student of Edge Master and son of both Kilik and Xianghua and the half brother of Leixia. He is on a quest to inherit the Kali-Yuga from Kilik and is followed by Leixia, Natsu and Maxi.

Name: Yama Tsukami
Summary: Yama Tsukami is an Elder Dragon introduced in Monster Hunter 2.

Name: Yamame Kurodani
Summary: Yamame Kurodani (黒谷 ヤマメ) is a tsuchigumo - an earth spider, that lives in the entrance to the Underworld.

Name: Yamato (One Piece)
Summary: Yamato (ヤマト?) is the child of Kaidou, one of the Four Emperors of the Sea. Groomed from a young age to be his heir, Yamato instead developed a profound admiration for the samurai Kozuki Oden. After his death, Yamato chose to become Oden, and adopted his mannerisms. This path has put Yamato at odds with Kaidou, with much of his life being spent imprisoned on Onigashima. Yamato befriended Portgas D. Ace during his visit to Wano, and after learning of Ace's death waited for the arrival of his sworn brother, Monkey D. Luffy. Together with Luffy and the Ninja-Pirate-Mink-Samurai Alliance, Yamato helped to defeat Kaidou and the Beasts Pirates.

Name: Yammy Llargo
Summary: Yammy Llargo (ヤミー・リヤルゴ, Yamī Riyarugo?) is an Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army. While he initially appeared to bear the rank of Arrancar Diez (10), Yammy is actually the Cero (0) Espada and thus the most powerful of the Espada.

Name: Yasutora Sado (Chad)
Key: '''Substitute Shinigami Arc''' | '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Lost Agent Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Yasutora Sado (茶渡 泰虎, Sado Yasutora), also known as Chad (チャド, Chado) is a human teenager who lives in Karakura Town. He is a student at Karakura High School, where he is in the same class as Ichigo Kurosaki.

Name: Yatsuhashi Tsukumo
Summary: Yatsuhashi Tsukumo is one of the Tsukumogami sister. She was transformed into a Youkai from a simple tool due to the Miracle Mallet's magical powers.

Name: Yoruichi Shihoin
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Early Arrancar Arc''' | '''Late Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Yoruichi Shihōin (四楓院 夜一, Shihōin Yoruichi) is the former captain of the 2nd Division of the Gotei 13, as well as the former commander of the Onmitsukido. Her lieutenant was Marenoshin Omaeda. Having abandoned her command of both positions, she works with Kisuke Urahara and Tessai Tsukabishi, based in the Urahara Shop out in the Human World.

Name: Yoshi
Summary: Yoshi (Japanese: ヨッシー, Yosshī, sometimes specified as Green Yoshi) is one of the heroes of the Mario series, an ally of Mario and Luigi, and the protagonist of his own series. He is a member of the Yoshi species and has aided his brethren in saving their homeland on multiple occasions. In his youth, Yoshi managed to rescue and protect Baby Mario and Baby Luigi from the wrath of Kamek and the Koopa Troop. According to Super Mario RPG: Legend of the Seven Stars, Yoshi is one of the few members of his species who can speak the language of the other characters, though it seems that this is not his first language, since, as in other games, his statements are translated through parentheses. In the Mario series, he is a major character and often acts as a steed for Mario and other protagonists, while in most of the Mario sports and party games, he is a playable character.

Name: Yoshimitsu (Soulcalibur)
Summary: Yoshimitsu is a reoccurring character in the Soul Calibur franchise. He is the leader of the Manji clan and is a thief who gives back to the least fortunate. After his Manji Clan was killed by Oda Nobunaga. Due to this, he is searching out Soul Edge in order to exact his revenge. It is implied that Yoshimitsu is the ancestor of the same Yoshimitsu from the Tekken series.

Name: Yu Takeyama (Mount Lady)
Summary: Yu Takeyama (岳山優 Takeyama Yū), better known by her hero alias Mount Lady (Mt. レディ Maunto Redī), is a relatively new Pro Hero. She's in the business for fame and fortune, quickly becoming popular for her flirtatious nature and the raw power her Gigantification Quirk provides, but is nevertheless a kind person at heart. She is the No. 23 Pro Hero.

Name: Yumichika Ayasegawa
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Early Arrancar Arc''' | '''Late Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War'''
Summary: Yumichika Ayasegawa (綾あや瀬せ川がわ 弓ゆみ親ちか, Ayasegawa Yumichika?) is the 3rd Seat officer and former 5th Seat officer in the 11th Division of the Gotei 13, under Captain Kenpachi Zaraki.

Name: Yun-Seong
Summary: Hong Yun-Seong is a character from the Soul series first appearing in Soul Calibur ll. He is an energetic, prideful and strong young warrior who is searching for Soul Edge. He serves as the successor of Hwang from Soul Blade and Soul Calibur. Idolizing Hwang as a child and a goal to surpass, Yun-Seong is searching for Soul Edge to gain power so that Hwang would see him as a true opponent and fight him.

Name: Yylfordt Granz
Summary: Yylfordt Granz (イールフォルト・グランツ, Īruforuto Gurantsu) is Arrancar Quince (15) in Sōsuke Aizen's army and one of Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez's five Fracción. He is the older brother of Szayelaporro Granz, the 8th Espada.

Name: Yūshirō Shihōin
Summary: Yūshirō Sakimune Shihōin (四楓院 夕四郎 咲宗, Shihōin Yūshirō Sakimune) is the 23rd head of the Shihōin Clan and the guardian of its sacred armor.

Name: Zasalamel
Summary: Zasalamel is a character in the Soul series of fighting games, a man with no allegiances except to himself, though some of his actions may reasonably be defined as evil.

Name: Zelda (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Zelda (ゼルダ, Zelda), is a playable character in the Super Smash Bros. series. For each generation of Hyrule, there has been a distinct incarnation of Zelda serving as its crown princess, as seen throughout The Legend of Zelda timeline. Similarly, her Super Smash Bros. counterpart has also cycled through different incarnations across the series, resembling her canon self in Ocarina of Time, Twilight Princess and A Link to the Past.

Name: Zephyr (One Piece)
Summary: "Black Arm" Zephyr, also known as Z, was the leader of the Neo Marines and the main antagonist of One Piece Film: Z. He was once a Marine admiral and instructor before his resignation.

Name: Zinogre
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | High 8-C | High 6-C | 7-B

Name: Zommari Rureaux
Summary: Zommari Rureaux (ゾマリ・ルルー, Zomari Rurū) is an Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army, and the Séptima (7th) Espada.

Name: Zorah Magdaros
Summary: In-Game Description: An Elder Dragon that rides from the earth like a volcano. Where it is headed, and why, the Research Commission has yet to figure out.

Name: Zunesha
Summary: Zunesha is a colossal, sentient elephant that carries the entire country of Zou on its back. In the ancient past, Zunesha was sentenced to walk the seas for eternity and only act upon being ordered to do so for committing an unspecified crime. Since then, it has wandered the sea of the New World and lived for centuries carrying the Mink Tribe and the other lifeforms on Zou. The elephant comes from an unusual species with multi-jointed legs that are incredibly long and reach far down into the ocean floor.

Name: AC-3 White Heron
Summary: The AC-3 White Heron (-しらさぎ) is a support vehicle used by the JSDF which first appeared in the 2002 Godzilla film, Godzilla Against Mechagodzilla.

Name: Akane Yashiro (Kiryu Saga)
Key: '''Akane Yashiro''' | '''Piloting Maser Cannon''' | '''Piloting AC-3 White Heron''' | '''Piloting Kiryu'''
Summary: Akane Yashiro (家城茜) is the human protagonist of the 2002 Toho Godzilla film Godzilla Against Mechagodzilla, also appearing in a minor role in its 2003 sequel Godzilla: Tokyo SOS. First Lieutenant Akane Yashiro A Type 90 Maser Cannon operator for the JSDF's Anti-Megalosaurus Force, Akane unintentionally caused the death of her comrades in a battle against Godzilla in 1999. Subsequently reassigned to a desk job, Akane was recruited to become a pilot for the Kiryu Squad in 2003, receiving the rank of Second Lieutenant. A member of the Kiryu team and the pilot of Kiryu Type-3. She is an excellent operator, but as the only member without relatives, she can be a bit awkward due to not being good at reading the feelings of others. Despite the odds against her, Akane earned the respect of her squad and played a key role in the battle between Kiryu and Godzilla in Tokyo. By 2004, she had been promoted to First Lieutenant and sought further training in the United States.

Name: All For One
Summary: All For One (オール・フォー・ワン Ōru Fō Wan) is the true leader and benefactor of the League of Villains who bears the title of the world's Symbol of Evil, the primary antagonist of the Hideout Raid Arc and the central antagonist of the series, along with Tomura Shigaraki.

Name: Arcee (IDW)
Summary: An ancient warrior from the dawn of Cybertronian history, sibling to the equally powerful warrior Galvatron, Arcee arose from the ashes of her mysterious, traumatic past to become one of the most feared Transformers of her era and beyond. Cold and detached off the battlefield and utterly ruthless in combat, Arcee's single-minded bloodlust put her at odds with both the Autobots and Decepticons for most of the Great War.

Name: As Nodt
Summary: Äs Nödt (エス・ノト, Esu Noto?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "F" - "The Fear".

Name: Askin Nakk Le Vaar
Summary: Askin Nakk Le Vaar (アスキン・ナックルヴァール, Asukin Nakkuruvāru?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "D" - "The Deathdealing", as well as one of Yhwach's Schutzstaffel (親衛隊シュッツシュタッフェル, Shuttsushutafferu?) German for "Protective Echelon", Japanese for "Elite/Imperial Guards".

Name: Astaroth (Soul Calibur)
Summary: Ares, the god of destruction, desired Soul Edge to dethrone his father, Zeus, so he ordered Kunpaetku, the grand priest of the cult order Fygul Cestemus, to seek it out. Astaroth, a golem, was created in hellish heat under the divine protection of Ares to head up the quest. Kunpaetku ordered his creation, Astaroth, to find the demonic blade. As he watched Astaroth depart from the shrine, the grand priest laughed to himself as he planned to keep the Soul Edge and become a god himself. Unknown to Kunpaetku, however, Ares had possessed Astaroth with his servants, the Keres, to ensure that Kunpaetku would not betray him.

Name: Bad (Metal Bat)
Summary: Bad (バッド, Baddo?), also known by his hero alias Metal Bat (金きん属ぞくバット, Kinzoku Batto?), is an S-Class hero, ranked 15 in the Hero Association. Despite his low status among the S-Class heroes, he is considered one of the strongest. Metal Bat's "Kiai" (fighting spirit) is the key to his strength; the more damage he takes, the stronger he becomes. His power grows in direct proportion to his injury and mental state, to the point where he can eventually defeat superior opponents on his own. Metal Bat typically treats both his allies and enemies badly. However, he is a kind and gentle soul to his younger sister.[1]

Name: Bahamut (Final Fantasy)
Summary: A recurring summon in the games, Bahamut is a force to be reckoned as one of the most powerful summons, if not the most powerful summon the player can acquire on their journey. He is most frequently found as part of a sidequest and is not relevant to the main plot, but in some cases he takes a much more active role, such as empowering the Warriors of Light in the original game with their job changes. His demeanor, behavior, and alignment change from appearance to appearance, but all recognize him as the King of Dragons and the Ruler of the Skies.

Name: Bambietta Basterbine
Summary: Bambietta Basterbine (バンビエッタ・バスターバイン, Banbietta Basutābain?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "E" - "The Explode".

Name: Baraggan Louisenbairn
Summary: Baraggan Louisenbairn (バラガン・ルイゼンバーン, Baragan Ruizenbān) is an Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and the Segunda (2nd) Espada.

Name: Bazz-B
Summary: Bazzard Black (バザード・ブラック, Bazādo Burakku?), more commonly known as Bazz-B (バズビー, Bazubī?), is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter, with the designation "H" - "The Heat".

Name: Beef
Summary: Beef is a member of the Best Fitness Friends and one of the main antagonists introduced in Mario & Luigi: Bowser's Inside Story + Bowser Jr's Journey.

Name: Beldam (Mario Bros)
Summary: Beldam is a notable antagonist of Paper Mario: The Thousand Year Door. She is the leader of the Shadow Sirens, a group which comprises of herself and her two sisters Marilyn and Vivian (Later Doopliss, as Vivian leaves the group and joins Mario). Beldam is an ally of the X-Nauts who want to summon the Shadow Queen, and kidnaps Peach at the beginning of the game as a vessel for the Shadow Queen. Beldam attempts to slow down Mario on his adventure, but eventually fails to do so. After the Shadow Queen is defeated, Beldam settles down in Twilight Town and reforms.

Name: Benben Tsukumo
Summary: Benben Tsukumo is one of the Tsukumogami sister. She was transformed into a Youkai from a simple tool due to the Miracle Mallet's magical powers.

Name: Benn Beckman
Summary: Benn Beckman is the first mate of the Red Hair Pirates, which is led by Shanks.

Name: Best Fitness Friends (Fusion)
Summary: Best Fitness Friends is the final boss of Bowser Jr's story in Mario & Luigi: Bowser's Inside Story + Bowser Jr's Journey.

Name: BG9
Summary: BG9 (ベー・ゲー・ノイン, Bē Gē Noin?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "K".

Name: Birdo
Summary: Birdo, Catherine (キャサリン Kyasarin), is a recurring character in the Mario series. While most commonly depicted as a single character, multiple Birdos have been seen on occasion. The central Birdo character wears a red bow and often a diamond ring. She also has some sort of relationship with Yoshi, as they are default partners in various competitions. She originally appeared as a part of the 8-Bits, an army led by Wart in the Subcon realm to thwart Mario's dreams. In later games, she would either help or hinder Mario, depending on her role in the story, and partake in various sports games.

Name: Bonetail
Summary: Bonetail is an enemy appearing in Paper Mario: The Thousand-Year Door. It is the elder sibling of Hooktail and Gloomtail, and was once a pet of the Shadow Queen, but died of starvation after being stuck in the bottom of the Pit of 100 Trials.

Name: Boom Boom
Summary: Boom Boom is a short-tempered brute who works for Bowser.

Name: Bowser
Summary: Bowser, sometimes known as King Koopa (Japanese: 大魔王クッパ, Daimaō Kuppa or "Great Demon King Koopa"), is the main antagonist of the Mario series and the King of the Koopas. He has repeatedly kidnapped or attempted to kidnap Princess Peach and take over the Mushroom Kingdom. He has also attempted to conquer other lands, such as the Mushroom World, Dinosaur Land, Sprixie Kingdom, and even the entire universe. Despite his villainous nature, he has occasionally helped the heroes of the Mushroom Kingdom against common threats and participates with them in their numerous sporting events in spin-off games.

Name: Bowser Jr.
Summary: Bowser Jr., known in Japan as Koopa Jr. (not to be confused with Koopa Kid), is the secondary antagonist of the Mario series, and the youngest child of Bowser and the apparent heir of the Dark Land. He debuted in Super Mario Sunshine. He acts as the main antagonist of both Super Mario Sunshine, and New Super Mario Bros., with his father only playing a minor role in each. He is a playable character in various multiplayer Mario games. Since his debut, he has stolen the spotlight as the main villain from his father in a few Mario games.

Name: Byakuya Kuchiki
Summary: Even if I scatter and never bloom again

Name: Cackletta
Summary: Cackletta is an evil witch from Beanbean Kingdom and a major antagonist in Mario & Luigi: Superstar Saga.

Name: Candice Catnipp
Summary: Candice Catnipp (キャンディス・キャットニップ, Kyandisu Kyatonippu?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter, possessing the designation "T" - The Thunderbolt.

Name: Captain Falcon (Smash Bros)
Summary: Captain Falcon is a character that first appeared in the F-Zero series and eventually became famous thanks to his appearance in the very first Super Smash Bros game.

Name: Cathleen Bate (Star and Stripe)
Summary: Cathleen Bate (キャスリーン・ベイト Kyasurīn Beito), also known as Star and Stripe (スターアンドストライプ Sutā Ando Sutoraipu), is the No. 1 Hero of the United States of America.

Name: Chocobo (Chocobo's Dungeon)
Summary: Chocobo is the protagonist of the Chocobo series of Final Fantasy games. Young, brave, and curious, he is the partner of treasure hunter Cid.

Name: Coyote Starrk
Summary: Why do I have to fight with a strong guy like this? I always envied the weak. Whenever we made friends, their souls would waste away just from being near us. Because we were so alone, we split our soul in two. I don't know which was our original form. Or perhaps, it was neither. But this was the only way we had to escape from our isolation. I so envied the weak. The weak can always find others to be around. I want to be weak. And if that's impossible, I at least want to find companions who are as strong as I...

Name: Crazy Hand
Summary: Crazy Hand is the left hand, and as the name implies, chaotic counterpart of Master Hand. Originating in Super Smash Bros. Melee, he is an ally of Master Hand and can be fought together at a high enough difficulty, always on final destination. He returns in future games as a boss, having prominent roles in Super Smash Bros. for Wii U, where he has his own mode known Crazy Orders, along with Super Smash Bros. Ultimate, where he is a major character in the story mode.

Name: Crust
Summary: Shield Hero: Crust (シールドヒーロー クラスト Shīrudo Hīrō Kurasuto) was the No. 6 ranked Pro Hero of Japan.

Name: Crystal King
Summary: The Crystal King is one of the henchmen picked by Paper Bowser to guard a Star Spirit. When Paper Mario reaches the top of the Crystal Palace, the Crystal King fights him, but is defeated and disappears.

Name: Dabi
Summary: Dabi (荼毘) is a villain affiliated with the League of Villains and was a member of the organization's Vanguard Action Squad. Later on, his organization and the Meta Liberation Army merged into the Paranormal Liberation Front, and became one of its nine lieutenants.

Name: Dark Bowser
Summary: Dark Bowser is Bowser's final boss in Mario & Luigi: Bowser's Inside Story.

Name: Diddy Kong
Summary: Diddy Kong (ディディーコング Didī Kongu?) is a fictional character in the Donkey Kong series of video games, first appearing in the 1994 game Donkey Kong Country.

Name: Dieter
Summary: Dieter is a member of the Best Fitness Friends and one of the main antgonists introduced in Mario & Luigi: Bowser's Inside Story + Bowser Jr's Journey.

Name: Donkey Kong (Character)
Summary: Donkey Kong, (often abbreviated as "DK", or rarely Donkey), is a major character in the Super Mario franchise and the main protagonist of the Donkey Kong franchise. He is a powerful and carefree Kong that lives in Donkey Kong Island. He likes to collect bananas and spend time with his friends, particularly his best friend, nephew, and sidekick Diddy Kong. However, he has also been portrayed as an antagonist on multiple occasions, mainly in the Mario vs. Donkey Kong series.

Name: Donkey Kong (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Donkey Kong (ドンキーコング, Donkey Kong), oftentimes shortened to DK, is the eponymous protagonist of the Donkey Kong series. First premiering in the video game of the same name alongside Mario, he has since starred in a plethora of his own adventures while persisting in his rivalry against the plumber. As a member of the "perfect-attendance crew", Donkey Kong has been featured as a playable character in every installment of the Super Smash Bros. series.

Name: Doopliss
Summary: Doopliss is a reoccurring villain in Paper Mario The Thousand Year Door.

Name: Duck Hunt Dog (Super Smash Bros)
Summary: Duck Hunt Dog, also known as Duck Hunt Duo, which comprises of the classic dog, a duck, and the hunter, is a playable character in the Super Smash Bros. series. Originating in Super Smash Bros. for 3DS and Wii U, the dog throws various projectiles, the duck carries it around and assists the dog by extending its melee range, and the hunter fires at their opponents from far away.

Name: Duon
Summary: Duon is a giant mechanical being constructed out of Shadow Bugs. It was created after Mr. Game & Watch's defeat, although it was defeated again.

Name: Elder Princess Shroob
Summary: Elder Princess Shroob, or Princess Shroob, is the leader of the Shroob race who invade the Mushroom Kingdom in Mario & Luigi: Partners in Time.

Name: En'enra
Summary: En'enra is an ancient smoke-based youkai long since sealed. It has been recently unsealed by Kosuzu in order to get rid of a word-eating youkai, but broke free and started attacking Gensokyo. It was eventually sealed and defeated by Reimu and Marisa.

Name: Enel
Summary: Enel is the former "God" of Skypiea and the main antagonist of the Skypiea Arc. Two years ago, after his defeat by the Straw Hat Pirates, he arrived at the moon and became its new ruler.

Name: Enji Todoroki (Endeavor)
Summary: Enji Todoroki (轟炎司 Todoroki Enji), also known as Endeavor (エンデヴァー Endevā), is the Pro Hero with the highest tally of resolved cases in history, husband to Rei Todoroki, and father of Toya, Fuyumi, Natsuo, and Shoto Todoroki. Formerly the No. 2 Hero, he took the place of No. 1 after the retirement of All Might.

Name: Evil Natural Water
Summary: Evil Natural Water (エビル天然水てんねんすい, Ebiru Tennensui?) is a mighty being that works for the Monster Association, an elite group of horrifying creatures working to dismantle the Hero Association.

Name: Fawful
Summary: Fawful is a citizen of the Beanbean Kingdom who serves as a major antagonist in Mario & Luigi: Superstar Saga and Mario and Luigi: Bowser's Inside Story.

Name: Fumikage Tokoyami (Tsukuyomi)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Fumikage Tokoyami (常闇踏陰 Tokoyami Fumikage), also known as Tsukuyomi (ツクヨミ Tsukuyomi), is a member of Class 1-A at U.A. High School. An oddly dark and serious individual, his strange mannerisms belie his powerful Quirk and the heart of a true hero, earning him an internship under Hawks, one of Japan's top Pro Heroes.

Name: Galleom
Summary: Galleom is a boss in the Super Smash Bros. series, appearing first as a member of the Subspace Army serving Tabuu, and latter as a lackey of Galeem and Dharkon.

Name: Garou
Key: '''Hero Hunter''' | '''Half-Monster''' | '''Post-Darkshine''' | '''Post-Sage Centipede''' | '''Awakened Garou''' | '''Parallel Timeline Awakened Garou'''
Summary: Saitama: Hey, you got a little better again! Garou: You call this a little?!

Name: Gecko Moria
Summary: Gecko Moria is a villain from One Piece, and was a member of the Shichibukai. He resided on the largest ship in the world, Thriller Bark, and his Devil Fruit powers can manipulate shadows. His former bounty is 320,000,000 Beli. He is also the main antagonist of the Thriller Bark Arc who stole Brook's and various other beings' shadows with the use of the Kage Kage no Mi. He took part in the Battle of Marineford and sided with the Marines, along with most of the other Shichibukai. Upon the war's end, he was stripped of his title, and was to be eliminated by Donquixote Doflamingo, but managed to escape before he was killed. He was last seen travelling to the island of Hachinosu in search of his subordinate Absalom, and being given an offer to join Blackbeard's crew after finding out Absalom had been killed to poach his Devil Fruit.

Name: Geno
Summary: Geno (whose real name is ♥♪!?) is a warrior from Star Road and one of Mario's partners in Super Mario RPG: Legend of the Seven Stars.

Name: Genos (Demon Cyborg)
Key: '''Beginning of Series''' | '''House of Evolution to Alien Conquerors Arc''' | '''Post-VGS''' | '''Post-G4''' | '''Post-Superfight''' | '''Post-Elder Centipede'''
Summary: King: Mr. Genos risked his life to save Miss Tatsumaki. It was truly admirable! Saitama: So that's why! You really hung in there, Genos! Nice fight! Genos: Master... when the time came for me to self-destruct, I was no longer able to do it. Can one truly say I've become stronger? Saitama: I don't really get it, but you didn't blow up, right? [touches his core] That means this part here got stronger too, doesn't it?

Name: Gensokyo
Key: '''Average Humans''' | '''Fairies''' | '''Average Youkai''' | '''Stronger Individuals''' | '''Dragon God & Eirin Yagakoro'''
Summary: Gensokyo is a land hidden somewhere in Japan. Formerly mere an isolated region of the country infested by Youkai, it has now since been separated from the "Outside World" and now exists as one of the last places where Youkai and fantasy can thrive.

Name: Gerard Valkyrie
Summary: Gerard Valkyrie (ジェラルド・ヴァルキリー, Jerarudo Varukirī?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "M" - The Miracle, as well as one of Yhwach's Schutzstaffel (親衛隊シュッツシュタッフェル, Shuttsushutafferu?, German for "Protective Echelon", Japanese for "Elite/Imperial Guards"). He is also the heart of the Soul King.

Name: Geten
Summary: Geten is a former member of the Meta Liberation Army and is currently one of the nine lieutenants of the Paranormal Liberation Front. He's never attended a hero school and has spent most of his life training his Quirk. He firmly believes that strength equals one's worth and those who lack strength are worthless.

Name: Giant Catfish
Summary: The Giant Catfish (大ナマズ Oo Namazu) is a villainous avatar of Taisui Xingjun, a God of Calamity who sent assassins (disguised as familiar characters) to attack Hong Meiling in her dreams. Its objective, as it claims, was to drain her of her power so that it could move the Earth and return to this world once again. It also spoke quite strongly of its plans to cause various disasters to Gensokyo. ZUN and Twilight Frontier has left no official comment about the catfish and its gender is unknown.

Name: Giant Toad
Summary: The Giant Toad is the guardian of the pond named after itself. It is usually calm and gentle, even protecting the pond.

Name: Giga Bowser
Summary: Giga Bowser is the non-canon, more monstrous super form of Bowser in the Super Smash Bros. series, and the boss of the Adventure Mode and the final event of the Event mode in Super Smash Bros. Melee. He comes to be if one clears Adventure Mode on the Normal difficulty level or higher without using any continues. If so, after one beats Bowser, his trophy flies back up on the stage, gets struck by lightning, and Giga Bowser breaks out. During Super Smash Bros. Brawl and onwards, this form was relegated to Bowser's Final Smash.

Name: Gigantomachia
Summary: Gigantomachia (ギガントマキア Gigantomakia) is a villain associated with the League of Villains. He is one of All For One's faithful servants and his former bodyguard, later serving his successor, Tomura Shigaraki. He is an incredibly powerful force, considered a "walking disaster" by heroes.

Name: Gin Ichimaru
Summary: Gin Ichimaru (市丸 ギン, Ichimaru Gin) was the captain of the 3rd Division of the Gotei 13 until he betrayed Soul Society, alongside Sōsuke Aizen and Kaname Tōsen. His lieutenant was Izuru Kira. He formerly served as the lieutenant of the 5th Division under Sōsuke Aizen and the 3rd Seat of the 5th Division under Shinji Hirako.

Name: Giselle Gewelle
Summary: Giselle Gewelle (ジゼル・ジュエル, Jizeru Jueru?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Stern Ritter, possessing the designation "Z" - The Zombie.

Name: Godzilla (GMK)
Summary: The GMK Godzilla (ＧジーＭエムＫケイゴジラ, GMK Gojira?) is a kaiju that appeared in the 2001 Godzilla film, Godzilla, Mothra and King Ghidorah: Giant Monsters All-Out Attack.

Name: Godzilla (Kiryu Saga)
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:Godzilla1999-2004SFX.ogg

Name: Goomboss
Summary: Tier: High 6-A

Name: Goto Imasuji (Muscular)
Summary: Goto Imasuji (今筋強斗 Imasuji Gōto), also known as Muscular (マスキュラー Masukyurā), was a member of the League of Villain's Vanguard Action Squad. He lost his left eye to the efforts of Water Hose, a pair of Pro Heroes who defended a town he was attacking. Because of this, he appears at U.A.'s secret summer training camp to attack Water Hose's only son, Kota Izumi, forcing Deku to intervene and save the boy from the villain's wrath.

Name: Gremmy Thoumeaux
Summary: Gremmy Thoumeaux (グレミィ・トゥミュー, Guremī Tumyū?) is a Quincy and a member of the Wandenreich's Sternritter with the designation "V" - "The Visionary".

Name: Greninja (Super Smash Bros)
Summary: Greninja is a Water/Dark type Pokemon and the final evolution of Froakie. They are hailed as being as dangerous as any other known ninja. This specific Greninja witnessed the intense battles the Smash Bros fighters undertook, and entered it himself as a surprise entrance. He has stayed with his newfound fighting partners ever since.

Name: Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez
Summary: Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez (グリムジョー・ジャガージャック, Gurimujō Jagājakku?) is an Arrancar and was the Sexta (6th) Espada in Sōsuke Aizen's affiliated army.

Name: Hariet
Summary: Hariet is the second Broodal fought in Super Mario Odyssey. She is the only female Broodal. Although it is not confirmed, she seems to be the second-in-command of the 4 main Broodals, due to being fought right before Topper in Bowser's kingdom.

Name: Heavy Lobster
Summary: Heavy Lobster is a mechanical lobster-esque boss character who first appeared in Kirby Super Star.

Name: Heihachi Mishima
Summary: Heihachi Mishima (roughly translates to "Eighth Peace of the Third Island") is a fictional Japanese character in the Tekken fighting game series serving as one of the main antagonists. He is the son of Jinpachi Mishima, the father of Kazuya Mishima and Lars Alexandersson, the adopted father of Lee Chaolan and the grandfather of Jin Kazama.

Name: Hero Association
Summary: The Hero Association is an organization founded by the multi-millionaire Agoni after his grandson was saved from a monster by a passerby. Operating independently of the government, the Hero Association recruits various individuals, ordinary and extraordinary alike, to fight for justice against the evil in the world. Those registered within the National Hero Registry database are tasked with protecting civilians from harm against monsters, villains, natural disasters, and other threats and are compensated for their efforts.

Name: Hikone Ubuginu
Summary: Hikone Ubuginu (産絹彦禰, Ubuginu Hikone) a hybrid soul created by Tokinada to become the new Soul King.

Name: Hole Punch (Paper Mario)
Summary: Hole Punch is the eighth boss of The Origami King. After removing the sun from the sky, he hid within the singing Toad Temple.

Name: Hong Meiling
Summary: Hong Meiling (紅 美鈴) is a youkai, though it isn't currently known which specific category she actually belongs to. She's the gatekeeper of the Scarlet Devil Mansion. She is known for her mastery of the martial arts, part of which can be seen from her movement which is performed with Shin-Kyaku (a move in Chinese martial arts).

Name: Hood (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Hood (フード Fūdo), also known simply as High-End (ハイエンド Hai Endo), was one of Dr. Garaki's intelligent High-End Nomu and the primary antagonist of the Pro Hero Arc.

Name: Huff N. Puff
Summary: Huff N. Puff is the leader of the Ruff Puffs and main antagonist of the sixth chapter of Paper Mario. He uses a Puff-Puff Machine to cover Flower Fields in clouds, which threatens the lives of its plant inhabitants. When Paper Mario reaches him in Cloudy Climb, they fight, and Huff N. Puff is defeated.

Name: Ice Climbers (Smash Bros.)
Summary: The Ice Climbers are fighters from the iconic NES game Ice Climbers. First originating in Super Smash Bros. Melee, the Climbers, comprised of Popo and Nana, fight as a team together and use various ice-based moves based off their games. They appeared in it's sequel, Super Smash Bros. Brawl, but did not appear in Super Smash Bros. 4. They returned in 2018 in Super Smash Bros. Ultimate

Name: Ichigo Kurosaki (Post-Timeskip)
Summary: Ichigo Kurosaki (黒崎くろさき 一いち護ご, Kurosaki Ichigo?) is the son of Masaki Kurosaki and Isshin Kurosaki, a Quincy with the powers of a Soul Reaper. Years after the death of his mother, Ichigo uses his innate spiritual awareness to help local ghosts, and unlocks his potential as a Soul Reaper when Rukia Kuchiki comes along in pursuit of a Hollow.

Name: Ichigo Kurosaki (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''Substitute Soul Reaper''' | '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Post-Bankai Training''' | '''Post-Visored Training''' | '''Final Grimmjow Fight''' | '''Full Hollowfication''' | '''Post-Resurrection''' | '''Post-Dangai Training'''
Summary: Ichigo Kurosaki (黒崎くろさき 一いち護ご, Kurosaki Ichigo?) is the son of Masaki and Isshin Kurosaki, a Quincy with the powers of a Soul Reaper. Years after the death of his mother, Ichigo uses his innate spiritual awareness to help local ghosts, and unlocks his potential as a Soul Reaper when Rukia Kuchiki comes along in pursuit of a Hollow.

Name: Iggy Koopa
Summary: Iggy Koopa is one of the Koopalings, a clan of seven siblings that act as leaders of the Koopa Troop under Bowser (originally considered his children). Iggy is depicted as a crazed, mechanical genius and childish in personality when together with Lemmy Koopa. His two main outstanding physical characteristics are his glasses and light green hair (originally pink, light blue, and yellow). In later appearances, he is shown to be the thinnest and fastest of the Koopalings. Iggy is named after Iggy Pop, a famous punk rock singer and leader of the band The Stooges.

Name: Ikomikidomoe
Summary: Ikomikidomoe (已己巳己巴) is an ancient Hollow that attacked Soul Society in the past but was defeated by Ichibē Hyōsube and was sealed inside a Zanpakutō by Ōetsu Nimaiya.

Name: Incineroar (Super Smash Bros)
Summary: Incineroar is a fiery hotshot newcomer to the Super Smash Bros roster, being the only new Pokemon in its latest game. But he can more than back it up with his strength in the ring, his battle prowess earning him a spot as one of the toughest combatants to ever come out of the Pokemon series, his abilities allowing him to already fight blow for blow with the veterans. Like any cat however, he has a softer side, making friends with many of the younger, smaller Pokemon outside the ring.

Name: Isabelle (Smash Bros.)
Summary: Isabelle (しずえ, Shizue) is a playable character in Super Smash Bros. Ultimate. She is the 68th fighter overall. While she shares many moves with Villager, Isabelle is not an Echo Fighter and is instead a semi-clone.

Name: Ivan (Power Rangers)
Summary: Ivan, commonly refereed to as Sir Ivan of Zandar is a main character of Power Rangers: Dino Charge and Power Rangers: Dino Super Charge. He once lived as a proud knight of the kingdom of Zandar, but one day while waking the then prince of Zandar on an unknown trip, he encountered the ruthless Fury. After a fierce but short lived battle, he was captured by Fury but the prince managed to escape.

Name: Ivy Valentine
Summary: Isabella "Ivy" Valentine is a character in the Soul series of fighting games and a staple character of the franchise. Ivy is the daughter of Cervantes de Leon and is of cursed blood due to Cervantes having been possessed by Soul Edge when she was conceived. Her goal is to find a way to erase Soul Edge from existence, even if it means her dying because of her connection to the blade. Her Whip Blade Valentine is a living sword that was granted life by Nightmare's hand.

Name: Izuku Midoriya (Deku) (Final Act)
Summary: Izuku Midoriya (緑谷出久 Midoriya Izuku), also known as the One For All Hero: Deku (ワン・フォー・オール ヒーロー デク Wan Fō Ōru Hīrō: Deku), is one of the 20% of people on Earth who were born without a Quirk, a natural superpower that is a basic biological function in modern society, causing him endless torment at school. However, thanks to his innate heroism, he was able to earn the Quirk "One For All", bestowed upon him by his idol All Might, and use it to grow into one of the world's greatest heroes.

Name: Izuku Midoriya (Deku) (Pre-Final Act)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Endeavor Agency Arc'''
Summary: Izuku Midoriya (緑谷出久 Midoriya Izuku), also known as Deku (デク Deku), was one of the 20 percent of people on Earth to be born without a quirk, a natural superpower that is a basic biological function in the modern society, earning him endless amounts of torment and bullying in school.

Name: Jackie Tristan
Summary: Jackie Tristan (ジャッキー トリスタン, Jakkī Torisutan) is a Human who formerly possessed Fullbring powers and is a former member of the organization known as Xcution.

Name: Jesus Burgess
Summary: Jesus Burgess, nicknamed "Champion", is the helmsman and captain of the First Ship of the Black Beard Pirates. During this time his bounty was of 20,000,000 belly.

Name: Jigglypuff (Super Smash Bros.)
Summary: Jigglypuff (プリン, Purin), is a creature from the Pokémon series. It debuted in the series' first generation, and is considered part of the "perfect-attendance crew" throughout the entire Super Smash Bros. series.

Name: Jin Kazama
Summary: Jin Kazama is the son of Jun Kazama and Kazuya Mishima. Jun's intimate relationship with Kazuya grew and she became pregnant with Jin. Afterwards, Jun moved to a remote location in the mountains where she raised Jin and trained him in the Kazama family's self-defense fighting style.

Name: Jugram Haschwalth
