Summary: Rider of "Red" ("赤あか"のライダー, "Aka" no Raidā?) is the Rider-class Servant of the Red Faction of the Great Holy Grail War. While he is originally summoned by one of the Pentel brothers, he later becomes one of the Servants of Shirou Kotomine.

Name: Akantor
Summary: Akantor are Flying Wyvern in Monster Hunter.

Name: All-Hunt Grount
Summary: All-Hunt Grount is a Marine Captain and a major antagonist for the Marines Rookie filler arc. He was a subordinate to Admiral Aokiji. He was transferred to Vice Admiral Prodi's base, which is close to Big Mom's territory.

Name: Amatsu
Summary: Also known as the "Storm Dragon", Amatsu is an Elder Dragon with a unique body structure, similar to that of sea life, but floats in midair. Its body is covered with fin-like protrusions, and has a small head in relation to the rest of its body. Its body mass is assumed to be quite light, as it is able to literally swim through the storm that is always surrounding it. It resides on the Sacred Mountain, a mountain located in the Yukumo region near the Misty Peaks. It is said to be the personification of the storm and its power is comparable to a natural disaster. As a result, its appearance has become a Yakumo Village tradition.

Name: Astaroth (Soul Calibur)
Summary: Ares, the god of destruction, desired Soul Edge to dethrone his father, Zeus, so he ordered Kunpaetku, the grand priest of the cult order Fygul Cestemus, to seek it out. Astaroth, a golem, was created in hellish heat under the divine protection of Ares to head up the quest. Kunpaetku ordered his creation, Astaroth, to find the demonic blade. As he watched Astaroth depart from the shrine, the grand priest laughed to himself as he planned to keep the Soul Edge and become a god himself. Unknown to Kunpaetku, however, Ares had possessed Astaroth with his servants, the Keres, to ensure that Kunpaetku would not betray him.

Name: Astolfo (Rider of Black)
Summary: Template:Astolfo

Name: Atalanta (Fate)
Summary: Archer of "Red" is the Archer-class Servant of the Red Faction in the Great Holy Grail War. While she is originally summoned by Rottweil Berzinsky, she later becomes one of the Servants of Shirou Kotomine. She also appears in the First and Third Singularities of the Grand Orders, Orleans and Okeanos.

Name: Avicebron (Fate)
Summary: Caster of "Black" is the Caster-class Servant of the Black Faction in the Great Holy Grail War, summoned by Roche Frain Yggdmillennia.

Name: Azwel
Summary: Azwel is a character who first appeared in the reboot of the Soul series Soul Calibur Vl as one of the antagonists of the series. He serves as the main antagonist of the Libra of Souls Story. He calles himself the "Leader of Humanity" and plans to gather the power of both Soul Edge and Soul Calibur in order to create the Ultimate Seed.

Name: Bang (Silver Fang)
Summary: Bang (バング) also known as Silver Fang (シルバーファング Shirubā Fangu) is the now-retired former S-Class rank 3 superhero for the Hero Association. Settled in Z-City, Bang owns a dojo passed down from generations and uses the fighting style the Water Stream Rock Smashing Fist. He has an older brother named Bomb, who is the master of Whirlwind Iron Cutting Fist. He was also Garou's former mentor, but after the events of the monster association arc, they are once again master and disciple.

Name: Bazelguese
Summary: Bazelgeuse are Flying Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Berukyurosu
Summary: Berukyurosu are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Season 4.0.

Name: Black Sperm
Summary: Black Sperm (黒くろい精せい子し, Kuroi Seishi?) is a monster who first appeared during the S-Class Heroes' raid of the Monster Association.

Name: Bofoi (Metal Knight)
Summary: Bofoi, also known by his hero name of Metal Knight is an S-Class, Rank 6 superhero for the Hero Association. A genius, Bofoi is the creator of the Hero Association's headquarters and combats foes through remote-controlled combat drones. He seems to be uninterested in actual heroics and much more focused on his research.

Name: Bomb (One Punch Man)
Summary: Bomb (ボンブ, Bonbu?) is Bang's older brother as well as a dojo master. Even in his old age, Bomb remains tough and daring. His martial talents are on par with, if not superior than, Bang's. Bomb had defeated Bang in a duel when they were younger. Bang, who was misguided and belligerent at the time, eventually reconciled with his brother and followed in his footsteps, enrolling pupils and establishing a martial arts dojo.

Name: Brachydios
Summary: Brachydios is the Flagship Monster of Monster Hunter 3 Ultimate.

Name: Capone Bege
Summary: Coming from the West Blue, Capone "Gang" Bege is one of twelve pirates who are referred to as the "Worst Generation" and also the captain of the Firetank Pirates. Once a powerful Mafia boss in his native Blue, he became bored with his dominance of the underworld and decided to head out to sea to conquer and loot as many powerful pirate crews as he can. He's rather infamous for his sadism, high class attitude, and very short temper. However, his most prominent attribute is his direct approach to victory. Bege is a cunning and crafty opportunist who always goes after the head honchos and no one else, just to enjoy watching their organizations dissolve into chaos after he knocks off the boss.

Name: Carnage Kabuto
Summary: Carnage Kabuto (阿あ修しゅ羅らカブト, Ashura Kabuto?) was an artificial mutant created by Dr. Genus of the House of Evolution and is by far their strongest creation. He is an extremely unstable being while also being very intelligent (which Dr. Genus also confirmed to be true), but has an insatiable bloodlust and thus had to be locked up because he kept killing anything that got near him. He considers himself far superior to humans, calling himself a 'new human' that Dr. Genus was looking for, and believing that all should bow to his will. Carnage Kabuto is also very sarcastic and low-tempered, which is considered by Genus to be one of his main failures.

Name: Carrot (One Piece)
Summary: Carrot is a rabbit mink in the Warrior Beast Tribe, a member of the Inuarashi Musketeer Squad, and a ruler's aide. She is currently accompanying Luffy's "Sanji retrieval team" to Whole Cake Island and continued on with the crew to Wano Country.

Name: Ceadeus
Summary: Ceadeus is a massive underwater Elder Dragon which was introduced in Monster Hunter Tri/Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Chameleos
Summary: Chameleos are Elder Dragons introduced in Monster Hunter 2.

Name: Charlotte Cracker
Summary: Charlotte Cracker, also known as Thousand Arms Cracker, is the 10th son of Big Mom and Totto Land's Minister of Biscuits. He has eaten the Bisu Bisu no Mi, allowing him to produce large numbers of biscuit crackers and reshape them in any form he wishes. He usually inhabits and fights from the inside of an enormous biscuit puppet crafted with his powers, to the point his bounty poster depicts the puppet and not his real face. He was first revealed within the Wholecake Island arc when encountering Monkey D. Luffy and Nami. He is the first of the Three Sweet Commanders to have been revealed.

Name: Charlotte Daifuku
Summary: Charlotte Daifuku is a member of the Big Mom pirates and the third son of the Charlotte family, as a minister he has a high standing within the Big Mom pirates and is highly respected by his siblings, he was referred to as a "Monster" by Vito whilst mentioned in the same breath as his siblings Charlotte Katakuri and Smoothie.

Name: Charlotte Katakuri
Summary: The third of the Sweet Commanders to appear, Charlotte Katakuri is the second son of the Charlotte Family and the oldest of a set of fraternal triplets, his younger brothers being Daifuku and Oven.

Name: Charlotte Oven
Summary: The fourth son of the Charlotte family and a member of the Big Mom Pirates, he resides over Totto Land as its Minister of Browned Food. He is loyal to his family and was noted as one of several monsters by Vito who compared him to his siblings Katakuri and Smoothie.

Name: Charlotte Perospero
Summary: As the eldest son of the Charlotte family, Perospero is the Minister of Candy. He is highly respected among the Big Mom crew, and was entrusted with Caesar Clown's heart, and ensuring that he would finish the task assigned to him.

Name: Charlotte Smoothie
Summary: The second Sweet Commander to appear, Charlotte Smoothie is a longleg-human hybrid, the 14th daughter of Big Mom and the oldest in a set of triplets, her younger sisters being Citron and Cinnamon. She's Totto Land's Minister of Juice, and has eaten the Shibo Shibo no Mi, which allows her to squeeze juice out of any object, as well as absorb the liquid into her body or weapons to increase their size and power.

Name: Chiron (Fate)
Summary: Archer of "Black" is the Archer-class Servant of the Black Faction in the Great Holy Grail War, summoned by Fiore Forvedge Yggdmillennia.

Name: Chizuru Kagura
Key: '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '96 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Deviljho
Key: '''Deviljho/Savage Deviljho/Starving Deviljho''' | '''Aberrant Deviljho''' | '''Four Heavenly King Deviljho'''
Summary: Deviljho is a Brute Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Diablos
Key: '''Diablos/HC Diablos/Gilded Diablos''' | '''Black Diablos''' | '''HC Black Diablos''' | '''Bloodbath Diablos''' | '''Varusaburosu'''
Summary: Diablos is a large dangerous Flying Wyvern which inhabits the Monster Hunter world's desert regions. Despite being a herbivore, it's incredibly aggressive which has earned it the title of "Tyrant of the Desert".

Name: Drive Knight
Summary: Drive Knight is the S-Class Rank 9 superhero of the Hero Association.

Name: Dyuragaua
Summary: Dyuragaua is a Flying Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Season 8.0.

Name: Elder Centipede
Summary: Elder Centipede was a high ranking member of the Monster Association who first appeared in S-City, wreaking havoc and fighting the S-Class heroes Metal Bat and Bofoi.

Name: Empress of the Skies
Summary: The Empress of the Skies governs nature itself. At the beginning of it all, the Empress struck a deal with the Goddess of Decay, agreeing that the latter would be responsible for deciding how all living things should die. All the Empress had to do was ensure no organism would perish before their time.

Name: Eo Garudia
Summary: Tier: High 6-C

Name: Eruzerion
Summary: Eruzerion is an Elder Dragon introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Z.

Name: Espinas
Summary: Espinas, also known as the Thorn Wyvern, is an incredibly powerful species of Flying Wyvern that spends much of its time asleep within its territory. Infamously, its shell is so tough that it can simply sleep through most creatures' attempts to attack it, while its thorny exterior envenoms the same would-be attackers. Should a determined or dangerous foe cause it to stir, however, it flies into a murderous rage that can quell even Elder Dragons. It was first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Season 2.0.

Name: Flame Queen
Summary: Flame Princess (first name Phoebe and occasionally called FP) is the princess and ruler of the Fire Kingdom, as well as Finn's ex-girlfriend. When Jake asks Flambo if he knows any princesses that are Finn's age so he can fix his broken heart, he introduces Jake to Flame Princess. Flame Princess was locked away in a lantern in the main chamber of the Fire Kingdom when Jake first encounters her. It is later revealed that her father, the Flame King, put her there on Princess Bubblegum's advice when she was an infant, and she did not come out for 14 years. She has a short temper, trust issues, and a heat core that can destroy the world if overblown with emotions.

Name: Frankenstein's Monster (Berserker of Black)
Summary: nan

Name: Fubuki (Blizzard of Hell)
Summary: Fubuki (フブキ?), also known by her hero alias Blizzard of Hell is the B-Class Rank 1 professional hero of the Hero Association. She is an Esper, the younger sister of Tatsumaki, and the leader of the Blizzard Group, a B-Class hero faction. She and her sister are known as the Psychic Sisters. Fubuki is one of the few people who are aware of Saitama's strength and is currently trying to recruit him into her group. She's also a self-declared member of the Saitama Group.

Name: Fuhrer Ugly
Summary: Fuhrer Ugly is a Dragon level Mysterious Being and a member of the Monster Association. He is an Ugmon, an ugly human that became a monster due to his extreme amount of jealousy and self hatred.

Name: Gaismagorm
Summary: Gaismagorm, also known as the Abyssal Archdemon, is an enormous Elder Dragon that lurks in the depths of the earth. It possesses great physical strength as well as the ability to command swarms of flying lamprey-like Qurio, draining the life from entire ecosystems and empowering itself before emerging on the surface. Fifty years prior to the events of Monster Hunter Rise, it attempted to surface in the Kingdom and clashed with an Elder Dragon who had already claimed the region as its territory, Malzeno. It was first introduced in Monster Hunter Rise: Sunbreak.

Name: Garou
Key: '''Hero Hunter''' | '''Half-Monster''' | '''Post-Darkshine''' | '''Post-Sage Centipede''' | '''Awakened Garou''' | '''Parallel Timeline Awakened Garou'''
Summary: Saitama: Hey, you got a little better again! Garou: You call this a little?!

Name: Gearsper
Summary: Gearsper, C-Class Rank 133, is a professional hero and member of the hero association. He believes himself to have telekinetic powers similar to the esper sisters, and wears a large helmet so as to be able to control his full output. His belief was revealed to be true during his confrontation against Nyan, where he unleashed his full telekinetic output against the cadre before knocking himself unconscious.

Name: Genos (Demon Cyborg)
Key: '''Beginning of Series''' | '''House of Evolution to Alien Conquerors Arc''' | '''Post-VGS''' | '''Post-G4''' | '''Post-Superfight''' | '''Post-Elder Centipede'''
Summary: King: Mr. Genos risked his life to save Miss Tatsumaki. It was truly admirable! Saitama: So that's why! You really hung in there, Genos! Nice fight! Genos: Master... when the time came for me to self-destruct, I was no longer able to do it. Can one truly say I've become stronger? Saitama: I don't really get it, but you didn't blow up, right? [touches his core] That means this part here got stronger too, doesn't it?

Name: Gild Tesoro
Summary: Gild Tesoro is the main antagonist of One Piece Film: Gold. He is a non-canon character.

Name: Godzilla (GMK)
Summary: The GMK Godzilla (ＧジーＭエムＫケイゴジラ, GMK Gojira?) is a kaiju that appeared in the 2001 Godzilla film, Godzilla, Mothra and King Ghidorah: Giant Monsters All-Out Attack.

Name: Gore Magala
Key: '''Gore Magala''' | '''Chaotic Gore Magala''' | '''Shagaru Magala''' | '''Risen Shagaru Magala'''
Summary: Gore Magala debuted as the flagship monster of "Monster Hunter 4", being the main antagonist of the games low rank story.

Name: Great Jagras
Summary: Great Jagras is a monster introduced in Monster Hunter World.

Name: Groribas
Summary: Groribas was a member of the Dark Matter Thieves, a group of alien pirates that traveled across the universe. Despite being one of Boros' top fighters, he was killed instantly by Saitama.

Name: Grøh
Summary: Grøh is a character who appeared in the Soul series reboot Soul Calibur Vl. He serves as one of the main protagonists of the Libra of Souls storyline. He is a member of the Aval Organization, an organization form to clear the world of Malfested also known as "Outsiders" by Aval. Grøh is considered to be the strongest fighter of Aval and one of the most loyal members. Throughout the story, his goal is to hunt down and kill Azwel who betrayed the Aval Organization. But he also has a personal reason for going after Azwel as he forced him to kill his best friend Curtis after he turned him into a Malfested right before his eyes and having him try to kill Grøh. It turns out that Grøh is one of Azwel's successful experiment in terms of enhancing warriors with the power of Soul Edge shards. As such he technically counts as an "Outsider" and plans to kill himself once his job is done.

Name: Guanzorumu
Summary: Guanzorumus are Elder Dragons introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G10.

Name: Harudomeguru
Summary: Harudomerugu is an Elder Dragon first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G7.

Name: Hody Jones
Summary: Hody Jones is the main antagonist of the Fishman Island Arc and a firm follower of the radical Fishman pirate Arlong. He is a great white shark Fishman who since his childhood was exposed and bathed in the hatred for the human race and grew to hold a massive disliking toward them, willing to go to extreme lengths to maintain the animosity between them.

Name: Homeless Emperor
Summary: Homeless Emperor was once a common tramp who encountered a mysterious divine entity, who claimed to be "God", that gave him the incredible power of summoning energy spheres similar to little suns, which explode on contact and create huge flaming bursts.

Name: Inagami
Summary: Inagami is an Elder Dragon first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G5.

Name: Isamu (Child Emperor)
Summary: Child Emperor (童帝, Dōtei) is the S-Class Rank 5 hero for the Hero Association. So far, he is the youngest hero in the Hero Association. He has his own laboratory in Y-City.

Name: Ivy Valentine
Summary: Isabella "Ivy" Valentine is a character in the Soul series of fighting games and a staple character of the franchise. Ivy is the daughter of Cervantes de Leon and is of cursed blood due to Cervantes having been possessed by Soul Edge when she was conceived. Her goal is to find a way to erase Soul Edge from existence, even if it means her dying because of her connection to the blade. Her Whip Blade Valentine is a living sword that was granted life by Nightmare's hand.

Name: Jack the Ripper (Assassin of Black)
Summary: Assassin of Black is the Assassin-class Servant of the Black Faction in the Great Holy Grail War, originally summoned by Hyouma Sagara. However, she rejects him as a Master and instead chooses Reika Rikudou as her surrogate mother.

Name: Jeanne d'Arc (Ruler)
Summary: nan

Name: Kamikaze (Atomic Samurai)
Summary: Kamikaze (カミカゼ, Kamikaze?), also known by his hero alias Atomic Samurai (アトミック侍ざむらい, Atomikku Zamurai?), is the S-Class Rank 4 professional hero for the Hero Association.

Name: Keoaruboru
Summary: Keoaruboru are Elder Dragons introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Z.

Name: Kilik
Summary: Kilik serves as one of the major protagonists of the Soul series. Kilik is a young and kind warrior who shows great mastery with rod martial arts. He was a monk at the Leng Shen Su Temple until a night in which the Evil Seed arrived at the temple and drove him and the other monks mad. Thanks to Xianglian Kilik manages to regain his sanity at the cost of Xianglian losing hers. Kilik as a result was forced to kill her in order to defend himself. Afterwards an unconscious Kilik was picked up and taught by Edge Master.

Name: Kim Kaphwan (The King of Fighters)

Summary: Kushala Daora are Elder Dragons introduced in Monster Hunter 2.

Key: '''Prologue Chapter (KOF '94)''' | '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '95 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of NESTS Saga (KOF '99 to KOF 2001)''' | '''KOF Sky Stage''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Lagiacrus
Summary: Lagiacrus are a variety of Leviathan introduced in Monster Hunter 3. They are feared by sailors as the "Lords of the Seas" and are the apex predators of their aquatic environment.

Name: Lord Boros
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:BorosIntroduction.ogg

Name: Lord Boros' Ship
Summary: Lord Boros's Ship is the gigantic aircraft that he and the rest of the Dark Matter Thieves use to travel around space. It landed on Earth for the purpose of finding a legendary warrior of prophecy to give Boros the fight he had always yearned for.

Name: Lunastra
Summary: Lunastra is an Elder Dragon introduced in Monster Hunter 2.

Name: Luppi Antenor
Summary: Luppi Antenor was the 6th Espada in Sosuke Aizen's army for a short period of time, having temporarily replaced Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez after he lost his arm.

Name: Magnamalo
Summary: Tier: High 6-C | High 6-C

Name: Malzeno
Summary: Malzeno, also known as the Silver Duke Dragon, is an elegant Elder Dragon that inhabits the Kingdom's territory. It holds a mutual relationship with swarms of flying lamprey-like Qurio, capable of directing them to lure or kill its prey. It can drain the life energy of other living creatures through its fangs and from Qurio to grow its power, and when it gorges itself on sufficient life force, it enters a far more dangerous and violent form known as the "Bloodening". It was first introduced in Monster Hunter Rise: Sunbreak.

Name: Maxi
Summary: Maxi is a major character in the Soulcalibur franchise and serves as one of the 3 main protagonists of the original Soulcalibur. He is a pirate whose crew was attacked in slaughtered by the Golem Astaroth. As a result, he decided to travel with Kilik who he befriended in order to avenge his crew.

Name: Melzargard
Summary: Melzargard was one of the Dark Matter Thieves, a group of extraterrestrial pirates that traveled across space. He was one of Boros' strongest warriors tasked with protecting the ship, eliminating any intruders on sight. After the destruction of A-City, Melzalgald was engaged in battle by Iaian. However, the A-class hero was no match to the mighty alien and quickly lost his arm. Soon, Atomic Samurai, Bang, Metal Bat, and Pri-Pri-Prisoner arrived to fight the hostile alien. Following a lengthy and seemingly fruitless battle, Metal Bat discovered Melzargard's weakness (destroying the marbles on his body), allowing the heroes to eliminate the extraterrestrial being.

Name: Meraginasu
Summary: Meraginasu is a Burst Species Flying Wyvern first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G3.2.

Name: Mi Ru
Summary: Mi Ru are Flying Wyverns that was first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G2.

Name: Mitsurugi
Summary: Heishiro Mitsurugi was born the fourth son of a farmer in Bizen, Japan; but after many years of seeing his homeland ravaged by war, he decided to become a samurai. After his parents' death in his 14th year, he took a sword and the last name Mitsurugi. He went to train under the powerful warlord of the Murakami clan. At this time, Japan was in the middle of the Sengoku Jidai or "the age of the country at war" in which the feudal lords or "daimyos" attempted to claim the title of Shogun. Mitsurugi was a powerful force on the battlefield, and rumors of him spread like wildfire, heralding him as the warrior that could mow down foes like fields of wheat, and he was noted by Uesugi Kenshin and Oda Nobunaga as a great warrior. He received numerous military commendations and eventually reached the rank of commissioned officer in the Japanese armed forces. But all along, his only true desire was a worthy opponent.

Name: Monkey D. Luffy (Post-Timeskip)
Summary: Monkey D. Luffy (モンキー・Dディー・ルフィ, Monki Di Rufi?), known as "Straw Hat Luffy", is the main protagonist of the manga and anime, One Piece. He's the son of Monkey D. Dragon, a revolutionary considered “The World's Most Dangerous Criminal”; the grandson of Monkey D. Garp, a powerful Marine Vice-Admiral who had cornered the late Pirate King himself on several occasions; the sworn brother of late "Fire Fist" Portgas D. Ace and Revolutionary chief of staff Sabo; and the foster son of Curly Dadan. He seeks to find One Piece and become the Pirate King; to accomplish this, he founded the Straw Hat Pirates and set out on the high seas at age 17 in search of the elusive treasure, beginning a series of increasingly odd and dangerous adventures. He has eaten the Gum-Gum Fruit, which turned his body into rubber and gives him stretching powers; he's developed great mastery and creativity with his powers, creating two unique techniques with them: Gear 2nd, which makes him much faster, and Gear 3rd, which allows him to inflate any body parts for a stronger attack. During the time-skip, he has a new technique: Gear 4th, which makes him much stronger and faster than even the other two Gears, but with a considerable cost to it. With the support from Silvers Rayleigh and the desire to reunite with his crew after the Sabaody Island Incident and the Marineford War, he endured vigorous training on the island of Ruskaina where he learned the 3 forms of Haki, and out of the three, he specialized in “Haoshoku Haki”.

Name: Mordred (Saber of Red)
Summary: nan

Name: Morudomunto
Summary: Morudomunto is an Elder Dragon introduced in Monster Hunter Explore.

Name: Myo Galuna
Summary: Myo Galuna is a monster that has only been mentioned as a legend in the MH Orage manga.

Name: Mysterians
Summary: The Mysterians (ミステリアン) are a race of aliens created by Toho that first appeared in the 1957 film The Mysterians.

Name: Nakarkos
Summary: Nakarkos are Elder Dragons introduced in Monster Hunter Generations.

Name: Nameless (The King of Fighters)
Summary: nan

Name: Nami (One Piece)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypeia Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Sabaody Archipelago Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Whole Cake Arc''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Nami, also known by her epithet "Cat Burglar", is the navigator of the Straw Hats who was initially introduced as a thief who detested pirates and stole from them, tagging along Luffy with dubious loyalty to him. However, it is revealed that her surrogate home, the Conomi Archipelago, was occupied by the Arlong Pirates and she only wished to buy her home back. When Luffy freed the archipelago from Arlong’s grip, she fully joined the Straw Hats afterward.

Name: Namielle
Summary: Namielle, also known as the Abyssal Dragon, is an aquatic Elder Dragon that generates and manipulates water around its body to ensnare and batter its foes, and that injects them with huge amounts of electricity for the finishing blow. It is an extremely rare monster native to the New World's Coral Highlands region, and many visual aspects of its design are reminiscent of deep-sea life. It was first introduced in Monster Hunter World: Iceborne.

Name: Nargacuga
Summary: Nargacuga are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom Unite.

Name: Nefu Garumudo
Summary: Nefu Garumudo is an Elder Dragon introduced in Monster Hunter Explore.

Name: Nergigante
Summary: Nergigante is an Elder Dragon first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Nyan (One Punch Man)
Summary: Nyan is a Dragon level Mysterious Being and an executive of the Monster Association. He is a former housecat who turned into a monster after receiving too much unwanted love and attention from his owner.

Name: Nyarlathotep (VShojo Mythos)
Summary: Nyarlathotep is the emissary sent by Azathoth to light the beacon of chaos and bring an end to existence. Before heading to the farthest reaches of the expanse, she created a companion named Goro from the cosmic dust surrounding her. Goro was the one to give her the nickname, "Nyan." Once Nyan stumbled upon Earth, she began harvesting the sanity of humans to fuel the beacon. Nature itself rose to stop Nyan from reawakening her creators, stealing her powers and freezing her beneath the East Siberian Sea.

Name: Odibatorasu
Summary: Odibatorasu are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Forward.5.

Name: Oltura
Summary: Oltura is the main antagonist of Monster Hunter Stories 2: Wings of Ruin.

Name: Oni (Street Fighter)
Summary: Oni (鬼, Ogre), is a hypothetical character transformation from the Street Fighter series, first appearing in Super Street Fighter IV: Arcade Edition as an unlockable boss. This is the state Akuma takes when he has become one with the Satsui no Hado entirely, completely sacrificing any humanity he had left for ultimate destructive power.

Name: Overgrown Rover
Summary: Overgrown Rover is an enormous, doglike monster who appeared during the S-Class Heroes' attack on the Monster Association. Rover is a Dragon level threat and is by far one of the Association's most powerful monsters, albeit one of the least intelligent. It makes its first appearance when Garou attempts to rescue Tareo, blocking their escape. The beast proves incredibly dangerous, blasting Garou through the floor with its energy projectiles. When Saitama shows up, the creature attempts to stop him, but Saitama, seeing him as a dog, punches Rover down. Amazingly, this merely knocks the monster unconscious instead of killing it. However, Saitama was only holding back. Rover regains consciousness after a bit, only seeing Saitama again when he awakens. Orochi orders Rover to help him, but wisely, Rover ran away.

Name: Ozpin
Summary: Professor Ozpin is the headmaster of Beacon Academy, first seen in Volume 1 inquiring Ruby Rose about where she learned how to fight, her future goals, and her desire to join his school. He is frequently seen with his cane despite having no visible motor impairment.

Name: Pedro (One Piece)
Summary: Pedro of the Treetops is a jaguar mink and captain of the Guardians, he is also the former captain of the Nox pirates who were disbanded after getting defeated in Totto land. He is quite loyal to whoever he follows and can often resort too quickly to violence during tense situations. As a Guardian, he is willing to lay down his life in order to defend the Whale Forest against intruders, however when not on duty as a Guardian, Pedro can be very cautious and distrusting toward suspicious people, quickly preparing to use force against anyone he feels may be a threat to him and his friends even if they seem to be friendly.

Name: Phoenix Man
Summary: Phoenix Man is a Demon level threat, who first appears accompanied by Elder Centipede as part of the Monster Association. Phoenix Man is more civilized than other monsters, expressing care for his allies. However, that doesn't stop his desire to dethrone Monster King Orochi and become the most powerful monster alive.

Name: Poborubarumu
Summary: Poborubarumu is a Flying Wyvern first introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G6.

Name: Promoted Rook
Summary: Promoted Rook is a powerful fusion between Genos and Drive Knight and was used to fight against an escaping Psykos-Orochi fusion.

Name: Psykos (One-Punch Man)
Summary: "Third Eye" Psykos (サイコス, Saikosu?) is a former friend of Fubuki that turned into a monster within One-Punch Man. She used to be the soft-spoken, dorky colleague of B-Class Fubuki that wanted to make use of her telekinetic powers to help the world. But ever since a horrifying vision of the future led her to insanity, she became the terrifying leader of the Monster Association, a group that boasts some of the mightiest Dragon level threats in the world, of which include herself. Her power is on a level that seemed to gain some respect from Orochi.

Name: Puri-Puri-Prisoner
Summary: Puri-Puri-Prisoner is an S-Class hero, rank 16th dropped to 17th. He is an athletic and flamboyant homosexual man. He constantly checks out all the men he is attracted to and assaults them with no regard for their sexuality, which is why he is in prison despite being a hero. He repeatedly escapes from jail during his hero activities.

Name: Qurupeco
Summary: Qurupecos are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Rajang
Summary: Rajang is a Fanged Beast introduced in Monster Hunter 2.

Name: Raphael Sorel
Summary: Raphael Sorel is a fictional character in Namco's Soul series of fighting games. First appearing in Soulcalibur II, he can be viewed as its protagonist but came out as an antagonist. He eventually takes the role of Graf Dumas in Soul Calibur V and serves as that game's Nightmare.

Name: Rathalos
Key: '''Base/HC/Azure/HC Azure/Destruction Wyvern Rathalos''' | '''Flame Rathalos''' | '''Silver/HC Silver Rathalos''' | '''Dreadking Rathalos''' | '''Zenith Rathalos''' | '''Zerureusu'''
Summary: The flagship monster of the entire Monster Hunter series and one of only two monsters to have appeared in every game in the series. Rathalos is a type of monster known as a Flying Wyvern, and it uses the fire element as its primary weapon.

Name: Rathian
Key: '''Base/HC/Conflagration/Scorching Heat/Pink Rathian''' | '''HC Pink Rathian''' | '''Gold/HC Gold Rathian'''
Summary: Rathian is the female counterpart to Rathalos, and one of only two monsters, together with Rathalos, to appear in every game in the Monster Hunter franchise.

Name: Roronoa Zoro (Post-Timeskip)
Summary: Roronoa Zoro (ロロノア・ゾロ?), also known by his former epithet of "Pirate Hunter" after the Raid his new title of "The King of Hell", is the premier swordsman of the Straw Hat Pirates and a member of the Monster Trio. Recruited as a mildly notorious bounty hunter (hence his “Pirate Hunter” moniker), he is a monstrously powerful man who doesn't wield the power of a Devil Fruit, using a unique Three-Sword Style in a battle of his own creation, wielding a sword in each hand along with one in the mouth. Zoro mostly drinks and sleeps in his spare time (when he is not busy training to get stronger) but can become such a real demon in battle that many people often wondered why someone of his strength isn't the captain. Whenever he engages in a serious fight, he tends to tie a bandana around his head. Also, he has a horrible sense of direction.

Name: Rukodiora
Summary: Rukodiora are Elder Dragons introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Forward.1.

Name: Ryuji Yamazaki (The King of Fighters)
Key: '''Chapter of Orochi Saga (KOF '95 to KOF '97)''' | '''Chapter of Ash Saga (KOF 2003 to KOF XIII)'''
Summary: nan

Name: Saitama
Summary: Saitama (サイタマ?) is a human from Z-City who; through rigorous (sort of) training broke through his human limiters and achieved unbelievable strength and abilities. Never breaking a sweat, the name One Punch Man is fitting for the effortless wins Saitama has achieved through the series. Never going beyond a simple brawl, his sheer strength, speed, and power have effortlessly mowed down anyone in his way.

Name: Salem
Summary: An incredibly enigmatic figure from Remnant's forgotten past, Salem is the true main antagonist of RWBY.

Name: Sanji (Post-Timeskip)
Key: '''Fishman Island Saga to Early Whole Cake Island Saga''' | '''Late Whole Cake Island Saga to Early Wano Act 2''' | '''Late Wano Act 2''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Sanji Vinsmoke (サンジ・ヴィンスモーク, Sanji Vinsumōku?), more commonly known as "Sanji" is the crew's chain-smoking chef and a member of the Monster Trio. There is not a dish he cannot cook, a pretty girl he will not try to woo, or something he will not argue with Zoro over. As a chef, he believes that he cannot afford to harm his hands, and so uses a fighting style which uses only his feet called the "Black Leg Style" (Kuroashi no Waza).

Name: Satan (VShojo Mythos)
Summary: Eternal bliss. Fueled by a thousand, thousand souls that knew no better. Everlasting beauty. Fabricated. Unending peace. Upheld by condemning all who display excess of emotion. The blinding vanity of this shameless monument, made in praise to a creator that's been asleep for a billion years. It's palpable. Welcome, human souls, to the tenth circle of hell! A true testament to self-importance! Blind faith made manifest! Would be a shame if somebody fucked it up.

Name: Semiramis (Fate)
Summary: Assassin of Red is the Assassin-class Servant of the Red Faction in the Great Holy Grail War, summoned by Shirou Kotomine.

Name: Seong Mi-na
Summary: Seong Mi-Na is a fictional character in Namco's Soul series of fighting games. Min-Na is one of the reoccuring characters within the series and is known for her upbeat personality and nature. She has a notable connection to Yun-Seong as well as Talim. She is close friends with Hwang.

Name: Shingo Yabuki

It is unknown which of the five puppet Masters of the Red Faction first summoned him, and unlike the rest who eventually become the Servants of Shirou Kotomine, he forms a contract with Caster of Black when captured by the Black Faction.

Name: Superalloy Darkshine
Summary: Superalloy Darkshine (超ちょう合ごう金きんクロビカリ, Chōgōkin Kurobikari?) is the Rank 11 S-Class hero of One-Punch Man. He is among the strongest heroes in the Hero Association and one of the few capable of fighting Dragon-level threats.

Name: Taki
Summary: Taki is a fictional character designed for the Soul series of fighting games, making her debut in the first game of the series, Soul Edge (Soul Blade). She has thus far appeared in all the following games with the exception of Soulcalibur V, in which she was replaced by her student Natsu, who is now searching for her master.

Name: Talim
Summary: Talim is nicknamed The Last Priestess of the Winds, and true to that nickname, has the power to sway the wind and relies on earth's nature to guide her in her adventures, and most importantly in battle. She fights with dual Elbow Blades, and as said earlier, uses her advantage of wind control to give her an unpredictable edge during combat, being able to hop around and over the opponent at any moment.

Name: Tamago
Summary: Baron Tamago is a combatant of the Big Mom Pirates, who originates from the Longleg Tribe. He and his partner Pekoms are responsible for collecting the monthly payment of sweets from Fishman Island in exchange for Big Mom's protection.

Name: Tartaronis
Summary: Tartaronis is an Elder Dragon, first introduced in Monster Hunter Online.

Name: Teostra
Summary: Teostra are Elder Dragons introduced in Monster Hunter 2.

Name: The Admiral
Summary: The Admiral is one of the members of the First Fleet of the research commission, who ventured to the New World to colonize it and discover the mystery of the Elder Crossing. In this, The Admiral dedicated himself to exploring the locale, finding the Elder's Recess and tracking down Nergigante.

Name: The Hunter (Monster Hunter)
Summary: Hunters are the playable avatar of the Monster Hunter series.

Name: Tigrex
Summary: Tigrex are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom 2.

Name: Tira
Summary: Tira is a major antagonist from the Soulcalibur franchise and first appeared in Soulcalibur lll. Tira serves as by far the most faithful servant of Soul Edge and does anything to find suitable hosts for Soul Edge while helping it gather souls. Tira is a former member of the "Birds of Passage" assassin organization and is known as the "Bird of Death". One of Tira's most notable traits is the fact that she has a split personality.

Name: Tori Hanson
Summary: Tori Hanson is the Blue Wind Ranger and is the first female Blue Power Ranger, in the show's history.

Name: Ukanlos
Summary: Ukanlos are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom Unite.

Summary: Unknown is a species of Flying Wyvern introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier Forward.1.

Name: Vaal Hazak
Summary: Vaal Hazak is an Elder Dragon first introduced in Monster Hunter: World.

Name: Valstrax
Summary: Crimson Glow Valstrax are Elder Dragons introduced in Monster Hunter Rise.

Name: Velkhana
Summary: Velkhana, also known as the Ice Dragon or the Iceborne Wyvern, is a powerful and elegant Elder Dragon capable of controlling the cold via its icy breath and armor forged out of crystallized water vapor from the air. It is an exceptionally dangerous, but reclusive, monster that is known to most as just a fairy tale, but its ability to freeze large monsters solid in mere moments with its breath is no myth. It was first introduced in Monster Hunter World: Iceborne as its flagship monster.

Name: Vinsmoke Ichiji
Summary: "Sparking Red" Vinsmoke Ichiji is the eldest son of the Vinsmoke Famiy, making him both a prince of the Germa Kingdom and a commander in its military arm, Germa 66.

Name: Vinsmoke Judge
Summary: Vinsmoke Judge, also known as Garuda, is the king of the Germa Kingdom, the supreme commander of the Germa 66, and the patriarch of the Vinsmoke Family. He is also a skilled scientist, and a former research partner to the leading World Government scientist Vegapunk.

Name: Vinsmoke Niji
Summary: Electric Blue Vinsmoke Niji is the 2nd son of the Vinsmoke Family. Like the rest of his family, he is proud of his royal status and does not care for his servants.

Name: Vinsmoke Reiju
Summary: "Poison Pink" Vinsmoke Reiju is the eldest child and only daughter of the Vinsmoke Family, making her both the princess of the Germa Kingdom and a commander in its military arm, Germa 66.

Name: Vinsmoke Yonji
Summary: "Winch Green" Vinsmoke Yonji is the fourth son and youngest child of the Vinsmoke Family, making him both a prince of the Germa Kingdom and a commander in its military arm, Germa 66.

Name: Vlad III (Lancer of Black)
Summary: nan

Name: Voldo
Summary: Born in 16th century Italy, Voldo was a servant of the weapons merchant Vercci. Known as the Merchant of Death due to his business with the Spanish Armada, Vercci desired the Soul Edge for his collection and had Voldo to attempt expeditions with Cervantes de Leon. When Vercci heard that his possessions have been ransacked as a result of civil war in Italy, he had his personal fleet travel to an uninhabited island off the coast of Sicily in the Mediterranean Sea and dug a 50-mt deep shaft that would serve as his tomb and as a vault for his remaining fortune. After killing off the sailors under Vercci's orders, Voldo becomes the guardian of the Money Pit. But he would emerge from the Money Pit, either to continue the search for the Soul Edge or hunt down thieves that steal from the vault in his absence.

Name: William Shakespeare (Fate)
Summary: Caster of "Red" is the Caster-class Servant of the Red Faction in the Great Holy Grail War. While he is originally summoned by Jean Rum, he later becomes one of the Servants of Shirou Kotomine.

Name: Wind Serpent Ibushi
Summary: Wind Serpent Ibushi, also known as the Wind God Dragon, is a graceful azure Elder Dragon that spends its life high up in the atmosphere using special organs called "windsacs" across its body. It possesses great control over the wind and flight, able to create immense windstorms and move freely while twirling its body or while upside down without disorientation, giving it a divine, otherworldly mien. Its mate is Thunder Serpent Narwa. It was first introduced in Monster Hunter Rise.

Name: Xianghua
Summary: Chai Xianghua is a major character of the Soulcalibur series. She serves as the main heroine of Soulcalibur alongside Kilik and Maxi. She is a member of the Imperial Guard and is the chosen wielder of Soul Calibur (before Siegfried and later Patroklos) and aided Kilik in defeating Nightmare.

Name: Yama Tsukami
Summary: Yama Tsukami is an Elder Dragon introduced in Monster Hunter 2.

Name: Yoshimitsu (Soulcalibur)
Summary: Yoshimitsu is a reoccurring character in the Soul Calibur franchise. He is the leader of the Manji clan and is a thief who gives back to the least fortunate. After his Manji Clan was killed by Oda Nobunaga. Due to this, he is searching out Soul Edge in order to exact his revenge. It is implied that Yoshimitsu is the ancestor of the same Yoshimitsu from the Tekken series.

Name: Zinogre
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | High 8-C | High 6-C | 7-B

Name: Achilles (Fate)
Summary: Rider of "Red" ("赤あか"のライダー, "Aka" no Raidā?) is the Rider-class Servant of the Red Faction of the Great Holy Grail War. While he is originally summoned by one of the Pentel brothers, he later becomes one of the Servants of Shirou Kotomine.

Name: Agrias Oaks
Summary: Lady Agrias Oaks is a secondary character appearing in Final Fantasy Tactics, initially as a guest character working together with Ramza Beoulve through the story, finally joining him during the events of Chapter 2.

Name: Alatreon
Summary: Alatreon is a monster capable of destroying the world. Some locals even believe that the Alatreon is a god or demon which is transformed into an Elder Dragon. Alatreons are very territorial. This may be the reason why no other monsters live in the Sacred Land. Alatreon might attack most of its prey from the air, giving it an advantage over most other monsters. It also is very aggressive towards flying objects, mainly airships.

Name: Ancient Leshen (Monster Hunter)
Summary: An old Leshen that arrived through a portal to assume control over the Ancient Forest. Sometimes revered as an indigenous deity. Dwelling deep inside the forest, this creature uses their innate magic to control all flora and fauna within their territory. Resulted from a crossover between Monster Hunter World and The Witcher 3.

Name: Astolfo (Rider of Black)
Summary: Template:Astolfo

Name: Atalanta (Fate)
Summary: Archer of "Red" is the Archer-class Servant of the Red Faction in the Great Holy Grail War. While she is originally summoned by Rottweil Berzinsky, she later becomes one of the Servants of Shirou Kotomine. She also appears in the First and Third Singularities of the Grand Orders, Orleans and Okeanos.

Name: Azwel
Summary: Azwel is a character who first appeared in the reboot of the Soul series Soul Calibur Vl as one of the antagonists of the series. He serves as the main antagonist of the Libra of Souls Story. He calles himself the "Leader of Humanity" and plans to gather the power of both Soul Edge and Soul Calibur in order to create the Ultimate Seed.

Name: Behemoth (Monster Hunter)
Summary: The Behemoth is a crossover monster introduced in Monster Hunter World.

Name: Dalamadur
Summary: Dalamadur is a massive snake-like Elder Dragon approximately which dwarfs most other monsters in the series in terms of size. Dalamadur has razor sharp blades covering its whole body, and two large arms with sharp claws.

Name: Dire Miralis
Summary: Dire Miralis is extremely hostile to all living things and can destroy an entire ecosystem just from its intense heat. A Dire Miralis actually destroyed the Tainted Sea and killed all living things in the area, filling the water with blood, until it was driven off in ancient times. This monster is one that many hunters don't live to tell about.

Name: Disufiroa
Summary: Disufiroa is an Elder Dragon introduced in Monster Hunter Frontier G2.

Name: Geralt of Rivia (Monster Hunter)
Summary: Geralt of Rivia is a warrior from another world known as a Witcher. Transported to the New World by the magic of a Leshen, a powerful spirit of nature, he was enlisted by the Fifth Fleet to hunt down the creature, using his special skills in such a way that even the Hunter must respect.

Name: Gogmazios
Summary: Gogmazios is a giant Elder Dragon which was introduced in Monster Hunter 4 Ultimate. It utilizes the fire element, a special tar-like substance, which it uses to incapacitate its prey, and its giant size against those who dare attack it.

Name: Grøh
Summary: Grøh is a character who appeared in the Soul series reboot Soul Calibur Vl. He serves as one of the main protagonists of the Libra of Souls storyline. He is a member of the Aval Organization, an organization form to clear the world of Malfested also known as "Outsiders" by Aval. Grøh is considered to be the strongest fighter of Aval and one of the most loyal members. Throughout the story, his goal is to hunt down and kill Azwel who betrayed the Aval Organization. But he also has a personal reason for going after Azwel as he forced him to kill his best friend Curtis after he turned him into a Malfested right before his eyes and having him try to kill Grøh. It turns out that Grøh is one of Azwel's successful experiment in terms of enhancing warriors with the power of Soul Edge shards. As such he technically counts as an "Outsider" and plans to kill himself once his job is done.

Name: Hiyori Sarugaki
Summary: Hiyori Sarugaki (猿柿 ひよ里, Sarugaki Hiyori) is the former lieutenant of the 12th Division under Captains Kirio Hikifune and Kisuke Urahara, and currently a Visored.

Name: Nightmare (New Timeline)
Summary: Nightmare is one of the two main antagonist of Soul Calibur VI alongside Azwel. He is the host, wielder and living incarnation of the cursed sword, Soul Edge, the objective of most other characters in the story. Nightmare is merely the host body of Inferno and when defeated, Inferno takes over and combats the opponent if not try and coerce them into grabbing Soul Edge, transforming them into a new Azure Knight. This particular Nightmare has Siegfried as a host.

Name: Oltura
Summary: Oltura is the main antagonist of Monster Hunter Stories 2: Wings of Ruin.

Name: Ramza Beoulve
Summary: Ramza Beoulve, also known as Ramza Lugria, is the main protagonist in Final Fantasy Tactics. Third son of House Beoulve, son of Barbaneth Beoulve and a commoner woman of the Lugria family, Ramza is the younger half-brother of Dycedarg and Zalbaag, and the full older sibling of Alma.

Name: Siegfried (Soul Calibur)
Key: '''Original Siegfried''' | '''Siegfried with True Soul Calibur''' | '''New Timeline'''
Summary: Siegfried had played host to Soul Calibur and, ultimately, destroyed Soul Edge. After that epic battle, the knight returned home and enjoyed a brief period of peace. But deep down he knew his work was not over; the cursed sword's minions—the malfested—remained a serious threat. Realizing he couldn't stop them alone, Siegfried gathered his staunchest allies from his old clan known as Schwarzwind, he reformed the clan of thieves into a clan of mercenaries.

Name: Sophitia Alexandra
Summary: Sophitia Alexandra is a major character of the Soul Calibur series. She serves as the main protagonist of the original Soul Blade and is usually a major character working behind the scenes in later Soul Calibur titles. She was sent by the Greek God of Fire and forging Hephaestus in order to destroy Soul Edge and was granted to Omega Blade and Elk Shield in order to do so. She is credited with being the one to shatter Soul Edge during her fight with Cervantes.

Name: Soul Edge
Summary: Soul Edge also known as the Cursed Sword serves as the main weapon of Nightmare and overall the main antagonist of the entire Soulcalibur franchise. Soul Edge serves as the catalyst on basically all the events in the franchise. All Soul Edge cares for is the devouring of souls and pure destruction. It's release of the Evil Seed corrupted countless people across the world, driving them mad or even transforming them into monsters. Soul Edge's counterpart is Soul Calibur. Soul Edge is known to be able to shape shift in order to morph into a form that best fits its wielder.

Name: Toichiro Suzuki
Summary: Toichiro Suzuki is a major antagonist in the Mob Psycho 100 anime and manga series. He is the leader of the worldwide organization of Espers, Claw, and uses his army of psychic individuals to attempt to take control over the governments of the world. In reality, though, Toichiro only uses this to make some sort of mark on the world. even if it means causing mass destruction with no real end-goal.
